title: doodie's snowball cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and form into small balls.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheets close to bottom of oven at 325° for 30 minutes.
Immediately roll in powdered sugar to coat well.
Cool on waxed paper.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: frijoles
directions: Cook beans in water until done.
Cut bacon into small pieces and fry with onion until done.
Add bacon, onion, tomatoes, cilantro and jalapenos (optional) to beans and cook 15 more minutes.

title: coconut oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat margarine, sugar and egg.
Add the remaining ingredients. Make ball.
Press down with fork.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 12 minutes.

title: cheddar 'n turkey potato pie
directions: Cook and stir mushrooms and onion in margarine over medium-high heat for 3 minutes.
Stir in flour, tarragon and pepper.
Gradually stir in broth and milk; cook, stirring frequently until mixture thickens and comes to a boil, about 5 minutes.
Reduce heat to low; stir in turkey, mixed vegetables and 1 cup of cheese.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Stir 3/4 cup of cheese into hot mashed potatoes.
Spoon turkey mixture into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with potato mixture.
Place under heated broiler for 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese and paprika.
Place under broiler for 2 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sauteed mushrooms
directions: Wash and slice mushrooms.
Combine lemon juice, garlic and salt in a large skillet.
Add mushrooms and onion.
Cook over medium heat until hot.
Reduce heat and simmer 20 to 30 minutes until liquid is reduced.
Serve hot over steak or as a side dish.

title: apple-nut cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9-inch square or round cake pan.
In medium bowl, blend together applesauce, brown sugar and vanilla by hand or with a mixer.
Add flour, cinnamon and salt. Stir a few times to combine.
Add juice; blend well.

title: frying pan cookies
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, salt and dates.
Melt margarine in skillet; add date mixture.
Cook over low heat for 1 minute or until dates are very tender.
Remove from heat.
Add nuts and Rice Krispies.
Cool slightly.
Form into small balls; roll in coconut.

title: minute steak
directions: Place steaks in casserole.
Cover with cream of mushroom, cream of celery soup and 1 can of water.
Add chopped onion and dot with butter.
Place in preheated oven and cook 30 minutes at 300°.

title: mexaroni
directions: Cook macaroni and cheese as directed on package
Cook undrained tomatoes with green peppers until peppers are tender. Mix together and heat through.

title: cinnamon toast sticks
directions: Combine sugar and cinnamon and set aside.
Cut breadsticks in half lengthwise.
Dip each half in butter, roll in cinnamon mixture.
Twist each strip 2 or 3 times and place on ungreased baking sheets.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.
Let cool on wire rack.
Yields 16 toast sticks.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix ingredients in order given: eggs, cold water, salt, pumpkin, Wesson oil, sugar, cinnamon, pumpkin pie spice, nutmeg, soda, flour, vanilla and pecans.
Pour into lightly greased and floured loaf pans.
Mini loaf pans are better.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes for mini loaf.
Makes 9.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes for regular loaf.
Use tester to check center.

title: punch
directions: Mix limeade and lemonade together according to directions on can.
Add grapefruit and pineapple juice.
Stir in dry Kool-Aid. Add sugar to taste.
Punch should be slightly tart.
Freeze punch until slushy.
Add 7-Up or ginger ale before serving.

title: bean salad
directions: In small saucepan over medium heat, bring sugar, oil, vinegar and salt to boil.
Chill.

title: stuffed shells
directions: In skillet, brown beef, onion and garlic.
Drain; cool.
Stir in cheese, crumbs, parsley, and egg.
Season with salt and pepper. Cook shells.
Use meat mixture to stuff shells.
Spoon 1/4 of sauce over bottom of baking dish.
Place shells on top of sauce.
Pour remaining sauce over shells.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: my mother's rhubarb sponge pie
directions: Beat egg yolks in a bowl.
Add flour and melted butter.
Stir milk in slowly.
Add sugar and lemon juice.
Mix well.
Stir in beaten egg whites.
Arrange rhubarb in pie shell and pour mixture over it.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes and then reduce to 350° for 30 minutes.

title: veal parmigiano
directions: Pound veal until very tender.
Season with salt and pepper. Beat egg and 1 tablespoon of water.
Dip meat in egg mixture, then in bread crumbs.
Brown in shortening.
Arrange veal in shallow baking dish.
Mix soup, water, onion, garlic and thyme.
Pour over veal.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: egg nog
directions: Whip cream until stiff, adding 1/2 c. sugar one tablespoon at at time.
Break eggs and separate.
Beat egg yolks slowly adding 1 c. sugar.
Beat until sugar is dissolved and the mixture smooth. Whip egg whites to frothy peaks by adding 1/2 c. sugar one tablespoon at a time.
Mix yolks with bourbon, add whipped cream and fold in egg whites.
Sprinkle with nutmeg and serve.
Yields 8 servings.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Melt butter; pour over mixture and mix well.
Reserve some crumbs for topping.
Press into bottom and sides of jelly roll pan.
Cover with cherry pie filling.
Sprinkle with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour, then at 300° for 15 minutes.
Serves about 20.

title: cheese ball
directions: First four ingredients get to room temperature.
Mix well and form into ball.
Roll in chopped nuts.
Refrigerate.
Can be made a day ahead.
Set out in time to come to room temperature for serving.

title: scotcharoos
directions: Bring the syrup and sugar to a boil.
Remove from heat immediately and stir in peanut butter and Rice Krispies.
Spread into buttered cookie sheet and smooth with rolling pin.
Pour melted chocolate and butterscotch morsels over top.
After morsels become hard, cut into desired size pieces.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Bake brownies according to box directions and let cool. Crumble 1/2 into bowl.
Mix pudding according to box directions and pour 1/2 over brownies.
Layer 1/2 of Cool Whip, 1/2 of Heath bars and 1/2 of nuts on top of pudding.
Repeat with remaining 1/2 of ingredients.

title: sloppy joe chocolate cake
directions: Cream eggs with sugar; add cocoa, then alternate milk with flour.
Add baking powder, baking soda and water; mix.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: apple fritters
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients and mix well.
Sift together flour and baking powder.
Mix flour mixture with apple mixture.
Drop into deep hot oil; drain and dust with powdered sugar to serve.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar. Beat in eggs and mix in pumpkin.
Mix nuts with dry ingredients and add alternately with boiling water.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: dirty rice
directions: Brown flour in oil until it is a deep red-brown, stirring constantly to prevent burning.
Add onion, celery, green peppers and garlic.
Cook until vegetables are tender.
Stir in beef, pork, giblets and seasonings.
Continue cooking until meat loses its red color.
Blend in broth, cover and simmer 25 minutes.
Stir in rice and onion tops.
Cook 5 minutes longer.
Mixture should be slightly moist.
Serves 6.

title: tropical lemon pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In small bowl, combine vanilla wafer crumbs and margarine.
Mix well. Press firmly onto bottom and sides of 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes. Cool completely.

title: delicious cheese ball
directions: Chop smoked beef until fine.
Mix with cream cheese (slightly softened) and Ranch dressing.
Make into 2 balls of equal size. Roll each ball in chopped pecans.
Serve with crackers.
Keep balls refrigerated.
However, they taste better after sitting out of refrigerator for awhile.

title: spinach salad
directions: Several hours before preparing salad, or night before, put small amount of red wine oil and vinegar dressing mixed with garlic salt in refrigerator.
Peel off and wash fresh spinach. Dry well (a hair dryer helps).
Mix spinach with oil and garlic salt from refrigerator.
Cut or slice hard-boiled eggs and crumble crisp bacon into salad.
Toss and serve.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour in 9-inch deep unbaked pie shell. Cook at 325° to 350° until thick, about 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Melt margarine.
Add sugar, cocoa and milk.
Mix well over low heat.
Increase heat and bring to a boil. Boil for 2 minutes. Remove from heat and add oatmeal and peanut butter.
Mix well. Drop by tablespoon onto wax paper.
Let cool.

title: cranberry-apple pie
directions: Preheat
oven
to
Line 10-inch pie pan with pie crust. Mix
apples
and cranberries and put half of the fruit in
the bottom
of the pie crust.
Mix water, apple juice and lemon juice. Drizzle half of the liquids over the mixed fruit in the pie crust.
Mix cornstarch, sugar, nutmeg, cinnamon and apple
pie spice.
Sprinkle half of this dry mixture over the fruit
in the pie crust.
Repeat layers of mixed fruit, liquid and
dry mixtures.
Cube butter and distribute across the top. Put top crust in place;
crimp edges and using a fork or knife tip,
make multiple
punctures
in
the top to allow steam to escape.
Bake in 425° oven for 10 minutes; lower heat to 350° and
bake
for
50 additional
minutes.
Allow to cool before serving.
Makes 1 pie.

title: colored rotini with tofu(an original recipe)
directions: Heat pan.
Add oil.
Saute tofu 2 to 3 minutes.
Add green beans, reserved juice, tomatoes and noodles.
Heat about 5 minutes or until hot.
Place on serving platter.
Top with Parmesan cheese, wheat germ and sunflower seeds.

title: mercedes buns
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch baking pan with nonstick spray and set aside. Roll out dough on a lightly floured surface to a 9 x 12-inch rectangle. Use your hands to stretch dough if necessary. Brush top of dough with 1/2 melted butter. Mix brown sugar and cinnamon in a small bowl. Sprinkle 3/4 sugar mixture over dough. Spread evenly to edges. Roll up dough jellyroll style. (You should end up with a 12-inch long loaf.) Pinch edges to seal. Using a very sharp serrated knife, slice loaf into 12 equal pieces. Arrange pieces close together in baking pan. Cover with a kitchen towel and let rise in a warm place until double in size (about 1 hour).

title: date sticks
directions: Sift flour once; add baking powder and salt gradually to eggs; add butter.
Beat in dates and nuts.
Add flour alternately with hot water, beating well.
Divide mixture into two greased pans, 8 x 8 x 2-inches, spreading batter thin.
Bake in slow oven, 325°, for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool; cut in strips, 2 3/4 x 1-inch. Remove from pans and roll in powdered sugar.
Makes about 48.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Place sliced zucchini, onion and butter or margarine in skillet and brown.
Stir stewed tomatoes, spaghetti sauce mix and mushrooms together.
Gently stir into the zucchini mixture.
Pour into casserole dish and top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 325° until cheese melts.

title: caramel dip
directions: Heat until melted.
Bring to a boil.
Stir constantly 2 minutes.

title: chicken-cabbage bake
directions: Arrange cabbage wedges in deep 3-quart baking dish.
Top with half the onion rings and water.
Sprinkle with 1 teaspoon of bouillon, 1/4 teaspoon nutmeg and 1/8 teaspoon of pepper.
Place chicken breast on top and add remaining onion rings.

Sprinkle with remaining bouillon, nutmeg and pepper. Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Remove cover and adjust oven to 375° and bake for 15 minutes more or until chicken is brown and fork-tender.

title: shrimp gumbo
directions: Boil the chicken in a large container until you can separate bones when cool.
Add tomatoes and other ingredients. Cook slowly, approximately 2 hours.
Add shrimp and cook until tender. Add bay leaves; simmer. Serve over rice.

title: stuffed quahogs
directions: Spread cream cheese in 8 x 8-inch foil pan or casserole dish. Mix other ingredients, except cheese and chips, and place on top of cream cheese.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: chicken in a biscuit
directions: Boil chicken breasts, debone and chop.
Mix chicken, cheese and melted butter.
Form fist shaped balls and roll in crescent rolls. Bake at 375° until brown.
While the rolls are baking, mix the soup, broth and milk.
Pour over rolls and put back in oven until mixture thickens, 15 to 20 minutes.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients first and add the rest.
Cook and stir constantly over medium heat until thick.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla. Pour in baked pie shell and cover with meringue.
Brown in oven. Triple for 2 large pies.

title: pea soup
directions: Saute vegetables in butter for 10 minutes.
Add soup, beer and broth; mix.
Simmer 10 minutes or until beer stops foaming.

title: apple swirl cake
directions: Peel, core and chop apples into small pieces.
Mix together with 3 teaspoons sugar and cinnamon.
Set aside.
In large bowl, combine sugar and flour.
Beat.
Add eggs, orange juice and vanilla.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Beat until smooth.
Pour 1/3 batter into greased and floured 12-cup Bundt pan, alternating with 1/2 apple mixture. Repeat.
End with layer of batter on top.
Bake at 325° for 60 minutes or until done.
Cool in pan 10 to 15 minutes.
Turn out to cool.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: apricot salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add marshmallows and stir until marshmallows are dissolved.
Add 1 cup of mixed apricot and pineapple juice and chill slightly.
Add apricots and pineapple and let set until firm.

title: chicken noodle dish
directions: Saute onion, celery, bell pepper and mushrooms in oleo.
Cut boiled chicken in pretty large pieces.
Sprinkle chicken with lemon juice.
Add vegetables and cup of broth to soups.
Heat but do not boil.
Fold in cheese, noodles, chicken and Worcestershire.
Bake 325 for 30-35 minutes.
May freeze then bake later.
Makes three 1 quart casseroles.

title: soy-sesame marinade
directions: Combine all
ingredients; stir until well blended.
Use to marinate beef or lamb before grilling.
Yields 1/2 cup.

title: homemade tomato soup
directions: Add butter and 1/2 cup water to tomatoes in boiler.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bring to rolling boil for 2 minutes.
In a cup, mix cornmeal and 1/4 cup water, then finish filling cup with sweet milk.
Stir well; add to tomato mixture, continuing to stir well.
Cut off heat and cover with lid.
Allow to sit for 10 minutes, then serve.
This is good with hot cornbread.

title: easy banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding and milk as directed.
Fold in Cool Whip.
In Pyrex dish, layer pudding, bananas and vanilla wafers, beginning and ending with pudding.
Sprinkle with crushed wafers.
Good for church dinners.

title: ham and cheese rice skillet
directions: In large skillet over medium heat, saute celery, onion and ham in oil about 2 minutes or until celery is crisp-tender.
Stir in rice, water, salt and thyme.
Bring to boil; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer about 20 minutes or until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed.
Stir 1/2 cup cheese into rice mixture; cook until cheese melts.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese and serve at once.

title: souped-up rice
directions: Melt butter in medium Pyrex dish in 350° oven.
Add soups and rice.
Cook, uncovered, approximately 20 minutes or until all liquid is absorbed.

title: chicken with roasted garlic, mushrooms and spinach(4 servings)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place garlic on small baking sheet; pour 1 tablespoon olive oil over and toss to coat.
Bake until soft, 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool garlic.
Press garlic between fingertips to release from peel.
Transfer garlic to bowl.
(Can be prepared 1 day ahead, cover and refrigerate.)

title: shrimp dip
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Fold in as much shrimp as you want.
Better if you let sit overnight.

title: texas fresh apple cake
directions: Mix apples and sugar together; let stand 1 hour to form its own juice.
Stir often.
Sift together dry ingredients and add to apples, then add oil, vanilla and eggs.
Stir by hand.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: fruit slush
directions: Boil water and sugar to rolling boil; remove from heat and cool.
This will be thin.
Combine remaining ingredients.
You can add other fruits, such as strawberries or grapes, whatever you like.
Combine sugar water and ingredients.
Freeze in large bowl. Remove from freezer 1/2 hour before serving.
This mixture can be refrozen.
A double recipe of this makes a large bowl and a small bowl.

title: freezer corn
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large electric frypan.
Heat, stirring often to prevent sticking.
When the corn starts to bubble, continue cooking for 3 minutes.
Cool corn thoroughly, then pack into freezer bags and freeze for future uses.

title: 1-2-3-4 cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and then other ingredients. Pour into greased Bundt pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pinwheels
directions: Blend first three ingredients in medium bowl until smooth. Take tortillas out of bag and spread mixture from the middle to outer edges.
Roll tortillas up from the farthest edge toward yourself.
Wrap in Saran Wrap (wrap each tortilla individually) and refrigerate for 2 hours.
Unwrap and slice into pinwheels.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Heat juices and marshmallows slowly until marshmallows are melted (stir constantly).
Set aside to cool.
Put in blender to stir in cream cheese which has reached room temperature.
Add fruit and nuts.
Pour into cans fruit was purchased in and freeze. When ready to serve, run water over cans until the contents will come out.
Slice and serve on lettuce leaves.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine all the ingredients.
Use chicken broth to be sure mixture is very moist.
Top with 1 cup crushed cornflake crumbs or herbal stuffing and 2 tablespoons margarine.
Bake about 35 minutes in 350° oven.

title: eggplant and tomato casserole
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Heat butter in skillet and add onion, mushrooms, green pepper and garlic.
Saute until vegetables are limp.
Add eggplant, tomatoes, parsley, salt, pepper and oregano. Cover and simmer until eggplant is tender.
Uncover and increase heat if needed to reduce liquid.

title: cheese hot dogs
directions: Place cheese on wiener in open bun. Wrap in napkin.
Microwave 30 seconds on High or until cheese melts.

title: chocolate fudge pie
directions: Mix all
ingredients
and
place
in pie shell. Bake in oven at	350° for about 30 minutes. Do not overbake.
This pie has custard texture. Serve warm with ice cream.

title: martha washington
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
After set, make into balls. Melt chocolate and wax over top of double boiler.
Dip balls into mixture and drop on waxed paper to dry.
Recipe can be halved.

title: sweet potato and apple casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Peel sweet potatoes.
Cut in half lengthwise, then cut into 1/2-inch slices.
Grease a 2-quart casserole or baking pan with 1 tablespoon butter.
Mix brown sugar, cinnamon and mace or nutmeg in small bowl.
Place 1/3 of potatoes in baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt to taste.
Crumble half sugar mixture over potatoes; dot with 1 tablespoon butter. Slice apple quarters into wedges.
Layer half of apples over potatoes.
Repeat layers.
Top with remaining potatoes and 1 tablespoon butter.

title: mex rice
directions: Brown onion and rice in canola oil until light brown.
Add water, cumin and garlic powder.
Cook rice mix for about 10 minutes.
Add tomato sauce and green peppers and cook about 5 minutes.
Check rice to see if it is done.
Turn off.
Rice will soak up water.
Cover; let stand.

title: meat balls
directions: Melt grape jelly in slow cooker, add chili sauce. Add meat balls to sauce until sauce can barely cover the meat balls. Cook 2 hours or until meat balls are hot.

title: dump it all cake
directions: In a 9 x 11-inch casserole dish; add cherry pie filling and crushed pineapple.
Mix together.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over top of cherry and pineapple mixture evenly.
Sprinkle pecans over dry cake mix.
Slice oleo across top of pecans.
Bake at 350° until brown and bubbly around edges.
Good by itself but extra good with Cool Whip or vanilla ice cream.

title: pork and peanut stir-fry(our favorite stir-fry)
directions: Slice pork into thin narrow strips.

Combine 2 teaspoons each cornstarch and soy sauce, ginger and pork; let stand 15 minutes. Meanwhile, combine remaining 2 teaspoons cornstarch, 2 tablespoons plus 1 teaspoon soy sauce, vinegar, garlic powder and 1/2 cup water; set aside.
Heat 1 tablespoon oil in hot wok (or a large skillet).
Add pork and stir-fry 2 minutes; remove.
Heat remaining 1 tablespoon oil in same pan.
Add onion and carrot; stir-fry 2 minutes.
Add zucchini; stir-fry 2 minutes.
Add pork and soy sauce mixture.
Cook, stirring, until sauce boils and thickens.
Stir in peanuts.
Good served over rice.
Serves 2 to 3.

title: pone
directions: Bake in hot oven (400°) for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate and peanut butter pie
directions: In a blender, sprinkle unflavored gelatin over cold milk; let stand 2 minutes.
Add hot milk and blend at low speed until gelatin is completely dissolved, about 2 minutes. Add peanut butter and sugar; mix until well blended.
Pour into prepared crust set on a large plate; sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Place in refrigerator and chill until firm, about 3 hours.
Serve.

title: barbecued scalloped potatoes
directions: Combine milk, catsup, Worcestershire and Tabasco sauce.
Pour over layered potatoes and onion.
Liquid should barely cover potatoes.
Dot with oleo.
Put bay leaf in center submerged.
Cook slowly at 325° to 350° about 75 minutes, until potatoes are done. Remove bay leaf before serving.

title: zucchini parmesan
directions: Arrange zucchini in 9-inch baking dish.
Dot with butter. Cover with plastic wrap.
Microwave at High 4 to 6 minutes, or until tender-crisp.
Drain.
Combine cheese, parsley, salt and pepper; sprinkle over zucchini before serving.

title: bean curd soup
directions: Boil chicken broth.
Add rest of ingredients except green onions.
Heat.
Add green onions just before serving.
Serves 6.

title: marinara sauce
directions: In large saucepan, heat oil over medium heat.
Add garlic and saute for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add parsley and onion.
Slowly add tomatoes.
Stir to break up tomatoes.
Add bay leaf, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer on low about 15 minutes.
Serve over pasta dishes or with rice.

title: easy ice cream shop pie(from cool whip)
directions: Step 1:
Pour half and half into large bowl.
Add pie filling mix.
Beat with wire whisk until well blended, 1 minute.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Cook the rice and allow to cool.
Mix with the ingredients except for the tomato juice.
Core the cabbage, pour boiling water over cabbage to loosen the leaves.
Put about one handful of meat mixture in each leaf and fold over and place, fold side down, in large pan.
Pour tomato juice over the cabbage rolls and cook for 1 hour on top of stove with a lid on.
May require a little longer cooking time.

title: barbecued pork ribs
directions: Place trimmed ribs in large covered casserole.
Add onion and hot water.
Bake in 350° oven or in microwave at 50% power until tender.
Drain.
Cover with barbecue sauce and heat until flavored blend well.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Coat chicken according to package directions.
Place breaded pieces skin up in an 8-inch square baking dish or 10-inch Corning Ware skillet without metal trim.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover. Cook in microwave oven 14 minutes.
Rearrange chicken pieces in corners toward center.
Cook, uncovered, 7 to 9 minutes longer or until done.
Total cooking time:
22 minutes.
Recipe yields 4 servings.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Drain and chop artichoke hearts.
Add mayonnaise, Parmesan cheese, garlic salt, hot sauce and Worcestershire sauce.
Stir well and spoon into lightly greased small casserole or souffle dish. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Garnish with fresh parsley. Serve with toast points, crisp raw vegetables or Frito-Lay corn chips.

title: easy shrimp creole
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter (5 minutes).
Stir in soup and water.
Bring to a boil; add shrimp and simmer 10 minutes. Thicken with 2 teaspoons cornstarch (thinned with water).
Serve over hot rice.

title: boiled chocolate icing
directions: Mix together sugar, cocoa and salt, then add milk and cook until forms a soft ball.
Add butter and vanilla; beat with a mixer or by hand until smooth and put on Old-Timey Yellow Cake.

title: homemade chicken and dumplings
directions: Cook chicken, cool, debone and chop, reserve broth, set both aside.

title: tomato pudding
directions: Combine brown sugar, tomato puree and water.
Cook 5 minutes. While tomato mixture is cooking, put bread cubes in casserole and pour melted butter over them.
Pour on hot tomato mixture.
Do not stir.
Bake 50 minutes in 325° oven.

title: mexican black-eyed peas
directions: Sort and wash peas.
Soak overnight.
Brown sausage until it crumbles.
Add onion.
Cook until tender and then drain fat. Drain peas.
Stir in sausage and other ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Cover.
Reduce heat and simmer 1 1/2 hours or until peas are done, tender but not falling apart.
Add more water slowly if necessary.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Place 2 inches apart on an ungreased baking sheet.
Bake until lightly browned but still soft, at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes. Makes 5 dozen.

title: zucchini appetizers
directions: Mix ingredients.
Turn out into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cut into 1-inch squares and serve warm or at room temperature.
May be frozen successfully.

title: hamburger and macaroni casserole
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add all ingredients, except macaroni.
Cook on low for 20 minutes.
Cook and drain macaroni.
Add all together and cook slowly for 15 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: pecan puffs
directions: Beat butter until soft.
Add sugar and blend until creamy. Add vanilla; blend.
Add
flour and pecans; blend.
Roll into small balls.
Bake on greased cookie sheet 300° 25 or 30 minutes. Roll while hot in confectioners sugar.
Reroll in sugar when cool.

title: strawberry-banana smoothie
directions: Put all ingredients into a blender.
Blend until smooth.

title: banana cream pudding
directions: Mix the vanilla pudding and milk until thick. Add sour cream and half the whipped topping. Layer vanilla wafers, bananas and pudding, another layer wafers, bananas and pudding. Top with remaining whipped topping. Chill a few hours.

title: tryon palace ginger cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix oil and sugar thoroughly.
Add egg and beat well.
Stir in molasses.
Stir dry ingredients; add to mixture.
Drop by teaspoonfuls in reserved sugar and form balls coated with sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet 3 inches apart.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Cookies will flatten and crinkle. Remove to cool.
Yields 5 dozen.

title: strawberry swirl cake
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°. In a medium-sized bowl, with an electric beater on medium speed, beat all the ingredients except the gelatin mix for 2 minutes or until creamy. Pour one third of the batter into a 10-inch Bundt or tube pan that has been coated with nonstick cooking spray. Sprinkle evenly with half of the gelatin mix. Repeat the layers with the batter and gelatin, then top with the remaining batter. Bake for 45 to 50 minutes or until a wooden toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean. Let cool for 5 minutes, then invert onto a wire rack to cool completely. Serve or cover until ready to serve.

title: barbecue
directions: Brown hamburger and mix rest of ingredients.
Boil 15 minutes.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown ground meat and drain.
Add soups, tomatoes and taco sauce to meat.
Mix well.

title: chicken salad casserole
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together; spread in 9 x 11-inch dish. Top with stuffing.
Spread melted butter over all.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° until bubbly.

title: new applesauce walnut cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease and flour 2 round cake pans. Put dry cake mix, butter, applesauce, eggs and cinnamon into a large bowl.
Beat 4 minutes at medium speed.
Stir in walnuts. Turn into pan and spread evenly.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Follow package directions for doneness.
Cool.
Frost with Mocha Frosting.

title: sesame seed cookies(recipe may be cut in half)
directions: Mix flour and baking powder.
Cut in lard.
Add sugar, eggs and milk.
Roll into rope and roll in seeds.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.
Use 1/2 of given amounts to make a half recipe.

title: fresh apple spice cake
directions: Combine oil and sugar; beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Stir.
Add dry ingredients to sugar mixture, beating well.
Add vanilla; mix well.
Stir in pecans and apples. Pour batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until cake tests done.

title: cookie salad
directions: Beat pudding and milk and add the remaining ingredients. Before serving, add 1/2 package of fudge striped cookies (crushed in large pieces).
Garnish with crushed cookies on top!

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks; beat.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt; add to butter mixture.
Add vanilla.
Gradually add milk.
Beat reserved egg whites; fold into batter.
Add 1/2 of grated chocolate.
Pour into large, oblong greased and floured pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Sprinkle chocolate bits over top of cake.
Bake at 350° for about 50 minutes.
Remove cake from oven; sprinkle with remaining German chocolate.
Dust with 10x sugar.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all and spread in a 9-inch pan. Cover with topping.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Place meat and water in 5-quart soup kettle.
Add salt, pepper, bay leaf and garlic, bring to boiling point; reduce heat and simmer about 1 hour.
Shred cabbage coarsely and add tomatoes, vinegar or lemon juice and a little more salt to taste.
Simmer gently for another 1/2 hour.
Brown the flour in the margarine, until light brown.
Add a little of the soup liquid, stirring constantly.
Thicken the soup with the mixture.
Add chopped parsley and dill.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add eggs, oil, carrots and vanilla; beat until combined.
Stir in pineapple, coconut and nuts.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool.
Frost with cream cheese icing.
Sprinkle with nuts or additional coconut.

title: salmon patties
directions: Drain salmon.
Add eggs and flour.
Mix; it will be thick. Take 1/2 cup salmon liquid and add to baking powder.
Beat until foamy.
Pour into salmon mixture.
Drop 1/2 teaspoon into hot oil. Use enough oil that will cover the patties well.
Fry until golden brown.
Drain onto paper towel.
Serve hot.

title: quick onion soup
directions: chop onion, sprinkle with 1 Tbsp. sugar.
Cook in saucepan with margarine until carmelized.
Add 1 c. onion rings and wilt. Add beef broth and water. Cook for 10 minutes.
Pour over tiny cubes of cheese in deep bowls.
Top with toast rounds and grated cheese.
Brown under broiler.

title: round steak in sherry
directions: Cut steak in pieces 1-inch by 2-inches.
Brown in oil.
Add onion and sherry and bake one hour at 325°.
Cover with lid.
Add cream of mushroom soup and bake another hour.

title: fudge frosting
directions: Mix all ingredients except vanilla in saucepan.
Stir over low heat until shortening and chocolate are melted.
Boil 1 minute or until candy thermometer reads 220°.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla.
Beat until thick enough to spread.

title: pasta con broccoli
directions: Cook mostaccioli and broccoli separately according to package directions.
Simmer half and half, butter, garlic and mushrooms for 10 minutes.
Add broccoli to half and half and bring to a boil.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Pour Parmesan cheese into mixture.
Cool until thickened.
Add cooked pasta and mix lightly.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Chop the artichokes and chilies and mix together with the mayonnaise.
Add a handful of Parmesan cheese and mix together in an ovenproof dish with cover.
Place the remaining Parmesan cheese on top and cover.
Cook at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 2 (9 x 5 x 3-inch) loaf pans. In medium bowl, mix dry ingredients.
In large bowl at medium speed, beat sugar and shortening until fluffy.
Beat in eggs, pumpkin and water until blended.
At low speed, beat in flour mixture until blended.
By hand, stir in nuts and raisins.
Spoon into loaf pans.
Bake for 65 to 75 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pans for 10 minutes. Remove from pans and cool on wire racks.
Serve at room temperature.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Mix coconut and nuts.
Press into 9 x 13 pan.
Mix cake as directed.
Put in pan.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and margarine. Drop onto cake mix using a teaspoon.
Bake at 350° for 45-60 minutes until cake is cracked on top but done.

title: orange slice applesauce cake
directions: Mix applesauce, pecans and raisins in large mixing bowl.
Sift spice cake mix into this.
Add eggs.
Stir in candy orange slices and candied cherries.
Pour into tube or long loaf pan lined with wax paper.
Bake in moderate 350° oven about 50 or 60 minutes. Test for doneness.

title: mary's cranberry salad
directions: Mix together cream cheese, mayonnaise and sugar and add the remaining ingredients.
Mix together and freeze in mold.
(Double recipe for big ring mold.)

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: *If using self-rising flour, omit baking powder and salt.

title: nancy's barbecue
directions: Brown the roast in a large stew pot. When seared on all sides, add all of the above ingredients. Cook covered on medium heat until roast flakes apart when fork is inserted. Remove roast to a flat cutting board and flake meat way from any bone or grizzle. Return flaked meat to juices and cook, uncovered, until reduced to a thicker sauce. Serve over hamburger buns. Serves 6-8.

title: hobo meal
directions: In foil, place hamburger and the desired amounts of onion, potatoes, carrots and 2 ice cubes per Hobo Meal.
Season to taste and butter.
Wrap well, sealing all edges of foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 25 minutes.

title: rice pudding
directions: Cook rice in water for 20 minutes or until done.
Separate eggs and beat yolks well and mix in rice and mix well.
Add margarine, sugar, extract and coconut.
Let cool to get correct consistency.
If needed, add a little milk.
Beat egg whites, add 6 tablespoons sugar.
Egg whites should be stiff before spreading on pudding.
Brown in moderate oven, approximately 4 minutes.

title: beanie weinie
directions: Combine. Bake at 350° for approximately hour.

title: venison chili
directions: Mix oil, onion and meat and brown.
Add all other ingredients and simmer for 2 hours or until you get hungry.

title: linguine with clam sauce
directions: Saute garlic in oil in medium saucepan until golden. Blend in flour.

Gradually stir in remaining ingredients except linguine. Cook over medium-low heat, stirring constantly, until sauce is thickened. Cook linguine according to package directions. Drain. Serve with clam sauce.
Makes about 4 servings.

title: corn casserole
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper to soften.
Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: impossible pie
directions: Mix well in a bowl.
Pour into 2 greased pie plates.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
(Makes its own crust.)

title: chicken broccoli bake
directions: Arrange chicken in baking dish.
Drizzle butter over chicken. Bake in 375° oven for 40 minutes.
Place broccoli around chicken. Blend soup, milk and cheese; pour over chicken and broccoli.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake an additional 20 minutes.
Serve with rice.

title: biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°. Grease cookie sheet or baking pan. Combine dry ingredients, sift together. Cut in shortening with a pastry blender. Stir in milk with fork until mixture forms a soft lightly 10-12 strokes. Pat out to about 1/2 inch thickness,
cut with biscuit cutter. Place on prepared pan, brush tops with melted butter or grease. Bake 10 minutes, or until biscuits are golden brown. Do not overbake. Makes 10-12 biscuits.

title: mock hare soup(3 to 4 persons)
directions: Chop vegetables; put in pan with dripping and fry thoroughly. Add oatmeal and cook until brown, stirring all the time to prevent burning.
Add seasoning, cloves and stock and cook 1/2 hour on low heat.
Sieve before serving; add meat essence and reheat.
(GE)

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: In bowl, combine meat, crumbs, eggs and 2 teaspoons bouillon; shape into 1 1/4-inch balls.
In large skillet, brown meatballs. Remove from pan.
Pour off fat.
In skillet combine preserves, lemon juice and 2 teaspoons bouillon.
Over low heat, cook and stir 15 minutes.
Add meatballs; simmer uncovered 10 minutes. Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: hamburger-vegetable casserole
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Put into the bottom of a square casserole dish.
Put frozen mixed vegetables over the top.
Mix chicken soup with water.
Pour over meat and vegetables.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Cover top with Tater Tots and bake for 15 minutes more.

title: lime congealed salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water; add Coca-Cola.
Put in fridge until partly set.
Add pineapple and nuts.
Return to fridge until set.

title: gumdrop cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Drop from a teaspoon onto ungreased baking sheets.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes. Cut gumdrops in eight, omit licorice ones.
As you cut up gumdrops, mix with part of cake mix to prevent clumping together.

title: chocolate-candy jumbo christmas cheesecake
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients; press mixture on bottom and 1 1/2 inches up sides of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Sprinkle chopped nougat bars evenly over bottom.
Set aside.
Beat cream cheese with mixer until light and fluffy.
Gradually add sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Stir in chocolate morsels and vanilla.
Beat until blended.
Spoon over candy layer.

title: husband's delight(hamburger casserole)
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Add tomato sauce and sugar. Simmer about 15 minutes.
Cook noodles.
Layer noodles, meat, cream cheese, sour cream and Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: shrimp vegetable quiche
directions: Saute carrots, celery and onion in margarine; add allspice. Combine milk, Egg Beaters and cheese.
Bake 9-inch pie crust for 5 minutes.
Put in vegetables, shrimp, then egg mixture.
Bake 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: deva's nacho dip
directions: Brown sausage and drain off fat.
Mix in both cans of soup. Heat over low to medium heat.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix all together, except strawberries.
Cook until clear and thick.
Cool a little and fold in the cleaned berries.
Pour into a baked pie shell.
Serves 8.

title: crock-pot barbecue
directions: Put ingredients in crock-pot.
Cook until well done.
Drain and remove any bones.
Cut into small pieces. Season with last 4 ingredients.

title: apartment 10 lasagna
directions: Mix 1 egg with 2 cups of cottage or Ricotta cheese.
Shred Mozzarella cheese.
Cook lasagna noodles.

Layer in the following manner in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan...starting at the bottom: noodles, sauce and hamburger, cottage or Ricotta cheese, Mozzarella cheese, noodles, sauce and hamburger, cottage or Ricotta cheese, Mozzarella cheese.
Sprinkle top layer with Parmesan cheese. Sprinkle top with parsley flakes.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: tropical dream cake
directions: Beat sugar and oil together.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Add pineapple (undrained) and vanilla.
Mix dry ingredients and blend into batter.
Stir in bananas.
Turn into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes. Cool in pan for 10 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli and cauliflower florets in bite size pieces.
Mix together in bowl, adding green onions, bacon bits and shredded cheese.
Mix mayonnaise and sugar together in small bowl, blending well.
Pour over broccoli mixture.
Refrigerate overnight.
Stir well when ready to eat.

title: snappy "unfried" chicken
directions: Coat the chicken in salad dressing mix, then bake skin side up at 325° for 30 minutes.
Add seasoning to top of chicken.
Bake an additional 15 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix beans, corn, soup, onion and Cheddar cheese.
Pour into buttered casserole.
Melt butter.
Combine with crackers, crushed. Stir in almonds.
Pour over top of vegetable mixture.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: In large mixer bowl, combine the following ingredients well: water, pumpkin, oil and eggs, then add these ingredients, which have been sifted together: flour, soda, cinnamon, cloves, salt and sugar.
Mix well.
Grease about 6 small loaf pans.
Put batter in the pans and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Beat cream cheese and mayonnaise until smooth.
Add Worcestershire sauce and other ingredients.
Slowly blend in grated cheese.
Shape into ball and roll in 1/2 cup crushed pecans.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Put broccoli in shallow greased casserole dish.
Combine next four ingredients.
Add croutons.
Pour over broccoli and bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: apple cobbler
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons of butter in baking dish; take flour, 2 tablespoons butter, 1/2 cup of sugar and 1/2 cup milk.
Make dough.
Take the butter in baking dish and pour soft dough on top of it.
Pour boiling water over dough.
Add 1 cup sugar and apples.
Stir up together. Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Any kind of fruit will work.

title: chili party wings
directions: Clean wings.
Mix dry ingredients in a plastic bag.
Shake wings a few at a time in bag until coated.
Place in a single layer in well-buttered shallow baking pans.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes.
Turn wings and bake until tender, about 10 minutes more.

title: shrimp sea island
directions: Combine all ingredients except onions and shrimp.
Layer shrimp and onions in casserole dish.
Pour marinade over layers and cover.
Refrigerate for 12 hours.
Serve ice cold.

title: zucchini
directions: Shred 1 pound washed zucchini using coarse grater.
Melt just enough butter to cover bottom of skillet (or for no-fat, spray with nonstick spray).
Saute a little onion until soft.
Add zucchini and cook and stir over medium heat 1 to 3 minutes.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Squash will be crispy and delicious.

title: nippy nuts
directions: Cover a jellyroll pan with waxed paper; set aside.
In a large bowl, combine cinnamon, ginger, nutmeg, red pepper and 1/4 cup of the sugar; set aside.
In a medium skillet, melt butter; stir in nuts, the remaining 1/2 cup of the sugar and 1 teaspoon water; cook and stir over medium heat until sugar melts and nuts start to brown, about 10 minutes.
Stir nuts into spice mixture, tossing to coat; spread on prepared pan and cool completely, then break into small pieces.
Store in a tightly covered container at room temperature.

title: strawberry fig preserves
directions: Mash figs, add sugar and jello.
Boil until thick.
Seal in jars.

title: cheesie potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes until tender. Cool and skin. Coarsely grate into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Spread evenly in pan. Sprinkle with salt.
Melt margarine and add half and half.
Pour over potatoes.
You may need to add a little milk to adjust for the dryness of your potatoes.
Top with grated cheese.
These can be made in advance and refrigerated before baking. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until cheese is bubbly.

title: quick and easy brownies
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan.
Stir in coconut and sugar.
Turn off flame.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well with wire whisk after each addition.
Blend in vanilla.
Add flour, stirring until blended.
Turn into greased 9-inch square pan.
Top with pecans. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: hello dolly bars
directions: Melt margarine in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs over melted margarine.
Sprinkle coconut over graham cracker crumbs.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over coconut. Sprinkle pecans over chocolate chips.
Pour milk over chopped pecans.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool in refrigerator for 15 minutes.
Mark in squares, cool a while longer and then cut into squares.

title: a tart sauce for broccoli, asparagus, cauliflower, etc.
directions: Cook the first 5 ingredients together, then add the cream or half and half and the egg.
Cook a little longer.
Add mixture to cream and egg, then add to original pan.

title: peanut butter blossoms
directions: Mix in order given.
Roll into balls size of walnuts, then roll in sugar.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Top immediately with a chocolate kiss, pressing into the top.

title: freezer cole slaw
directions: In a large bowl, combine vegetables with salt.
Let stand 1 hour.
Bring remaining ingredients to a boil and boil 1 minute. Cool.
Drain vegetables and add to vinegar mixture.
Stir gently. Put in freezer containers and freeze.
When ready to use, defrost and serve chilled.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Grease 3 medium size loaf pans.
Use electric mixer and add ingredients in order listed.
Bake for 40 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: easy as pie pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend all ingredients in a blender, then pour into a buttered, glass pie pan.
Bake for about one hour.
Remove from oven and let sit until cool.
Makes its own crust.

title: watergate salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine whipped topping with dry pudding and mix.
Add drained pineapple and marshmallows.
Stir gently.
Top with cherries.

title: pineapple-cheese salad
directions: Heat pineapple, sugar and lemon juice.
Dissolve gelatin in 1 cup water; add to first mixture.
Let cool in refrigerator until it begins to thicken.
Remove from refrigerator and add grated cheese and whipping cream.
Pour into Pyrex dish; return to refrigerator until thick.

title: blueberry syrup
directions: Bring ingredients to a boil.
Crush berries with the back of a spoon.
Serve warm.
Optional:
Add 2 tablespoons butter before serving.

title: ham and egg bake
directions: Grease a square baking dish, 8 x 8 x 2-inch. Mix biscuit mix, milk, salt, mustard, parsley and eggs in the dish with a fork until batter is of uniform color. Stir in remaining ingredients. Bake uncovered until a knife inserted in center comes out clean, about 45 minutes in a 350° oven.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: clear grape jelly
directions: Thaw grape juice.
Combine
the sugar and water in an 8 quart kettle and bring
to a full rolling boil.
Boil hard for 1 minute. Remove from
heat
and stir in the fruit pectin and the
grape juice.
Mix
well.
Pour
into
sterilized
jelly glasses and seal with paraffin.

title: creamy colada punch
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart pitcher or punch bowl, stir cream of coconut and pineapple juice until well mixed.
Add ginger ale, stirring gently.
Serve immediately.
Makes 10 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: salmon pattiessocorro, new mexico
directions: Roll into balls (use the other half of crackers) cover with ground crackers.

title: crumbly crispys
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Add beaten eggs and shortening. Drop by spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets.

title: cranberry pineapple salad
directions: Mix gelatin with boiling water; add cranberries and pineapple with juice.
Mix well.
Let mixture gel in refrigerator.
Fold in celery and nuts.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: impossible seafood pie
directions: Place shrimp, green onions, Cheddar cheese and cream cheese in a greased 10-inch pie pan.
In a mixing bowl add Bisquick, milk and eggs.
Beat together with a mixer and pour on top of shrimp mixture.
Bake for 30 minutes on 400°, or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix broccoli, soup mix, water chestnuts and almonds in glass baking dish.
Melt margarine 40 to 50 seconds on Full power.
Pour over broccoli.
Microwave on Full power, covered, 10 to 20 minutes. Top with croutons before serving.

title: chris and sara's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Combine flour, salt and baking soda in a medium bowl.
Set it aside.
In a larger bowl, combine butter, vanilla extract, brown sugar and granulated sugar.
Beat butter, extract and sugars until creamy.
Add eggs and beat.
Add flour, salt and baking soda combination in three increments, beating with each addition. Spoon in chocolate chips, stirring manually.
Spoon batter, 1 teaspoon servings maximum, onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes or until cookies are light brown and firm looking.

title: cauliflower soup
directions: Cut up all vegetables, add bouillon and barely cover with water; cook until tender.
Cool slightly; add milk (as you would for potato soup).
Add margarine and cut up cheese.
Cook slightly until cheese is melted.

title: quick bread
directions: Melt 1 tablespoon shortening in 5 x 8-inch pan or glass baking dish and pour batter in on hot greased pan.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: shrimp, broccoli and cheez whiz
directions: Heat large skillet until hot and add 1/4 cup olive oil.
Let cook 1 minute and add shrimp.
After 1 minute, turn shrimp over. When shrimp are almost cooked (they will be bright red), add cognac and cook until cognac is burned off, then add cream cheese and Cheez Whiz.
Heat at medium heat until smooth.
When smooth, add all other ingredients and cook low for 3 minutes.

title: chicken strip tortilla wraps
directions: Heat oil in frying pan. Wash in cool water the chicken strips; toss in flour and cook in oil until tender and juicy. Place 2 strips on tortilla. Add toppings you desire and roll up.

title: congealed salad
directions: Add water to jello and melt.
Set in refrigerator to thicken, slightly.
After thickens, add other ingredients, stirring well. Return to refrigerator to congeal, approximately 6 hours.

title: citrus punch
directions: Juices should be chilled.
Stir together juices and soda. Spoon in sherbet.
Serve immediately.

title: parmesan potatoes
directions: Coat potatoes with oil and pepper. Bake at 400° until tender inside, crusty outside.
Sprinkle with cheese and basil when done.

title: mixed nut bars
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together and press into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Spread nuts over cooled crust.
Melt chips, butter and syrup; pour over nuts and bake 10 minutes more.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar; add eggs.
Add wafer crumbs alternately with milk.
Add vanilla, nuts and coconut.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Freezes real well, is very moist.

title: goldenrod eggs
directions: Make white sauce by melting butter in top of double boiler, adding flour, milk and other ingredients and cooking until thick. Add chopped eggs and pour over toast.
(White sauce can be prepared in microwave.)
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: sweet potato puree
directions: Cook carrot slices in boiling water to cover, 15 minutes or until very tender; drain.
Using food processor, place carrots and other ingredients, process until smooth, stopping to scrape down sides.
Yields 6 servings (0.3 g fat).

title: flounder florentine
directions: Spray baking dish with vegetable spray of choice.
Cover bottom with fish; may use fish of choice.
Combine thawed spinach, bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese and mix to spreading consistency and spread evenly over fish.
Top with more cheese.
Bake, covered, at 375° for approximately 20 to 25 minutes.
Low-fat, low calorie and easy.

title: no knead bread
directions: Place first 3 ingredients in a large bowl and let cool to lukewarm.
Beat egg slightly and stir in.
Sprinkle yeast into 1/4 cup warm water and stir until dissolved.
Add to egg mixture.
Sift flour, measure and lightly stir in dry milk.
Add 1/3 of dry ingredients into yeast mixture at one at a time and beat after each addition until smooth.
Cover with moist cloth and let rise to almost double.
Punch down and place in greased 9 x 5 loaf bread pan.
Let rise slightly and bake in a 375° oven for about 45 minutes or until golden.
Take out of pan immediately to cool. Makes 1 loaf.

title: easy minestrone
directions: Saute carrot, celery and cabbage in 1 tablespoon oil.
Add other ingredients.
Add small amount of cooked spaghetti (optional).
Top soup with Parmesan cheese and serve.

title: mystery cookies
directions: Cream oleo, sugar and flavoring.
Add eggs.
Stir in Bisquick and potato flakes.
Cover and chill for 1 hour.
Make in marble size balls.
Cook at 375° for 12 to 14 minutes on an ungreased cookie sheet.

title: scotcheroos
directions: In microwave, bring sugar and syrup just to a boil. Remove and stir in peanut butter. Add Rice Krispies. Spread in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan (lightly buttered).
Melt together the chocolate chips and butterscotch chips.
(If melted in microwave, watch carefully. Takes about 2 to 3 minutes depending on your microwave.)
Spread on top.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Brown chicken breasts in margarine with onions and bell peppers.
Combine all the soups, rice and water in roaster.
Add chicken, margarine, onions and bell pepper.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cook 2 1/2 to 3 hours or until done.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream margarine and oil.
Add sugar and beat until mixture is smooth.
Add egg yolks and beat well.
Combine flour and soda. Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Add vanilla, coconut and pecans.
Fold in egg whites.
Pour batter into 3 (8-inch) pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Frost with Italian Cream Cake Frosting.

title: chicken parmesan wings
directions: Wash wings; pat dry.
Melt butter in flat dish.
Combine all remaining ingredients in food processor; blend and mix well.
Dip chicken wings in butter, then in coating.
Cook for 15 to 20 minutes at 400°.

title: french dressing
directions: Toss salad greens (about 12 cups) with oil just until leaves glisten.
Combine vinegar, salt, garlic, monosodium glutamate and pepper; toss with garlic mixture.
Makes about 1/3 cup.

title: garden hot dog relish or autumn relish
directions: Grind the vegetables in a food processor or a meat grinder. Place in a large sealable container and sprinkle 1/2 cup salt over. Let stand overnight in the refrigerator.
In the morning, drain off all the liquid through a towel or cheesecloth; don't let any excess water remain.
Place back in large container.
Mix the last 6 ingredients together in a large pan, stirring to combine, then heat to boiling.
Pour this hot mixture over the vegetables and stir. Place in pint jars or quart size, if preferred.
Pressure cooker for 10 minutes at 5 pounds of pressure just to seal jars.
This should make approximately 15 pints or 8 quarts.
Store in cabinet until needed.
After opening, place in refrigerator.
We use as a relish over hot dogs, Polish sausage and hamburgers.

title: tomato hot dip
directions: Boil for 3 minutes.
Seal in pint jars.
Better than Ro-Tel.

title: ham and asparagus roulades
directions: Soften cream cheese and blend with horseradish, Tabasco sauce and parsley.
Blanch asparagus spears, then cool.
Spread cream cheese on ham.
Lay asparagus on ham and roll up.
Slice each roll into 4 pieces. Spear with toothpick and serve chilled.
Yields 20 roulades.

title: mandel brodt
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large mixing bowl, beat the eggs, oil, vanilla, almond flavoring and sugar until smooth.
Add flour mixed with baking powder.
Stir in walnuts and chocolates.

title: chocolate no bake cookies
directions: Combine oleo, sugar, cocoa and milk in saucepan on stove, continually stirring until mixture comes to a full, rolling boil. Boil for 1 minute.
Remove from stove.
Add peanut butter, oatmeal and vanilla; stir in well.
Drop from tablespoon on waxed paper.

title: chinese sweet-sour pork
directions: Brown pork in hot fat.
Add water; cover and simmer for 1 hour.
Combine cornstarch, salt, brown sugar, vinegar, pineapple juice and soy sauce; cook, stirring constantly, until slightly thickened.
Pour sauce over hot pork; let stand for 10 minutes. Add green peppers, onion and pineapple chunks; cook 5 minutes. Yields 6 servings.

title: spicy vegetable soup
directions: Heat olive oil in heavy stockpot.
Add onions and garlic and saute for 5 minutes.
Add carrots and saute for 5 minutes more. Add mushrooms, zucchini and potatoes.
Saute for another 5 minutes. Add tomatoes, kidney beans and water or stock and mix.
Add tomato sauce, wine, herbs and spices.
Simmer 30 minutes or until all vegetables are tender.
Remove bay leaves.
Serve with sprinkling of Parmesan cheese.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix oats and Crisco oil; let stand for 10 minutes.
Cook raisins and water until raisins plump, then cool slightly.
Add sugar, eggs, flour, soda, vanilla, cinnamon and salt to oats and oil mixture; mix well.
Then add raisins, chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: lazy mary pie
directions: Pour pie filling into baking dish.
Crumble cake mix over filling.
Put finely crushed nuts over mixture and add melted margarine over top. Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Butter the Bread.
Place 4 slices of Bread Butter side down in a 9 x 13 inch baking dish.
Add grated Cheese.
Add Sausage (browned and crumbled).
Place other 4 slices of Bread Butter side up on top of Sausage.
Beat 5 Eggs and 3 cups of Milk, Salt and Dry Mustard.
Pour over casserole.
Cover and refrigerate overnight. Bake at 350 for 50 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt peanut butter and margarine together.
Stir in confectioners sugar. Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill until firm.
Cut into squares.

title: chicken breast in wine
directions: Dredge chicken in seasoned flour.
Brown in oil and butter. Add wine and cover tightly.
Simmer for 1/2 hour.
Add grapes and toasted slivered almonds.
Cover and simmer for another 1/2 hour.

title: chicken enchilada bake
directions: Grease 2-quart baking dish.
Combine chicken, cheese, beans, olives, salsa, chili powder and garlic powder in large bowl. Blend well.
Spoon into dish; set aside.
To prepare crust, combine baking mix, milk and butter in mixing bowl.
Blend well. Pour over chicken mixture.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until crust is golden brown.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350° and grease a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Thoroughly combine all ingredients but use only 1/2 of tomato sauce.
Turn meat mixture into loaf pan.
Smooth and top with rest of the tomato sauce.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix together.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: garden pea salad
directions: Mix together and store in refrigerator over night.

title: brown sugar pound cake
directions: Beat together Crisco and margarine.
Gradually add brown sugar, beating together until creamy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Sift flour and sift again with addition of baking powder and salt.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
Add maple flavoring.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Put in a cold oven.
Turn temperature to 300° and bake for 1 hour or until done.

title: taffy
directions: Mix all together; boil.
Bring to 275° on candy thermometer. Put on buttered dishes (saucers); cool slightly, still warm to the touch.
Lightly butter hands, pull and enjoy.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Combine cheese, soup, pepper, pimento and onion.
Stir in spaghetti; blend well.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: wassail
directions: Mix all ingredients.
(If desired, cloves and cinnamon sticks can be put in a tea ball and placed inside the pot.)
Simmer all ingredients in very large pot for 10 minutes.
Makes 1 1/2 gallons.
Serves 16.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Melt margarine in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish. Add stuffing and spread over the bottom of dish.
Combine soups and water and pour over stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: pineapple bars
directions: Mix sugar and butter.
Add eggs and mix.
Add flour, salt and soda and mix.
Mix in pineapple and nuts.
Pour into greased 9-inch square pan and bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Remove and cool.
Cut into squares.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together well and pour into greased pan; bake.

title: rolled wheat brownies
directions: Pour boiling water over rolled wheat in mixer bowl.
Let stand 2 minutes.
Add butter, eggs and vanilla. Mix 2 minutes at low speed.
Thoroughly blend dry ingredients.
Add to rolled wheat mixture.
Mix 2 minutes. Pour into 3 buttered pans (12 x 20 x 2 1/2-inches).
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chow chow relish
directions: Place in stone jar. Mix together. Sprinkle sparingly with salt. Let stand 24 hours. Drain off brine. Place mixture in cooking pot. Sprinkle with turmeric, red peppers, mustard seed, celery seed, allspice, cloves, sugar and ground mixed mustard. Pour enough vinegar to cover vegetables. Cover tightly. Cover over medium heat, stirring often. When vegetables are tender, remove and pack in sterile jars.

title: golden almond bars
directions: Mix until crumbly; set aside 1/2 cup for topping.
Press remainder of mix into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: broccoli quiche
directions: Toss cheese with flour.
Add all other ingredients.
Pour into a pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: rich dinner rolls
directions: Scald milk; stir in sugar, salt and margarine.
Cool to lukewarm.
Measure warm water in large warm bowl.
Sprinkle in yeast; stir until dissolved.
Add lukewarm milk mixture; add eggs and 2 cups flour.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in enough flour to make a soft dough.
Turn on floured board and knead until smooth. Put in greased bowl and turn to grease top.
Cover and let rise in warm place until double.
Punch down and turn on lightly floured board.
Make into rolls and let rise in bread pan again.
Bake at 375° for about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: baked fish with potatoes(pesce con patate el forno)
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Place fish in large baking dish and place potatoes (cut into
1/4-inch
thick
slices)
and onions around and on top of
fish.
Place
chopped tomatoes and juice all
over fish,
potatoes
and
onions.
Sprinkle
fish
with garlic, parsley, Parmesan cheese, salt and pepper.
Pour olive oil on fish and bake at 375° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cover pan with tin foil,
removing
last 30 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Mix all ingredients, except nutmeg, and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.

title: cabbage au gratin
directions: Place cabbage in saucepan.
Add 1/2 teaspoon of salt, sugar and water.
Cover and cook for 8 to 10 minutes.
Melt margarine in saucepan.
Add flour.
Mix until smooth.
Add remaining 1/2 teaspoon of salt and milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring until thick.
Add cheese.
Place half the cabbage in a casserole dish. Pour half of cheese over cabbage.
Repeat layer.
Cover with bread crumbs or corn flakes.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Put 6 slices of bread on bottom
of
extra large casserole dish.
Brown sausage and drain.
Spread 1/2 of sausage on bread. Spread 1/2 of cheese over sausage.	Layer again.
Beat eggs.
Add milk and salt.
Pour
over	mix.
Cook,
uncovered, for 1 hour at 350°.
Can be prepared
the night before, put in refrigerator and cooked the next day.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: weight watcher's meal in a skillet
directions: Mix all ingredients in pan.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Makes 2 servings.

title: graham cracker cookies
directions: Cover cookie sheet or jelly roll pan with waxed paper and spray with Pam.
Lay graham crackers on foil.
Combine butter or margarine and brown sugar in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Cook while stirring until sugar is dissolved and mixture is blended. Remove pan from heat; stir in nuts.
Pour hot mixture over graham crackers.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: sketti squares
directions: *Three ounce package thinly sliced pepperoni or ham slices or Canadian bacon.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except 1/2 of fried onions. Put in 1 1/2-quart casserole. Bake 30 minutes at 350°. Put on remaining onions and bake for 5 minutes more or until brown.

title: baked fudge pie
directions: Add oleo and chocolate to sugar.
Stir in eggs.
Add flour, vanilla and nuts, stirring after each addition.
Pour mixture into greased 8-inch pie pan.

title: apple streusel cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Spread apple filling in a 9-inch square baking dish, well buttered.
In a medium bowl beat eggs; add sweetened condensed milk, melted margarine, cinnamon and nutmeg. Mix well and spread over apple filling.

title: creamy chicken fettuccine
directions: Cook chicken in skillet in oil over medium heat until done, 2 to 3 minutes each side.
Cut into 1/2-inch cubes; set aside.
In same skillet, combine mushrooms and garlic.
Cook over medium heat for about 1 minute.
Sprinkle with flour and stir quickly to combine.
Add chicken broth and milk.
Reduce heat and simmer 2 to 3 minutes.
Stir in cheeses and pepper.
Return chicken to skillet.
Stir frequently until chicken is well heated.
Serve over cooked fettuccine noodles.

title: delicious potatoes
directions: Mix all together and place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with 1 cup crushed corn flakes or potato chips, if desired. Bake at 375° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: "surprise" sugar cookies
directions: Mix up in a big bowl.
Make them into cookies.
Mash them in the pan.
Put stuff on top of them.
Put them in the oven.
Eat them.
I like them.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Blend together.
Refrigerate 24 hours before serving.

title: frozen strawberry dessert
directions: Cream the sugar and cream cheese together.
Mix strawberries, bananas and pineapple.
Fold in the Cool Whip (thaw before using). May be frozen up to 9 months.
Can be put into a mold.

title: ultimate meat loaf
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except bacon.
Place in large casserole dish.
Take additional catsup and spread thickly on top of meat loaf.
Arrange bacon slices on top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: sesame sauce
directions: Melt butter in a saucepan.
Add onion, garlic and salt.
Cook slowly for 5 minutes.
Whisk in flour 5 minutes.
Add tahini. Continue to cook over lowest heat, whisking frequently.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 10 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook sugar, water and cornstarch until clear.
When it boils, stir Jell-O in mixture, then let it cool.
Mix in strawberries. Put in pie pan.

title: nanny's pink salad
directions: Mix cream cheese with mayo.
Mix all other ingredients.
Last, add the whipped cream.
Freeze in square Pyrex 8 x 8-inch or 9 x 9-inch dish.
Serve on lettuce leaf after the salad is frozen. Cut it into squares.
Really good with chicken or turkey.
This may be served before freezing.
Reminds me of pistachio salad.
We like it best frozen.

title: ortega bread
directions: Pour into greased pan.
Bake for 40 minutes at 325° or until browned on top.
Absolutely delicious as a snack or for serving as an hors d'oeuvre.

title: orzo with mushrooms and snow peas
directions: Heat olive oil in a saute pan. Add shallots and saute. Add mushrooms and saute until brown. Add snow peas and cook for 1 minute. Add mixture to the orzo. Butter may be added to taste. Season with salt and pepper.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Constantly stir in "double boiler" the egg yolks to consistency of honey. Remove from heat. Add clarified butter slowly as not to cook the egg yolks. Use wire whip to constantly stir yolks to keep from sticking. Add remaining ingredients. Used over asparagus or broccoli. Add herbs and/or spices to give it a different touch.

title: "custard pie"
directions: Beat eggs. Add 1/4 cup of cold milk (heat rest of milk). Add to beaten eggs, sugar, flavoring, nutmeg, vanilla

and salt. Mix slowly. Add hot milk. Pour into unbaked crust. Bake 10 minutes in 450° oven, then moderate oven at 325° about 25 minutes or until knife comes out clean, mixture doesn't stick to knife. "Serve hot or cold."

title: egg casserole
directions: Brown and drain sausage.
Mix eggs, milk, mustard and salt. Stir in bread, sausage and cheese.
Put in greased casserole dish and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: apple cake - dairy free
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Peel, core and chop the apples into small pieces.
Mix together with 3 tablespoons sugar and the cinnamon.
Set aside.

title: okra-tomato casserole
directions: Place layers of okra, tomatoes, onion, green pepper, salt and pepper in nonstick 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Repeat layers.
Top with dry butter substitute.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: easy chicken gravy
directions: Cook cornstarch and broth over medium heat stirring until bubbly and thick.
Add cream and heat.
Makes approximately 1 quart.

title: date balls
directions: Combine butter, sugar, dates and coconut in one pot and boil for 3 minutes.
Add pecans and Rice Krispies.
Remove from heat and then add the pecans and Rice Krispies.	Let cool slightly, enough to handle.
Roll into small balls then coat with powdered sugar.

title: grandma's stew and noodles
directions: Mix flour, salt and pepper.
Roll stew meat in flour mixture. Brown in skillet with vegetable oil that covers the bottom of the pan.
Pour off excess oil.
Add tomatoes or tomato sauce, water, vinegar, onion, bay leaf and carrots.
Cover and simmer until carrots are done.
Serve over cooked noodles (or rice).

title: creamy baked corn(a light corn pudding)
directions: Melt margarine in a heavy saucepan over low heat.
Add flour, stirring until smooth.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly. Gradually add milk; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture is thickened and bubbly.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook chicken in pot covered with water.
Remove chicken to cool and save water.
Cook spaghetti according to package directions in reserved chicken broth.
Drain.
Saute celery in butter in large skillet.
Add chicken that has been removed from the bone and cubed, cooked spaghetti and rest of ingredients, except Parmesan cheese.
Mix carefully.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: hot and spicy sausage vegetable soup
directions: Soak the first 3 ingredients for 30 minutes.
Drain; save liquid.
Brown sausage with the onion; drain fat.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Add wine broth and water to desired consistency.
Simmer for 2 hours.

title: banana split dessert
directions: In mixing bowl, toss together crumbs and melted butter.
Press mixture onto bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
In a bowl, beat remaining 1/2 cup butter for 30 seconds.
Add powdered sugar and beat until fluffy. Beat in eggs.
Spread egg mixture over the crumbs. Slice bananas lengthwise in halves and arrange over top. Spoon pineapple over bananas.
Spread Cool Whip over bananas. Sprinkle with chocolate and nuts.
Cover and refrigerate 4 hours. Cut into squares.
Top with a cherry.

title: quick rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast.
Add remaining ingredients.
Knead a little. Let rise until double.
Make into rolls.
Let rise again.
Bake at 400°.
Yields 1 dozen.

title: sweet dill pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers and cut in strips; put in jar (with head of dill for each jar).
Heat remaining ingredients to boiling and pour over cucumbers.
Seal.

title: pineapple-bran muffins
directions: Mix and bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes. Makes 12 to 14.

title: holiday trash
directions: Mix ingredients.
Melt candy and pour until coated.
Spread on wax paper.
Let harden.
Break in pieces and store.
Serve in new small trash can.

title: oriental chicken
directions: Layer chicken in a dish.
Mix other ingredients and pour over chicken.
Cover and bake for 2 hours at 300°.
Good served with rice.

title: cornbread-railroad pie
directions: Saute onion and green pepper.
Brown beef in skillet.
Add soup, water, corn and seasoning.
Mix well and simmer for 15 minutes.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch glass casserole or pan 3/4 full, leaving room for Cornbread Topping.

title: jello dessert
directions: Mix all together and chill. Top with fresh or canned fruit.

title: frankfurter casserole
directions: Cut frankfurters in half lengthwise, then crosswise.
Melt butter in skillet.
Add onions; cook slowly until soft.
Add beans.
Stir in soup and milk; mix well.
Cook over low heat until it simmers.
Fold in frankfurters.
Heat until bubbling, then put in casserole dish.
Put biscuits on top.
Bake at 375° until shredded cheese on top melts.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Let butter soften.
Grate cheese and mix together.
Work in flour, a little at a time.
Make small balls and press with fork. Add nut to each top, if desired.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes. Makes 75.

title: seasoned nuts
directions: Saute nuts in butter for 2 minutes.
Stir in soy sauce. Remove from pan.
Stir in salad dressing mix.
Place nuts in single layer to cool.

title: cream of wheat cornbread
directions: Mix well the first 5 ingredients and pour in the remaining ingredients.
Stir gently.
Do not overbeat.
Pour into greased skillet or muffin tin. Bake at 425° until the top is golden brown, crisp and crumbly.

title: classic german chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a small saucepan, over low heat, melt chocolate in water.
Stir.
In a large bowl, beat sugar and Crisco until fluffy.
Beat in egg yolks and vanilla.
Stir in chocolate mixture.

title: chocolate chip bars
directions: Mix together shortening, brown sugar and eggs.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir in chocolate chips and broken nuts.
Spread into pan greased.
Bake 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix all ingredients at medium speed. Pour into 3 (9-inch) greased and floured pans. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Chop cabbage coarsely.
Put in large pan or crock-pot.
Mix together hamburger, onion, egg, rice and Worcestershire.
Form into patties or meatballs; place on top of cabbage.
Mix soup, water and sugar together; pour over top of all.
Cook, covered, until meat is done.
To thicken, cook, uncovered, for 10 minutes or more.

title: sausage noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles until tender; drain.
Brown sausage and onions. Spoon off all but 1 1/2 tablespoons fat.
Add noodles, soup, milk, water and cheese.
Stir well.
Pour into greased baking dish. Sprinkle top with crackers and butter mixed together.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cream delight
directions: Combine butter with flour and 1 cup chopped pecans.
Press in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake for 20 minutes at 325°.
Let cool completely.
Combine cream cheese, 1 cup Cool Whip and confectioners sugar.
Spread on crust.
Combine milk with pudding. Spread on cream cheese mixture.
Top with 1 cup Cool Whip, 1/2 cup chopped pecans and chocolate syrup.
Refrigerate.

title: beef dumplings
directions: Cook beef stew in a large pot. When done, add butter and milk. Bring to a boil. Separate layers. Drop into mix. Dumplings are done when they begin to roll. You can also use your own dough from scratch.

title: hot holiday punch
directions: Combine the cranberry juice, pineapple juice, orange slices, cinnamon sticks and cloves in a large sauce pan. Bring to a boil. Strain into a heatproof punch bowl.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Drain and chop fruits.
Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add lemonade and stir until melted.
Chill until slightly thickened. Blend in Cool Whip and fold in fruit.
Pour into serving dishes and freeze about 4 hours.

title: sukiyaki
directions: In skillet, brown beef in oil.
Add vegetables, soup and soy sauce.
Cover and cook over low heat 20 minutes until meat is tender.
Stir now and then; blend cornstarch and water; stir into mixture.
Cook, stirring until thickened.
Serve with cooked rice.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Cook asparagus just 5 minutes, then place in casserole dish. Blend butter and flour.
Add milk gradually and cook slowly until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add cheese and salt.
Pour sauce over asparagus; sprinkle with crumbs.
Dot with butter and bake in slow oven at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: beef barley soup
directions: Brown meat well and scrape up brown bits while adding water, then add rest of ingredients.
Adjust seasonings.
Cooks in 1 hour.
Even better the second day.

title: pork sum gum
directions: In saucepan, combine celery, mushrooms, bouillon, onion, peppers, sherry extract, soy sauce, salt, pepper, ginger and nutmeg.
Cover and cook over low heat for 10 minutes or until onions and celery are tender but still crisp.
Add pork and pimentos.
Mix well.
Cook 3 minutes longer or until hot.
Serve over rice.
Serves 4.

title: pink party punch
directions: Mix together; serve when well chilled.

title: no-bake fruit cake
directions: Butter a large loaf pan. Line with waxed paper and butter paper well. Mix all ingredients together well. Pack into prepared pan. Refrigerate overnight before cutting. Serve plain or with whipped cream.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix the mayo and sour cream. Add the dill weed, onion flakes, seasoned salt, garlic salt and Accent. Add the Worcestershire sauce, hot sauce and parsley flakes.

title: mock apricot jam
directions: Boil zucchini for 6 minutes.
Drain.
Add pineapple, lemon juice and sugar.
Stir well.
Boil 10 minutes.
Add dry jello. Pour into containers.
Cover and refrigerate or freeze or cover with paraffin and lid.

title: beef casserole 2
directions: Saute beef until it loses its red color. Add onion and cook until tender.
Stir in corn, soup, sour cream, pimento, salt, pepper and noodles.
Spoon mixture into a lightly greased 2-quart casserole. Sprinkle with crumbs and cheese. Dot with margarine. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: special meringue
directions: Beat egg whites with cream of tartar until frothy.
Beat sugar in gradually.
Continue beating until meringue is stiff and glossy.

title: green enchiladas
directions: In skillet, cook tortillas, one at a time, in hot oil for 15 seconds on each side.
(Do not overcook or they won't roll.) Place 2 tablespoons shredded cheese and 1 tablespoon chopped onion on each tortilla; roll up.
Place, seam side down, in 11 x 7 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.

title: instant hot chocolate
directions: Mix well and use 3 tablespoons per cup of hot water.

title: german liver dumplings
directions: Grind liver, onion and suet together, then add an egg.
Roll crackers to make a large cupful.
Add 1/2 teaspoon salt and a little pepper.
Add to liver and mix well.
Boil a soup bone to which onion, celery and 1 teaspoon salt have been added.
When vegetables are tender, make small balls of liver mixture and drop into the soup.
Cook 20 minutes.
Serve hot with crackers.

title: hot pineapple casserole
directions: Mix pineapple, flour and sugar.
Stir in cheese.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Cover with cracker crumbs.
