Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: three bean salad
directions: Mix all in a large bowl and set aside.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli and cauliflower into small pieces, using primarily the flowerets. Add onion, water chestnuts, Parmesan cheese, bacon pieces, basil and croutons.
Mix Miracle Whip and sugar.
Pour over salad and mix.
Refrigerate.

title: strawberry tidbits
directions: Mix milk, jello, coconut, pecans and vanilla.
Chill for 1 hour.
Form in shape of strawberry.
Roll in sugar.
Make strawberry leaves out of almonds.

title: mexican bites
directions: In skillet, cook the sausage over medium high heat, stirring until browned and fat is rendered. Add onions, garlic, chili powder and spices and cook, stirring until onions are soft. Remove from heat and cool.

title: cranberry apple punch
directions: Heat water and sugar to boiling, stirring constantly, until sugar is dissolved.
Cool.
Refrigerate all ingredients.
Just before serving, mix in large punch bowl.
Makes 60 (1/2-cup) servings.

title: busy day casserole
directions: In large casserole dish, layer the pork chops (salted and peppered), then the onions and then potatoes.
Pour mushroom soup over potatoes, covering well.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until potatoes are tender.

title: easy potato-sausage casserole
directions: In skillet, crumble and brown sausage and onion.
In a mixing bowl, blend together milk, mushroom soup and pepper.
In 9 x 9-inch casserole dish, layer 1/2 of potatoes, 1/2 of soup mixture, 1/2 of grated cheese and 1/2 of sausage.
Repeat.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Uncover; sprinkle a little more cheese over top.
Return to oven until cheese is melted.

title: rhubarb crisp
directions: Place rhubarb in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix sugar, cornstarch and water.
Boil until clear.
Add vanilla.
Let set.

title: mandarin fruit mix
directions: Drain oranges and pineapple.
Mix these and other ingredients. Cool in refrigerator and serve.

title: onion shortcake
directions: Mix muffin mix, egg, milk and hot sauce; spread in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: oyster roll
directions: Cream enough mayonnaise into the cream cheese to hold it together.
Add Worcestershire sauce, garlic and onion and mix well.
Spread to 1/2-inch thickness on waxed paper.
Chop oysters and spread them on top of cream cheese mixture.
Roll as for jelly roll using a knife to start it.
Chill for 24 hours.
Serve with toast rounds or crackers.

title: green congealed salad
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Chill in salad pan.

title: family favorite casserole
directions: Place hamburg in a large casserole, add layers of sliced onions and sliced potatoes.
Cover with tomatoes, add seasonings. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: banana boat salad
directions: In an 11-inch plate arrange a "sea" of lettuce leaves on a lower portion of plate.
Place a banana half on surface of "sea" creating the hull of a sailboat.
Use remaining full length piece of banana to create the "mast."
Using 2 shorter pieces outline the "sail".
Fill in with fruit cocktail.

title: easy oven baked chicken
directions: Wash chicken. Then salt and pepper chicken. Batter heavy with flour. Place in roasting pan with onion. Cover with water. Cover with lid and bake about 45 minutes in a 450° oven.

title: pink salad
directions: Empty cottage cheese and Cool Whip into large salad bowl. Fold together.
Chop cherries and orange slices into small pieces. Fold into the cheese and Cool Whip mixture.
Fold the crushed pineapple into the mixture and sprinkle with just enough of the cherry Jell-O to make it a pink color when mixed well.

title: sausage filled crepes
directions: Combine eggs, milk and oil.
Add flour and 1/2 tsp. salt. Beat until smooth.
Pour 2 Tbsp. batter into greased 6 inch skillet.
Tilt.
Cook on 1 side and turn.
Invert on toweling. Repeat to make 16 crepes.
Cook sausage and onion together; drain. Add cheeses and marjoram.
Mix well.
Place 2 Tbsp. sausage filling down center of each crepe; roll up.
Place in 11 x 7 inch baking dish.
Cover and chill.
Bake covered in 375 degree oven for 40 minutes.
Mix sour cream and butter and spoon over top. Bake uncovered for 5 minutes.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Combine powdered sugar, cream cheese and yogurt.
Spread dough out on cookie sheet and bake.
After cool, top with cream cheese mixture.
Top with favorite fruit.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Melt
chocolate in boiling water.
Cool.
Cream
butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks, 1 at a
time,
beating
well
after each one.
Add melted chocolate and
vanilla.
Mix well.
Sift dry ingredients together and add
alternately
with buttermilk to chocolate mixture.
After beating until smooth, fold in egg whites.
Bake in 3 (8 or 9-inch) greased
Teflon
cake pans at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool
and frost with Coconut-Pecan Icing.
Yields 1 (3 layer) cake.

title: apricot nectar salad
directions: Heat 1 can apricot nectar.
Pour into bowl with orange jello. Stir until dissolved.
Place other can apricot nectar in blender. Add cream cheese, one package at a time, blending well.
Add this to jello and stir well.
Add crushed pineapple and chopped pecans. Pour into 3-quart mold.

title: george's cake
directions: Blend flour, brown sugar; add cooking oil, eggs, flavoring; mix in 2 cups of nuts and butterscotch morsels. Mix well and pour in greased and floured oblong pan.
Bake in 250 degree oven about 1 hour or until done.

title: caterina's minestrone soup
directions: Combine and cook first 10 ingredients 25 minutes.
Add beans and peas with their juice and potatoes.
Cook 20 minutes more. Add cabbage and 3 tablespoons olive oil and cook until cabbage is tender.
In separate pan, cook 1 cup macaroni; drain.
Add to soup.
Serve with Romano cheese.

title: cornbread salad
directions: After cornbread has been cooked and cooled, crumble until very fine.
Add your onion, bell pepper, tomatoes and celery.
Add 2 dashes of Tabasco sauce for a little flavor or 4 to 5 for a hot flavor.
Add Hellmann's mayonnaise and stir until well mixed. Refrigerate overnight for best taste.

title: pork chop special
directions: Arrange pork chops in long casserole dish.
Mix together other ingredients and pour over chops.
Cover and bake at 300° for 1 hour or until chops are tender.

title: tomato casserole
directions: Mix puree, sugar and salt.
Add 1 1/2 cups boiling water. Boil for a few minutes.
Pour melted butter over bread.
Then pour puree mixture over bread.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° or 375° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate boil cookies
directions: Mix together and boil for 2 minutes in saucepan.
Remove from heat.
Add 3 cups oatmeal and 1/2 cup peanut butter.
Drop by teaspoons on wax paper.
(Grease wax paper with margarine.)

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan that has been sprayed with cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour or until real brown on top.
Sooo good!!

title: bacon things
directions: Cut bacon strips into three pieces.
Coat with egg mixture. Dip generously in Parmesan cheese.
Place on cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Check at 15 minutes (maybe turn).

title: bird candy(really)
directions: Use equal parts of ground suet, corn meal and sugar.
Add 1/2 part water and cook 20 minutes.
Add several tablespoons peanut butter.
Pour into greased pan.
Cool.
Cut into squares and put in mesh bags (like orange bags).
Hang in tree.
Birds prefer this over most other foods.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease loaf pans.
Mix first 6 ingredients, then add the rest and beat well.
Pour in pans and bake about 1 hour.

title: orange jelly
directions: Add lemon juice to water.
Pour over oranges.
Let stand overnight.
Boil until soft; press through jelly bag and strain. To each 2 cups of juice, add 1 3/4 cups sugar.
Boil rapidly to jelly stage.
Pour into sterilized jelly glasses.

title: black bottom pie
directions: Scald milk; slowly add egg yolks.
Combine sugar and cornstarch; add to milk and egg mixture.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture coats spoon, about 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
To 1 cup of this custard, add 1 1/2 squares grated chocolate and the vanilla, mixing well.
When cool, pour into the baked pie shell and chill.
Soften gelatin in cold water and dissolve in remaining custard.
Cool.
Beat egg whites and cream of tartar until stiff and gradually add sugar.
Fold into custard. Add rum extract.
As soon as chocolate has set, pour in the custard mixture.
Chill until firm.
Whip the cream and spread on pie.
Top with grated chocolate.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cheese log roll
directions: Mix thoroughly; roll in 2 logs and roll each in chopped pecans.
Chill 6 hours.
Serve on Ritz crackers.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll in ball or log.
Roll in Bac*Os or nuts.

title: creme de menthe brownies
directions: Mix all together.
Bake for 30 minutes in a 13 x 9-inch pan at 350°.

title: turtle cake
directions: In double boiler, melt caramels and butter. Add sweetened milk to mixture. Prepare cake mix according to package directions. Pour 1/2 of batter in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°. Pour caramel mixture over cake.
Then sprinkle chocolate chips and chopped walnuts over mixture.
Pour the other half of batter over all. Bake for another 20 to 30 minutes or until done.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: In a large bowl add flour, sugar, soda, and cinnamon; add eggs and oil.
Stir to mix; do not beat.
Stir in vanilla, pineapple, pecans and bananas.
Spoon into 3 greased and floured 9-inch tins. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Melt margarine; add chopped onion and chopped mushroom stems. Saute.
Add spices and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix well.
Stir bread crumbs.
Add bouillon or water, if needed.
Stuff mushrooms with mixture.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until brown.

title: grandma's crustless coconut pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Beat eggs. Add sugar and flour. Beat until thoroughly mixed. To this mixture, add milk, margarine, flavoring, and vanilla. Mix well and pour into two 9 -inch pie plates. Spray plates with a little Pam. Bake about 35-40 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: potato dumplings
directions: Peel potatoes and boil in salted water until soft. Drain and mash smoothly. Blend in egg yolks, corn starch, bread crumbs, salt and pepper. Mix thoroughly and shape into dumplings. You may need to add flour to make dumplings hold together. Roll each dumpling in flour and drop into rapidly boiling water. Cover and cook for about 15 or 20 minutes.

title: velvet cookies
directions: Cream the shortening, peanut butter and sugar together.
Add eggs and extracts.
Mix in dry ingredients.
Drop by teaspoons onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° until brown.
This mixture freezes well so that you can use as needed.

title: plum cake
directions: Melt butter; remove from heat and add the juice and rind of the lemon and sugar.
Blend well.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Chill 24 hours before serving.

title: caramel cake
directions: Go by recipe on cake mix box.
Cook at 375° until light brown.
Let cool.

title: hamburger barbecue
directions: Cook meat in skillet. Drain. Make sauce of remaining ingredients. Cook onions and celery first with meat.

title: corn dip
directions: Mix well and serve with dip-size Fritos.

title: chocolate oatmeal candy
directions: In broiler pan, mix sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring to dissolve sugar.
Let boil 4 minutes.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and 2 cups oatmeal or 1 1/2 cups oatmeal and coconut or pecans.
Spoon onto wax paper and let cool.
Easy!

title: pumpkin sheet cake
directions: Mix flour, cinnamon, soda and salt.
Mix egg, sugar and oil; add to first mixture.
Add pumpkin; beat well.
Pour into greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken gumbo
directions: Boil chicken.
In a skillet, saute in butter until tender the onion, okra and tomatoes.
Debone chicken.
Add chicken and skillet ingredients back to broth.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Boil 30 minutes until ready to serve.
Serve over rice.

title: butter horns
directions: Combine milk, shortening, sugar and salt.
Cool to lukewarm. Add yeast and eggs, then flour.
Mix to smooth soft dough.
Knead lightly on floured surface.
Place dough in a greased bowl; cover and let rise until at least double in bulk.
Divide dough in thirds; roll each 1/3 on lightly floured surface to 9-inch circle. Brush with melted butter.
Cut each circle into 12 to 16 wedges. Roll each wedge starting with wide end and roll to point.
Arrange in baking pan and brush with salad oil.
Cover.
Let rise until very light.
Bake in 400° to 425° oven for 15 minutes.
Cool. When slightly warm, frost with confectioners sugar frosting.

title: chicken etti
directions: Break spaghetti
in
2 inch pieces and cook until done. Add all
other	ingredients and mix well.
Place in casserole, keeping 1 cup
cheese
for	on
top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Makes 2 casseroles.

title: shish kabobs
directions: Pour all ingredients in bowl and marinate meat overnight. Make kabobs using meat, onions, green peppers, tomatoes, potatoes and pineapple chunks.
Grill and turn often.

title: sausage bean chowder
directions: In a skillet, cook pork sausage until brown; pour off fat. In a large kettle, combine kidney beans, tomatoes, water, onion, bay leaf, seasoned salt, garlic powder, thyme and pepper.
Add sausage.
Simmer, covered, 1 hour.
Add potatoes and green pepper. Cook, covered, 15 to 20 minutes until potatoes are tender. Remove bay leaf.
Yields 8 generous portions.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Spoon into pan.
Bake at 350° for 7 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet.
Makes about 2 dozen cookies.

title: spinach rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill for at least 1/2 hour.
Make into small balls.
Put on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350 degrees for 10-15 minutes.

title: beef noodle casserole
directions: Brown beef in skillet.
Add onions and cook until tender, but not brown.
Add corn and soups, sour cream, pimento, salt and pepper.
Stir in noodles.
Spoon mixture into a 4 quart casserole dish.
(At this stage, casserole may be frozen and cooked later.) If desired, mix bread crumbs with butter and sprinkle over top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: quick crescent taco pie
directions: Press dough into 10-inch pie plate.
Seal perforations. Sprinkle with 1 cup corn chips.
Brown ground beef in skillet. Drain.
Add seasoning mix, water and salsa.
Simmer for 5 minutes. Spoon over corn chips.
Spread with sour cream.
Cover with cheese slices.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup corn chips.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 6 servings.

title: icebox cheese cake
directions: Mix crumbs, margarine and powdered sugar together, saving 2 teaspoons for topping.
Line 9 x 13-inch pan with this mixture. Cream sugar, vanilla and cream cheese together until well blended and creamy, then set aside.
Mix jello and water together, set aside.
Chill milk in freezer for at least 4 hours or until very cold, then put into large bowl and whip until peaks form.
Blend in jello about 1/2 minute or so.
Add cheese mix and mix just enough to blend.
Do not overmix.
Pour into pan and top with a few crumbs.
Chill overnight.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Grease a shallow 2-quart baking dish. Place chicken and veggies in dish. Stir together soup, chicken broth and pepper; pour mix over chicken. Combine flour, milk and butter; stir until smooth. Pour over mixture in baking dish. Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until lightly browned. Let cool 10 minutes. I like this served over cooked rice. Yield: 4 to 6 servings.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Prepare apples.
Cover and set aside.
Measure oil and pour into large mixing bowl.
Add sugar and eggs; mix well.
Sift together dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture in small amounts, beating after each addition.
When batter becomes stiff, finish mixing by hand.
Fold in nuts and apples.
Spread evenly in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan or Bundt pan, if preferred. Bake about 1 hour at 350°.
Remove from oven and set aside.

title: cool whip salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip and cream cheese together.
Stir in 1 small package dry jello.
Add pecans and marshmallows.
Chill before serving.

title: chicken ritz
directions: Cook chicken and cut into bite size pieces.
Put in casserole dish (9 x 13-inch baking dish).
Mix soup and sour cream and pour over chicken.
Crumble Ritz crackers and mix with poppy seed. Sprinkle over soup mixture.
Melt butter and pour over crackers. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Bake, covered. Uncover and cook another 5 to 10 minutes.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Place chicken pieces in baking dish.
Mix dressing, preserves, soup mix and water.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° covered with aluminum foil for 1 hour.
Add pineapple and pepper chunks.
Bake an additional half hour.

title: north coast mussels(serves 4)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, toss the hot spaghetti with the olive oil.
In a small bowl, combine the eggs and the 1/2 cup of Parmesan cheese.
Stir into the spaghetti.

title: zucchini-mozzarella casserole(an italian-flavored delight)
directions: Melt margarine in a large, nonstick skillet over medium heat. Add zucchini and onion; cook 10 minutes, stirring frequently, until vegetables are tender-crisp.
Remove from heat.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Stir the parsley, garlic powder, oregano, basil, salt and pepper into zucchini.

title: party salad
directions: Drain fruit cocktail and pineapple, saving 6 tablespoons pineapple juice and mix with cream cheese.
Add Cool Whip and mix thoroughly.
Fold in all fruit and marshmallows.
Chill.
Food coloring can be added if desired.

title: crackling corn bread
directions: Heat oil in iron skillet until hot.
Mix all remaining ingredients together; pour into hot skillet.
With spoon, dip oil from sides of skillet to center of corn bread, making little puddles all over top.
Bake at 375° to 400° until golden brown and crusty.

title: hawaiian cake
directions: Cream the margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add crumbs and milk; beat until smooth.
Add vanilla and beat again. Fold in coconut, pineapple and nuts.
Pour into oiled tube pan. Bake at 300° for 2 hours.

title: black bean and corn salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl, mix well.
Cover and chill several hours or overnight.
Serves 8.

title: olive cheese balls
directions: Cream the cream cheese and butter together.
Blend in flour and cayenne.
Drain olives and dry on paper towels.
Wrap each olive with 1 teaspoon of the dough.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake 15 minutes in a 400° oven.
Very tasty warm or cold; best warm.

title: homemade brownies
directions: Mix together the butter, sugar and cocoa.
Add eggs, flour and salt.
Beat until smooth. Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: green pea salad
directions: Layer ingredients in your serving dish as follows,
lettuce, peas, onion.
Mixed well mayonnaise and sugar; and spread over top.
Then, cover with grated cheese; and chill for one hour before serving.

title: mom's hobo supper
directions: Add 1/2 cup of each dry ingredient to a hamburger patty.
Wrap in individual foil packets and bake or grill at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: breakfast bread
directions: Beat eggs; add rest of the ingredients.
Bake in greased loaf pan at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or in greased muffin tin.
Makes 20 to 24 muffins.
Can be frozen.
You can add onions, green peppers or mushrooms if you like.

title: muffin biscuits
directions: Add enough milk to batter to make it like cake batter.
Pour into greased muffin rings.
Bake at 400° until done and brown.

title: peanut butter cornflake cookies
directions: Heat syrup and sugar until melted.
Add peanut butter.
Pour over cornflakes.
Mix well.
Drop by spoonful on wax paper or press onto cookie sheets and cut into bars.

title: hot fudge sundae cake
directions: Mix in 8 x 8-inch pan.
Add topping.

title: crinkles
directions: Cream shortening with sugar.
Beat in egg and molasses.
Add dry ingredients.
Make small balls and press onto a cookie sheet with a glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: chicken bake
directions: Cook frozen potatoes 5 minutes in boiling water; drain. Combine soup and milk; add mushrooms, chicken and drained potatoes.
Stir; spoon into a 2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle corn flakes over top.
Drizzle melted butter over corn flakes.
Bake 45 minutes or until hot and bubbly in center.

title: party mints
directions: Mix cream cheese, peppermint and sugar until smooth.
Add food coloring to achieve desired color.
Roll into small balls. Place on waxed paper and flatten with fork. Can also be used in mint molds. Great for weddings and showers.

title: fried rice
directions: Put rice and oil in heavy skillet and lightly brown, stirring constantly.
Saute chopped vegetables and add to rice.
Add meat, 3/4 cup water and add a little soy sauce.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Remove from heat and let it stand for a few minutes before serving.

title: dr. bird cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients and sift; mix well.
Do not beat.
In a large bowl, mix dry ingredients.
Add bananas and pineapple and the rest of the ingredients; use pecans, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix flour, margarine and pecans.
Press into sheet cake pan. Cook at 375° for 15 minutes; cool completely.

title: french fried eggplant
directions: Peel and slice eggplant and soak in water with small amount of sugar for 2 to 3 hours.
Drain off water.

title: scrumptious pie
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk and lemon juice.
Add Cool Whip, pineapple and nuts.
Mix well.
Pour into pie shells and refrigerate overnight.

title: frances' sour cream coconut cake
directions: Day 1:
Mix sour cream, sugar and Tropic Isle fresh frozen coconut together well. Refrigerate overnight.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom only of 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Mix all ingredients and beat 30 seconds.
Pour into pan. Bake until wooden toothpick inserted in center comes out clean, 55 to 65 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Loosen sides of loaf pan; remove from pan.
Cool completely before slicing.
To store, wrap and refrigerate no longer than 1 week.

title: no peek chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Blend soups and milk together.
Add rice and mix.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased cake pan.
Lay pieces of raw chicken over rice mixture.
Sprinkle soup mix over the chicken.
Cover pan tightly with foil and bake 2 hours.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Bring cocoa, sugar, milk and oleo to boil 1 minute.
(Will form soft ball when dropped in water.)
Then take from stove and add oatmeal and vanilla.
Drop by tablespoon onto cookie sheet.

title: no-bake cheesecake squares
directions: In saucepan melt margarine; stir in crumbs and sugar.
Press firmly on bottom of 8 or 9-inch square pan.
Chill.
In large mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Mix in sweetened condensed milk. Stir in ReaLemon and vanilla.
Pour into prepared pan.
Chill 4 hours or until set.
Cut into squares.
Mix together relish, walnuts and rind.
Spread over squares.
Garnish as desired. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: strawberry sour cream jello
directions: Mix both boxes of jellos with hot water until dissolved.
Add pineapple, strawberries and bananas.
Pour half mixture into mold, refrigerate for about 20 minutes.
Check to see if it has started to set up-if so, spoon sour cream over mixture, then add the remaining jello over sour cream.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Drain and wash sauerkraut several times and squeeze as much water out as possible.
Mix other ingredients and let set overnight before serving.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In 8 x 8-inch baking pan melt margarine until bubbling in oven.
Mix dry ingredients together in bowl; add milk and mix well.
Pour over margarine.
Drain peaches (save juice); arrange them on batter.
Pour 1/2 the juice on top of peaches.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes.
Serve warm with ice cream.

title: strawberry daiquiri pie
directions: In large mixer bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in Eagle Brand milk until smooth.
Stir in daiquiri mix and rum.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into prepared crust.
Chill or freeze for 4 hours or until firm.
Garnish with fresh strawberries.

title: crab ball
directions: Stir cream cheese, pimento and diced onions until evenly mixed.
Mold into ball.
Cover ball with 1/2 can crab meat, drained.
Chill for 2 to 3 hours.
Cover with shrimp sauce. Serve with crackers.

title: catfish gumbo
directions: Heat oil in large stock pot.
Saute celery, green pepper, onion and garlic.
Add beef broth, tomatoes, okra, thyme, bay leaf, cayenne pepper, oregano and salt.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Add catfish and continue simmering 15 minutes or until catfish flakes easily.
Remove bay leaf.
Serve over cooked rice, if desired.
Makes 10 servings.

title: crepes
directions: Combine all ingredients plus 1/8 teaspoon salt.
Beat until smooth.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter in small dish in microwave. Add 2 tablespoons oil to butter.
With brush, put some butter/oil on bottom of hot omelet pan (do this between every crepe).
Then put about 1/3 cup crepe mixture into pan.
Swirl around so it spreads out evenly.
Cook a couple minutes.
Turn over and cook couple more minutes.

title: diets delight salad
directions: Sprinkle jello on cottage cheese; mix.
Add fruit mix, then add Cool Whip.

title: vegetable beef soup
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Mix all ingredients.
Simmer 2 to 3 hours or until carrots and potatoes are soft.

title: tamale pie
directions: In a large frying pan, brown ground beef and onion; drain off excess fat.
Add tomato sauce, water, taco seasoning, salt and pepper.
Simmer covered 45 minutes.
Stir in corn and olives.
In a saucepan, add milk and cornmeal; mix together.
Cook 3 to 5 minutes until thickened.
Pour meat mixture into a 3-quart casserole.
Top with corn meal mix.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: fried rice (basic)
directions: Slice bacon in 1/4-inch pieces and stir-fry until cooked, but not crispy.
Push aside.
Crack eggs in same skillet and scramble. Throw in onions and push aside with bacon and eggs.
Toss in rice and sprinkle on soy sauce and Accent.
Mix all together and turn off heat.

title: fettuccine and asparagus in parmesan sauce
directions: Saute mushrooms and garlic in margarine for about 2 minutes. Stir in asparagus; set aside.
In small bowl, combine egg and Ricotta cheese.
Mix until smooth.
Add milk.

title: casey's famous meatballs
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In large mixing bowl, mix together all ingredients.
Mix everything with your hands (you did wash them, didn't you?).
Keep squeezing the mixture and turning it around and around in bowl.
Shape into 1-inch meatballs and arrange in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan, next to each other, but not touching. Bake for 20 minutes.
You don't have to turn them, they will brown evenly.

title: dump cake
directions: Pour pie filling into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add pineapple and juice and spread evenly over cherry mixture.
Sprinkle cake mix on top of pineapple.
Pour melted margarine over cake mix.
Sprinkle with coconut and nuts.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together, then add next 3 ingredients. Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes. Yield:
1 pie.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook chopped onion and the broccoli per package directions, then drain.
Add soup, eggs and cheese.
Pour mixture into greased casserole dish.

title: overnight caramel cookies
directions: Mix flour, sugar, salt, soda and cream of tartar.
Melt shortening and cool; add to mixture.
Beat eggs and mix well; add vanilla and mix well.
Form dough into four or five rolls and refrigerate overnight.
Slice and bake at 350° until golden brown, placing them on ungreased cookie sheet.

title: blueberry jello salad
directions: Prepare Jell-O as directed, substituting juice from fruit for 1 cup of water.
Add fruit.
Chill.
Mix together the cream cheese, sour cream, vanilla, sugar and pecans.
Spread topping on Jell-O.
Sprinkle a few pecans on top.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel and cube eggplant and cook until slightly tender.
Drain and cool.
In skillet saute onion, green pepper and tomatoes.
In large casserole dish combine the eggplant with beaten egg, 1/2 can cream of mushroom soup and crackers to thicken the mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Remove from oven, cover with favorite cheese.
Place back into oven long enough to melt cheese.

title: breakfast burrito
directions: Saute sausage.
Scramble eggs.
Add onions.
Roll in soft tortilla shells and heat in skillet about 5 minutes or until hot.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Marinate all vegetables in dressing for 24 hours.
Makes 8 servings.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Beat in sugar, salt and vanilla. Fold in chocolate chips when stiff enough to peak.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Combine bay leaf and a small amount of water in a saucepan and boil.
Arrange zucchini in a colander or straining rack.
Reduce heat and place rack in a saucepan.
Cover and steam 8 minutes or until zucchini is crisp-tender.
Set aside.

title: zucchini nut loaf
directions: In mixing bowl, stir together flour, cinnamon, baking soda, salt, nutmeg and baking powder; set aside.
Then in another bowl, beat together sugar and shredded zucchini.
Add egg, oil and lemon peel; mix well.
Stir flour mixture into zucchini mixture.
Gently fold in chopped nuts.

Turn batter into greased 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pan. Bake in 350° oven for 55 to 60 minutes or until wooden pick inserted near center comes out clean. Cool in pan 10 minutes. Remove from pan and cool on wire rack. Wrap to store loaf overnight before serving.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Combine macaroni with chopped vegetables and eggs.
Mix with mustard and mayonnaise.
Add seasoning.

title: seven layer bars
directions: Mix butter and graham crackers.
Pat in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer in order:
butterscotch chips, chocolate chips, coconut and walnuts.
Pour milk over the top and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together (except rice) and bring to a simmer for 15 minutes.
Mix in rice and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
This is good served with baked chicken and salad. Serves 6 people.

title: skillet peanut butter fudge
directions: In electric skillet, combine sugar, butter and milk.
Set heat at 280° and bring to a boil.
Boil 5 minutes, stirring constantly. Turn off heat.
Add the rest of ingredients; stir until melted and well blended.
Pour into buttered 8-inch pan.

title: broiled shrimp in garlic butter
directions: Brown garlic in butter.
Remove garlic; mix other seasonings in butter.
Place peeled and deveined shrimp in baking dish.
Pour butter mixture over shrimp.
Broil 5 minutes, or until done.
Add lemon juice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: deviled salmon
directions: Blend first 5 ingredients for about 15 seconds.
Flake salmon. Combine with sauce from blender; turn into casserole dish.
Top with crumbs and then with lemon slices.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: brussels sprouts (any vegetable) soup
directions: Saute onion and tater until tender.
Add sprouts, broth, salt and pepper.
Boil until tender.
Puree in food processor.
Return to pan.
Mix egg with milk with fork.
Stir into soup.
Cook and stir until hot.
Do not boil.

title: lemon pie
directions: Crust:
Beat vanilla wafers up (in blender) to fine crumbs and pour into pie dish.
Line sides of dish with vanilla wafers (whole).

title: heavenly fudge sauce
directions: Combine powdered sugar, chocolate morsels, butter and evaporated milk in a medium saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring frequently, 15 to 20 minutes or until mixture comes to a boil.
Boil 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; stir in vanilla.
Let cool.
Serve over ice cream, cake, etc.
Yields 3 cups.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients.
Dredge chicken in flour mixture.
Heat oil in skillet over medium-high heat.
Add chicken and cook.
Remove; drain and return.
Combine soy sauce, preserves, barbecue sauce and onions.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer for 40 minutes.
The last 15 minutes, stir in green pepper, water chestnuts and pineapple.
Serve over rice.

title: sweet-sour chicken
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together.
Pour over the chicken parts, after arranging skin side up, in a baking dish.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Baste several times.

title: pecan crunch fudge
directions: Combine brown sugar, butter and evaporated milk in a 3-quart saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture reaches soft ball stage (238°).

title: 7 minute frosting
directions: Beat egg whites with mixer until it stands in peaks.
Cook water and sugar together until it forms a string like candy.
Pour mixture over egg whites while still beating.
Add cream of tartar then vanilla.
May use on any cake.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream together.
Drop on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: fudge sundae pie
directions: Mix corn 1/4 cup corn syrup, sugar and butter.
Cook over medium heat, stirring, until it boils.
Remove from heat; add cereal and stir to coat.
Press into 9-inch pie pan to form crust.

title: lemon sauce or nutmeg sauce
directions: In saucepan, combine sugar and cornstarch.
Gradually stir in water.
Stir constantly.
Boil for 1 minute.
Add butter and nutmeg to taste.
If you want lemon sauce, use 2 teaspoons lemon extract.
If nutmeg, use 2 teaspoons vanilla extract.
Serve warm over pound cake or ice cream.

title: wine cake
directions: Mix eggs, wine and oil well.
Add cake mix and cinnamon; mix for 2 minutes.
Bake in a Bundt pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Cool in pan for 10 minutes, then turn out onto cooling rack. Sprinkle with powdered sugar or your favorite icing when completely cooled.

title: orange sesame muffins
directions: Lightly coat 12 muffin tin cups with nonstick cooking spray. Set aside.
Sift together flours, baking powder, baking soda and salt in a large bowl.
Stir in oats.
In a separate bowl, whisk together honey, egg, canola oil, sesame oil, buttermilk, orange peel, orange extract and sesame seed.
Mix together contents of the 2 bowls, stirring until just combined.
Fill muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 12.

title: pimento cheese
directions: Put milk and cheese in broiler and melt before adding other ingredients. Add egg, sugar and pimento; cook for about 10 minutes.
Add salt.
Take off of heat and add mayonnaise; cover immediately.
Cool and refrigerate.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Grease casserole dish.
Brown ground beef, drain and layer with onions and soup.
Top with cheese. Spread Tater Tots on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and eggs.
Sift flour, cream of tartar and salt; add to creamed mixture.
Mix until well blended; chill, if desired.
Form into small balls the size of small walnuts. Roll in sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Place on an ungreased cookie sheet about 2 inches apart.
Bake at 425° (degreased) for 8 to 10 minutes.
Yield: 90 servings.

title: patrician potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes and mash.
Blend in sour cream and cream cheese. Add dash of salt.
Whip vigorously.
Put in buttered casserole.

title: fried tomatoes
directions: Slice tomatoes 1/2-inch thick.
Beat egg slightly and season with salt and pepper.
Dip tomato into the crumbs, then into the egg, then back into the crumbs.
Fry in a small amount of grease in a skillet until brown on both sides.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake as directed.
Put 1/2 of mixture into 9 x 12-inch pan. Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Melt the caramels, oleo and milk. Pour over baked cake portion.
Sprinkle chips over this, then add the nuts.
Pour the rest of the cake mix over this and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: scotch shortbread cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly the butter and
sugar.
Stir
in
flour. Mix well with hands.
Separate and
add
coloring, if desired. Chill dough.
Roll out and cut into
desired shapes.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets.
(The tops do not brown during baking nor does the shape of the cookies change.) Bake at 300° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: low-fat fettuccine alfredo
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan over medium heat.
Add garlic; saute 1 minute.
Stir in flour.
Gradually add milk, stirring with a wire whisk until blended.
Cook 8 minutes or until thickened, stirring constantly.
Stir in cream cheese; cook 2 minutes.
Add 1 cup Parmesan cheese, stirring constantly until it melts.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown beef and onion; drain and add remaining ingredients. Simmer; serve with grated cheese and coarsely crushed taco chips or tortilla chips and sour cream if desired.

title: wanda's bourbon balls
directions: Mix wafer crumbs, cocoa, sugar and nuts.
Add corn syrup and bourbon; mix well.
Turn into 1-inch balls and roll in powdered sugar.
Cover and store for a day or so to ripen.

title: betty's chili
directions: Saute onion, then ground beef, until pink of meat is gone. Put into 3 or 4-quart cooking pan.
Add taco seasoning to taste. Add tomato juice.
Put beans in blender.
Add to pot.
Add chili powder.
Cook 1 hour.

title: chocolate trifle
directions: Prepare brownie mix and bake according to package directions in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Prick top of warm brownies at 1-inch intervals using a fork; drizzle with Kahlua.
Let cool and crumble.

title: scalloped asparagus
directions: Drain and place 1 can of asparagus on bottom of baking dish for first layer.
Cover with white sauce, then cheese.
Repeat for second layer.
Cover with bread crumbs and bake at 350° until hot all through.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chocolate peanut butter cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl; mix well.
Add chopped peanuts.
Pour batter into 3 greased and floured 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool in pans.
Remove.
Frost with Chocolate Peanut Butter Icing.

title: mississippi mud pie
directions: Combine melted chocolate and margarine in a large bowl.
Mix well.
Add remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake in a preheated 375° oven for 35 minutes.

title: layered nacho dip
directions: Combine beans and taco seasoning.
Spread into a 12 x 8 x 2-inch dish.
Layer remaining ingredients in order listed.
Serve with large corn chips.
Makes about 8 cups.

title: breakfast butterflies
directions: Children help fix scrambled eggs and toast.
Eggs are served in the center of the plate to form the butterfly body.
The children can add triangle "toast wings" and add thin, rectangle "toast feelers".

title: ham, cabbage and rice skillet
directions: In a large deep nonstick skillet, mix 2 cups water, cabbage, rice, seasoning packet, red bell pepper and white part of sliced scallions.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat, cover and simmer 15 minutes.

title: chicken and rice vegetable soup
directions: Cook celery and onions in margarine until tender.
Stir in water, chicken, carrots, tomatoes, bouillon, thyme, pepper and bay leaf.
Bring to boil; simmer 30 minutes.
Remove bay leaf.
Stir in rice and cook 15 minutes or until rice is done.

title: squash casserole
directions: Slice squash and onion.
Steam on steamer until soft.
Add salt and pepper.
Mix soup, egg and cheese together.
Mix in squash and onion.
Put in baking dish.
Put shredded Cheddar cheese on top and crumble Ritz crackers on top of that.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: red clam sauce
directions: In large saucepan, saut garlic in olive oil until lightly browned. Slowly stir in tomato paste and white tomatoes. Add parsley, salt, pepper, oregano and sugar. Simmer 1/2 hour. Add clams and simmer an additional 15 minutes. Serve over spaghetti. Serves 6.

title: pork roast with onion gravy
directions: Place onion soup mix in the center of a 30 x 20-inch piece of aluminum foil. Place pork roast, fat side down, on soup. Fold foil over and secure tightly, leaving room for juices. Bake in a 300° oven for 3 1/2 hours. Remove roast to a serving dish.

title: easy vegetable soup
directions: Brown meat; drain fat.
Add onion, celery, beef bouillon and enough water to cover.
Cover pan and cook for 15 minutes.
Add pasta, mixed vegetables, tomato soup and undrained beans.
Add more water, if necessary.
Cover and cook 8 to 10 minutes or until pasta and vegetables are tender.
Serves 6.
Soup freezes well.

title: pistachio delight
directions: Crumble cookies and add to the melted margarine.
Mix and press into a 9 x 13-inch sheet cake pan.
(Save 1/2 cup for the 4th layer.)
Next, mix together on medium speed for 3 minutes and spread on cookie mixture the cream cheese, confectioners sugar and large Cool Whip.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Preheat oven
In heavy saucepan over low heat melt chocolate and
butter.
In large bowl combine Eagle Brand milk and warm
chocolate
mixture.
Mix well. Add eggs, water, vanilla and salt,
mixing
well.
Pour
filling into prepared crust and top with
cup
nuts and coconut.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until the center is softly set.
Cool and chill for 3 to 4
hours before serving.
Garnish with whipped cream and pecans, if desired.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix well and drop on a greased sheet.
Bake 12 minutes at 375°.
Sprinkle top before baking with cinnamon and sugar.
Yields 5 dozen.

title: bean-rice casserole
directions: Place rice, apple juice, chives and bell pepper in slow cooker and cook for 3 hours.
Meanwhile, steam garbanzos (which have soaked overnight in water) for 1 hour.
Add peas, carrots and corn to steamer and continue steaming for another 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove vegetables along with garbanzos to rice in slow cooker.
Serve when ready.

title: pork chop-vegetable skillet
directions: Spray a large skillet with Pam.
Brown chops on both sides in the skillet for 15 minutes.
Remove chops.
Drain off fat.
Place potatoes in skillet and top with meat.
Combine tomatoes, onion, celery, parsley, bouillon and sage, then pour over meat and potatoes.
Cover and cook over medium-low heat for 20 minutes.
Add zucchini.
Cover and cook about 10 minutes more or until tender. Remove meat and vegetables.
Keep warm.
Skim any fat from pan. Measure juices.
Add water to make 3/4 cup liquid; return to skillet.
Mix water and cornstarch.
Add to skillet.
Cook until thickened.
Spoon over meat and vegetables.

title: green bean delight
directions: Mix ingredients together in saucepan or iron skillet.
Cook over medium heat until bacon is done.
Simmer on low 5 minutes longer.

title: acapulco eggs
directions: In large skillet, cook tortillas in butter until golden. Remove and set aside.
Add onion; cook until tender.
Drain tomatoes, reserving liquid.
Add liquid to skillet over high heat and cover; stir frequently.
Stir in tomatoes, meat and pepper; heat through.
Reduce heat.
Add tortillas and eggs.
Cover and cook until eggs are set.
Sprinkle with cheese; cover and cook 1 minute until cheese melts.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni for 10 to 15 minutes in boiling water.
Do not overcook.
Drain macaroni.
Place in a large mixing bowl.
Dice cheese.
Add all other ingredients.
Mix well.
Place in proper cookware and bake for 20 minutes until brown.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Combine peaches with 1 cup sugar; set aside.
Melt margarine in a baking dish.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar, flour, baking powder, milk and salt.
Fold into margarine.
Place peaches on top.
Bake for 1 hour at 350° or until golden brown.

title: chicken breast casserole
directions: Mix together in casserole dish; sprinkle with cup cracker crumbs.
Sprinkle almonds on top.
Bake 30 minutes in a 300° oven.

title: esta's butter pound cake
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients well.
Add all 6 eggs.
Mix well but don't beat to death.
Add flour and milk until blended.
Spray two 8 or 9-inch cake pans with Baker's Joy.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 45 minutes until knife comes out clean in center.
Turn out on rack to cool.

title: country french chicken
directions: In a large skillet over medium-high heat, warm the olive oil. Season the chicken; brown it in the oil for 2 to 3 minutes on each side and remove to a plate. Return pan to stove and reduce heat to medium. Add butter to pan and saute the shallots, carrots and mushrooms. Saute for 3 to 5 minutes, until mushrooms darken and carrot bits are fork-tender. Add tarragon and parsley and stir. Add wine and reduce liquid for 1 to 2 minutes. Add tomatoes to the sauce and stir to combine. Add chicken back to pan and simmer chicken in sauce for 6 minutes or until chicken is cooked through and juices run clear.

title: macaroni, cheese deluxe
directions: Cook macaroni; drain well.
Combine cottage cheese, sour cream, egg, salt and pepper.
Add shredded cheese; mix well.
Stir in cooked macaroni.
Put in greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: flour tortillas
directions: Combine flour and salt.
Cut in shortening with a pastry cutter until crumbly like coarse cornmeal.
Mix in enough water to make stiff dough.
Knead on a floured surface until smooth.
Make 6 equal portions and shape into balls.
Cover with a damp towel and let rest for 15 to 20 minutes.
Roll each ball into an 8-inch round.
Cook on a moderately hot griddle or skillet until freckled with brown spots, being careful not to break puffy air bubbles as you turn it.
The tortilla will still look white for most part. Keep warm in a clean dish towel covered with foil.
Use tortillas to make burritos.
These will not fall apart.

title: crisp cucumber pickles
directions: Wash and cut cucumbers; soak overnight in lime and water. Next morning wash them in cold water and soak 3 more hours. Combine vinegar, sugar and spices, dissolving well. Pour over cucumbers and soak 5-6 hours or overnight. Then boil in liquid until transparent. Fill jars, seal and process.

title: spinach pie ii
directions: Beat 2 of the eggs and Ricotta cheese until blended.
Stir in rest of the ingredients except the last egg.
Fill pie crust.
Top with other crust.
Brush top crust with egg and prick vent holes. Bake below center rack at 425° for 15 minutes.
Continue baking at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Let stand for 10 minutes before serving.

title: pier 4 marinated mushrooms
directions: Place mushrooms in container, Add remaining ingredients.
Stir well. Merinate for 3 Days.

title: hermit cookies
directions: Cream shortening, brown sugar and egg.
Mix together water, flour, salt, soda, cloves, cinnamon and nutmeg; add to first mixture.
Add remaining ingredients.
Spoon out on cookie sheet and bake 15 minutes at 325°.

title: salsa
directions: Chop all ingredients; put in big saucepan.
Bring to boil and turn down and simmer for 1 hour.
Put in cans and seal.

title: pocket bread
directions: Combine 1/2 cup warm water, yeast and sugar.
Combine flour, salt and oil, then yeast mixture, along with remaining water. Knead.
Let rise until double.
Roll into log 8-inches long.
Cut into 8 pieces and pat into balls, then roll into circles 6 1/2-inches in diameter.
Place on greased squares of foil and let stand one hour uncovered.
Place oven rack on lowest point and preheat to 500°.
Bake breads directly on rack for 5 minutes, or until barely brown.
Cover to keep soft.

title: hamburger - noodle casserole
directions: Mix together.
Bake in casserole at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Wash, slice and drain tomatoes.
In large zip lock bag add, flour, corn meal, salt, and pepper.
Zip bag shut and shake to mix all ingredients together.
While tomatoes are draining, in large cast iron skillet, place generous amount of crisco or non fat cooking oil, heat skillet.
Place several tomatoes into bag mixture and shake to coat each tomato with coating.

Open bag, shake off excess coating of each tomato and place it into the hot oil and cook to golden brown color on both side and tender in the middle. Drain tomatoes onto paper towels when removing from skillet and sprinkle again with salt.

title: quinze pie(copied from mother's 1873 cookbook)
directions: Press stewed quinzes through a sieve.
Add milk and eggs. Sweeten to taste.
Pour into a prepared pie crust and bake 45 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: seafaring vegetable salad
directions: Place salmon in a bowl; sprinkle with lemon juice and toss. Add remaining ingredients and mix lightly.
Chill until serving time.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: younger set spice apple nog
directions: Beat egg white until it forms soft peaks.
Beat in sugar. Combine apple juice, ginger and cinnamon; fold into egg.
Pour into 4 tall glasses.
Fill with ginger ale.
Mix gently; sprinkle nutmeg on top.

title: "sin" butter
directions: Combine ingredients and mix well with electric mixer.
Yield: about 20 ounces.
Put mixture in airtight plastic container and keep it refrigerated.
You won't be able to keep this sinful butter for long once your family finds it.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Mix hamburger, rice, eggs, Lawry's, pepper and onion.
Form into 3-inch balls and wrap with cabbage leaves (cabbage may also be cut in quarters and cooked in kettle with rolls).
Place in pressure cooker.
Cover rolls with tomato soup and add one soup can of water.
Shut pressure cooker and cook over medium heat 30 minutes after it starts to jiggle.

title: pork chops and gravy
directions: Salt, pepper and flour pork chops; brown.
Drain off grease. Cut up onion and add to pork chops.
Mix mushroom soup and water and pour over pork chops and onion.
Cover and let simmer for approximately 40 minutes.

title: paprika baked chicken with stuffing
directions: Put chicken in 3 quart baking dish; sprinkle with salt, paprika and pepper; dot with 3 tablespoons butter.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.

title: mulled cider
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bring to boil slowly. Simmer, covered, 20 to 30 minutes. Strain and serve hot.

title: peanut butter crispies
directions: Combine butter, sugar and corn syrup in a saucepan.
Bring to a rolling boil.
Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter and cereal.
Drop into cookies on wax paper.
Let cool.

title: brown sugar syrup
directions: Add sugars to water and boil 3 to 4 minutes.
Delicious syrup.

title: jello salad
directions: Put cottage cheese in bowl.
Add Jell-O (no water).
Stir until Jell-O dissolves.
Drain pineapple and add pineapple and Cool Whip, mix well.
Add coconut, chill and serve.

title: mushroom-crab meat souffle
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
To cook souffle slowly and thoroughly, place an ungreased 2 1/2-quart casserole in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking pan and pour boiling water into baking pan about 1 inch deep.
Place in oven while preparing souffle.

title: szechwan beef stir-fry(serves 4)
directions: Cut steaks lengthwise into 2 strips.
Slice across the grain into 1/4-inch thick strips.
Combine soy sauce, 2 teaspoons oil, sugar and cornstarch; stir into strips.
Heat remaining 2 teaspoons oil in wok over medium-high heat.
Add garlic, ginger and pepper pods.
Cook 30 seconds.
Add bell pepper and corn; stir-fry 1 1/2 minutes.
Add peas pods and stir-fry 30 seconds. Remove vegetables from the skillet and reserve.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Mix together.
Sprinkle bacon grease on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: nacho dip
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain fat.
Add taco seasoning and tomatoes.
Put cheese into a slow cooker; turn to medium heat. Add hamburger mixture; stir.
Serve when cheese is melted.

title: party potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 350°.

title: nuts, bolts and screws
directions: Melt butter or margarine in a large roasting pan.
Add all other ingredients and place in a 250° oven.
Bake for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Pour the entire can of pineapple with juice into a 13 x 9-inch pan (ungreased).
Sprinkle coconut on top of pineapple (do not stir).
Sprinkle entire box of cake mix over the coconut (do not stir).
Slice the 2 sticks of margarine in small patties and place on top of cake mix.
Be sure to use all the margarine and cover cake mix with slices.
Sprinkle chopped pecans over margarine and bake for 45 minutes or until golden brown in 350° oven.

title: easy pot roast
directions: Place foil in baking dish.
Place meat on foil.
Cover meat with dry soup mix and cream of mushroom soup.
Wrap foil around meat and cook in 300° oven for 4 hours.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw and drain spinach (pretty dry).
Add water chestnuts (if desired).
Combine ingredients; chill overnight.
Can be served with crackers or pumpernickel or rye bread.
We usually buy a round loaf of bread and cut the middle out to make a bowl.
Put the dip in that and serve with the little pieces of bread that were taken out of the middle of the bread.

title: chocolate earthquake cake
directions: Prepare cake batter according to package instructions. Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 12 inch baking pan.
Cover the bottom of pan with nuts and coconut.
Pour cake batter on top. Melt margarine in bowl.
Add the cream cheese and powdered sugar; stir to blend.
Spoon over unbaked batter and bake for 40 to 42 minutes.

title: peanut butter
directions: Shell the peanuts and put them into a blender.
Add the salad oil.
Blend until chunky or smooth, whichever is preferred taste. Add salt and honey, if necessary.
Makes 1 cup.

title: easy barbecue chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix salad dressing, onion soup mix, and preserves.
Pour over chicken.
Bake 1 1/2 hours uncovered. Serves 6-8.

title: vegetable spaghetti
directions: Saute vegetables in butter.
Cook spaghetti.
In 12 x 8-inch baking dish, layer 1/2 spaghetti sauce, vegetables, cottage cheese and Mozzarella cheese; repeat layers.
Top with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: lemonade
directions: Heat 1 pint of water with sugar until sugar is melted, then cool.
Roll lemons until soft, squeeze lemon into water with Kool-Aid.
Makes 1 gallon.
Add slices of lemon.

title: georgia pecan pie
directions: Mix eggs and corn syrup, add sugar.
Stir in salt and vanilla.
Mix well.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Spread pecans evenly on pie shell bottom.
Mix melted butter into syrup mixture.
Pour over pecans which should rise to top.
Bake at 375° until center is firm, about 20 minutes.

title: parmesan potatoes
directions: Put dry ingredients in a bag.
Shake.
Peel and quarter potatoes; drop into bag and shake well.
Meanwhile, melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Lay the potatoes in melted butter and bake 45 to 60 minutes at 350°.
Turn once during baking.
Good!!

title: never fail meringue
directions: Cook cornstarch, boiling water, cold water and lemon juice; set aside.
Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry.
Beat in sugar 1 tablespoon at a time.
Beat until well mixed.
Beat in cornstarch mixture.
Put on pie filling, making sure meringue covers pie well into pastry.
Bake at 375° until golden brown.
Will not fail or pull away from sides of crust.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Layer crumbled bread, cheese, diced peppers, chopped onions, mushrooms and bite sized pieces of sausage in well buttered 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.

title: ham and fruit skillet
directions: In a large skillet over medium heat, brown ham on both sides. Arrange peach slices around edges of ham; dot with margarine. Sprinkle with brown sugar and cinnamon.
Turn ham and peach slices to glaze.
Cover; cook until thoroughly heated.
Makes 4 servings.

title: mayonnaise chicken
directions: Peel skin off of chicken.
Boil chicken for 15 minutes.
Pull out of pan and let cool.
Spread mayonnaise over pieces of chicken.
Crush up croutons and roll pieces of chicken in crumbs. Place on baking pan and place in oven at 350° for 20 minutes or until brown.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Form into round egg shaped steaks (looks like a big egg). Bake at 450° for 20 minutes.

title: seafood rice casserole
directions: White sauce:
Mix butter, flour, milk, salt and paprika.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix gelatin and boiling water.
Place in refrigerator.
Put cream cheese in a bowl to soften.
Crush graham crackers and 1 stick melted butter.
Add powdered sugar; mix well.
Save 1/4 of crust mixture for top.
Press mixture into bottom and sides of a 13 X 9 dish.
Cream sugar, cream cheese and vanilla.
Add gelatin to cream cheese mixture; mix well.
Beat evaporated milk until stiff. Add gelatin to cream cheese mixture; fold into whipped milk.
Pour mixture into crust; cover with remaining crust mixture.
Chill well before serving.

title: stroganoff(brazilian)
directions: Saute onions in butter (or oleo) with garlic.
Add beef and fry; set aside.
Make sauce of Worcestershire sauce, plus 1 cup water.
Add beef to sauce and cook, stirring frequently.
Add another cup of water when needed.
Add the ketchup; bring to a boil.
Lower heat to simmer.
Add the evaporated milk; cook with cover on for 10 minutes.

title: bread pudding
directions: Break up bread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add eggs, brown sugar and butter to hot milk.
Stir and pour over bread.
Add raisins and stir until bread is moist.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and over cinnamon sprinkle a light coating of white sugar.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
(Knife should come out clean when inserted.)

title: top secret mrs. field's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large mixing bowl, cream butter, sugars, eggs and vanilla.
In a separate bowl, sift together flour, salt, baking powder and soda.
Combine wet and dry ingredients.
Stir in chocolate chips.
With your fingers, place golf ball size portions of dough 2 inches apart on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 9 minutes, or until edges are light brown. Makes 30 cookies.

title: dirt pudding
directions: Mix pudding with milk, then combine all other ingredients except for the cookies.
Lay half of the crushed cookies into the bottom of a baking pan or casserole.
Cover with pudding mixture. Put rest of cookies on top of the pudding mixture.
Chill. Can be made a day ahead of time.

title: mommy's mashed potatoes
directions: Drain potatoes.
Add butter while hot.
Beat with mixer until fluffy, adding milk and mayonnaise.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Beat shortening, sugars, vanilla and eggs until light and fluffy.
Mix flour with soda and salt, then blend into shortening mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop onto greased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for about 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chocolate drop cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Melt chocolate and mix ingredients. Drop by teaspoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: hermits
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add egg and molasses.
Then add all dry ingredients and water; mix well.
Add desired amount of raisins and nuts.

title: layered spaghetti bake
directions: In large skillet combine beef, onion and garlic.
Cook until tender.
Stir in Ragu, water and basil.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, simmer 10 minutes.
Prepare spaghetti as directed, then drain.

title: sweet-sour chicken
directions: Put chicken pieces in shallow baking dish.
Mix dressing, soup mix and preserves with small amount of water.
Pour over chicken and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until chicken is tender. Serves 4.

title: potato lefse(makes 15 large rounds)
directions: Bring to a boil in 3-quart saucepan the water, margarine, sugar and salt. Take off burner and add milk and flakes; mix. If it's too soupy, add 1/4 cup more flakes. Add half and half; mix well. Cool in refrigerator overnight. Put paper towel over potatoes to collect moisture and add cover before refrigerating.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread rolls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Push together to cover sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: angel cookies(lo-cal)
directions: Mix cake mix, cherry water and almond extract until well blended.
Fold in coconut or oats.
Drop by level tablespoonful on lightly sprayed cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: black magic cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two 9-inch round pans or a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
In a large mixing bowl, blend sugar, flour, cocoa, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Add eggs, coffee, buttermilk, oil and vanilla; beat on medium 2 minutes (batter will be thin).
Pour batter into prepared pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes for round pans; bake 35 to 40 minutes for rectangular pan.
When toothpick comes out clean, cake is done.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pans to wire rack; cool completely.
Frost as desired.

title: pot roast
directions: Brown meat on all sides in hot fat.
Dissolve bouillon cube in water; mix with catsup, mustard, salt and pepper.
Add to beef and simmer 3 to 4 hours or until tender.
Add more water occasionally, if necessary.

title: browned chicken and dumplings
directions: In large pot, place hen and cover with water and seasonings (salt and pepper to taste).
Boil for approximately 1 hour or until tender.
Remove meat from pot, cool and debone chicken.
Skim fat from chicken broth; set aside.
Should have enough broth for 1 1/2 cups; if not, add hot water andl.
Add flour, salt and fat from chicken broth and enough broth to have dough consistency of pie dough.
Roll out on floured board about as thin as pie crust; cut in strips and let dry out while making gravy for dumplings.

title: praline pecan crunch
directions: Combine cereal and pecan pieces in a 13 x 9-inch pan and set aside.
Combine corn syrup, brown sugar and margarine in a 2 cup microwavable bowl.
Microwave 1 1/2 minutes or until boiling. Stir in vanilla and baking soda.
Pour over cereal mixture.
Stir to coat evenly.
Bake 1 hour, stirring every 20 minutes, in 250° oven.
Spread on cookie sheet to cool.
Break into pieces.
Yields 10 cups.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Preheat ove to 325°.
Sift flour, sugar, baking powder and baking soda.
Mix in raisins and currants.
Combine beaten eggs, buttermilk and shortening.
Add this liquid mixture to the dry ingredients.
Mix until just moistened.
Do not overmix.
Add caraway seed and mix in gently.
Bake in 325° oven for about 1 hour.
Remove from pan and let cool.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots until tender and crisp, drain and rinse in ice water.
Layer carrots, peppers and onions.
Blend other ingredients until sugar is dissolved.
Pour over veggies and refrigerate, overnight is good.
Use leftover dressing for salads. Good! Keeps well in refrigerator.

title: funnel cake
directions: Add milk and sugar to beaten eggs.
In separate bowl, put dry ingredients.
Add egg mixture; beat until smooth.
Heat about 6 cups of oil to 375°.
Pour batter into hot oil through funnel (small), about 3/4 cup.
Make circle and swirls.
When brown on underside, turn with tongs and brown on other side.
Drain on Scott towel and sprinkle lightly with powdered sugar.

title: impossible taco pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 9 1/4-inch pie dish.
Cook and stir beef and onion; drain.
Stir in taco mix; spread in pie plate. Sprinkle in chilies.
Beat milk, eggs and Bisquick until smooth with wire whisk.
Pour over meat and chilies.
Bake 25 minutes; top with cheese then tomato slices.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes more or until knife inserted comes out clean.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Cut to desired serving size.

title: chunky homemade salsa
directions: Peel, seed and coarsely chop tomatoes (you should have about 14 cups).
Place tomatoes in a large colander.
Let drain about 30 minutes.
Place drained tomatoes in an 8-quart Dutch oven.
Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer uncovered for 45 to 50 minutes or until thickened (similar to the consistency of chunky salsa), stirring frequently.
Add chili peppers, onion, cilantro, garlic, vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper.
Return mixture to boiling. Remove from heat.
Ladle into pint jars leaving 1/2-inch headspace.
Place lids on jars and process in boiling water bath for 35 minutes.
(Start timing when water begins to boil.)

title: cornmeal sausage bake
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Grease 10 1/2-inch skillet or 2-quart baking dish.
Set aside.
Brown sausage and onion.
Drain well. Combine eggs, cornmeal, corn and milk and oil.
Pour half meat mixture into dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Pour remainder of batter over top.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes.
Let cool 10 minutes. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: lemon-buttermilk frost
directions: In a large bowl, beat ice cream to soften.
Add buttermilk and lemonade concentrate or lemon juice mixture.
Beat until frothy and serve immediately.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash in small amount of boiling water until tender; drain well and mash.
Add salt and pepper.
Combine soup, pimentos, carrots, onion, sour cream and butter, blending well.
Add squash and mix thoroughly.
Line a greased casserole dish with half the stuffing mix.
Spoon squash mix over the stuffing.
Cover with remaining stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until bubbly.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine sweet potatoes, sugar, eggs, vanilla and milk with 1/2 cup butter in mixing bowl; mix well.
Pour into 2-quart casserole dish.

title: rhubarb salad
directions: Cook over low heat until tender, do not stir.
Bring to boil, remove from heat and add 1 6 oz. pkg. strawberry jello.
Stir gently until dissolved; add 2 c. cold water, 1/4 c. lemon juice.
Chill until very thick and spoon into mold.

title: hot dog sauce
directions: Brown ground beef and onions until done.
Drain all possible grease.
Add rest of ingredients.
Pour in about 1 cup water. Simmer until thickens up, like hot dog sauce is supposed to be (2 hours).
Keep adding a little water to keep from sticking.

title: dirt dessert
directions: Cream butter, cream cheese and confectioners sugar in mixer bowl until light and fluffy.
Set aside.
Combine milk and pudding mix in large bowl; mix well.
Let stand until partially set.
Fold in whipped topping and cream cheese mixture.
Place cookies in food processor container.
Process until crumbled.
Layer cookie crumbs and pudding mixture alternately in 2 plastic flowerpots, ending with cookie crumbs.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: big batch muffins(keeps without baking for 2 weeks in refrigerator)
directions: Add 2 cups bran cereal to the boiling water. Set aside. Cream shortening and sugar in large bowl. Add eggs. Beat well. Add buttermilk and scalded bran cereal. Sift flour, baking soda and salt. Add dry ingredients to liquid mixture. You need a big bowl for this recipe. Stir in remaining bran cereal and raisins. Bake in greased muffin tins for 15 to 20 minutes in a 400° oven. By keeping in fridge, unbaked, you can make just what you need.

title: foolproof dark chocolate fudge
directions: In a heavy saucepan over low heat melt chips with milk and salt.
Remove from heat, stir in walnuts and vanilla.
Spread evenly into waxed paper lined 8 to 9 in. pan. Chill 2 hours or until firm. Turn fudge out onto cutting board, peel off paper and cut into squares. Store loosely covered at room temperature.

title: buttermilk pecan pie
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Blend in flour, lemon juice and vanilla.
Stir in buttermilk and pecans.
Pour into the pie shell. Bake at 325° for 55 minutes or until set. Cool on a wire rack. Store in the refrigerator.
Yields 8 servings.

title: shoney's strawberry pie
directions: Combine first five ingredients.
Cook until thick.
Add strawberries and cool.
Pour into pie shells.
Top with whipped cream.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Toast bread in 250° or 300° oven for 20 to 25 minutes until hard.
Bring water to a boil and add Hi-Energy Chicken soup Supplements, celery and onion.
Cook until tender.
Break up bread in mixing bowl and add oil, sage and black pepper.
To the bread mixture, add Hi-Energy Supplement mixture with celery, onion and chicken/turkey.
Mix well.
Add egg and mix well.
Spray glass dish with canola spray and fill dish with dressing mixture.
Bake 40 minutes or until brown on top and moist in the middle (350° oven). Makes 2 servings.
(Eat one and freeze one for later.)

title: chocolate peanut butter squares
directions: Make sandwiches with crackers and a small amount of peanut butter.
Melt the chocolate chips in a double boiler and dip sandwiches in chocolate.
Place on cookie sheets lined with waxed paper and sprinkle rainbow sprinkles on top for decoration.
One bag of chocolate chips does 1/2 box of Wheat Thins.

title: glorified macaroni and cheese
directions: Boil macaroni and drain.
Mix other ingredients with macaroni and put in a 9 x 12-inch casserole dish.
Top with buttered bread crumbs (or cheese).
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until it bubbles.
This can be made in advance and baked later.
You can leave out the ground beef for just a side dish.

title: christmas snacks or things
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add cracker crumbs and coconut; mix well and spread in a 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan.
Press.
Sprinkle over this, evenly, the chocolate bits, then nuts and, finally, the condensed milk.
Do not mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool; cut into squares.
Yields 24 to 30.

title: "no peek" beef tips
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake in covered casserole dish at 300° for 3 hours.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: my dip
directions: Spread cream cheese in bottom of casserole.
Spread beans on top of cream cheese, then layer salsa.
Top with cheese.
Bake or microwave until top cheese is melted.
Serve with chips and enjoy. Double recipe for a crowd.

title: coleslaw
directions: Mix mayonnaise, vinegar, sugar, salt and spices.
Mix all other ingredients and cover with dressing.

title: peanut soup
directions: Steam chicken and season to taste.
In separate pot, mix peanut butter and water; cook to boiling, using medium heat and stirring constantly.
Appearance in beginning will be milky white, but will turn a light brown as it continues to cook.
Blenderize tomato paste and onion to a liquid state.
Once all this is finished, mix all together with ginger, Tabasco or red pepper and return to a low simmer.
Serves 4.

title: squash casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Peel, mash and whip sweet potatoes until smooth.
You should have 3 cups potatoes after mashing.
Add beaten egg, half and half, sugar, salt and Cointreau.
Beat until light and fluffy. Put in buttered 1 1/2 quart casserole.
Drizzle with 1 tablespoon melted butter.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes 6 servings.

title: hidden valley ranch oyster crackers
directions: Combine dressing mix, dill and oil (also lemon pepper and garlic powder).
Pour over crackers; stir to coat.
Place in warm oven (250°) 15 to 20 minutes.
Stir gently halfway through baking.

title: shaker strawberry summer pudding
directions: Remove the crust from the bread.
Mash and sweeten berries. Line a
pan with foil or wax paper and place the slices of bread on the bottom.
Spoon berries over the bread and alternate berries and bread until pan is filled.
Cover with wax paper and cardboard, slightly smaller than the pan.
Chill at least 8 hours or overnight.
To serve, invert on a platter.
Top with whipped cream.
Scatter fresh berries on top and around edge.

title: new england clam chowder
directions: In covered 2-quart pan, boil clams in own water with potatoes, bouillon cubes, sugar and m.s.g. until potatoes are tender.
Saute onions in salt pork until tender, but not scorched.
Add onions to clam mixture and heat over low heat.

title: chocolate cherry fruitcake(with chocolate glaze)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour one 10-inch fluted tube pan.
Stir together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Add the chopped red cherries and mix well with your hands, separating the bits of cherries.
Set aside.
In a large bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add vanilla and blend.
Stir in melted chocolate.
Add dry ingredients and milk alternately, in 3 parts each, blending well.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Pour into prepared tube pan. Bake 60 to 70 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes; then turn out onto rack.

title: mrs. huff's nut cake
directions: Mix the
fruit
and
nuts
with
1 cup of flour and set aside. Cream
the butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well.
Add flour and beat well.
Add vanilla.
Mix in fruit and nuts.
Grease
and flour tube pan.
Pour mixture in and bake about 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Add and mix softened butter, sugar, milk and vanilla together. Mix in flour, slowly, along with baking powder.
Add eggs last and mix well.
Roll into a ball; divide in half.
Roll out.
Cut out shapes.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Allow to cool. Decorate.

title: stagecoach chicken
directions: In bowl, combine salad dressing and egg; set aside. Cut up chicken ; with water, rinse and drain well. Dredge chicken pieces in flour, salt and pepper. Dip in salad dressing mixture and roll in cornflake crumbs. Arrange pieces on broiler pan (lined with foil if desired); drizzle with butter. Bake at 350° for 2 hours or until fork tender.

title: blueberry congealed salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 1/2 cups boiling water.
Mix in pineapple and blueberries with juices.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Refrigerate until firm.

title: cream cheese and vegetable pizza appetizer
directions: For crust, separate crescent rolls into four 4-roll rectangles and press into the bottom and up the sides of an ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan, pressing perforations to seal.
Bake in a 375° oven for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden.
Cool the crust in the pan on a wire rack.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix pineapple and cherry pie filling together.
Sprinkle cake mix over this mixture.
Melt margarine and pour over the mixture. Bake at 325° until it bubbles and browns.
Bake in square baking dish.

title: calico beans
directions: Using a clean hand, mix all ingredients, shape meat mixture into patties and place in skillet. Cook like hamburgers until no pink can be seen.

title: low sodium brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and vegetable oil or margarine together in a saucepan.
Remove from stove; stir in sugar, eggs (1 yolk at a time), vanilla and flour.
Add chopped nuts.
Spread the mixture in a shallow pan.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Cut into squares while still warm.
Makes about 16 squares.
One square equals 3 mg. sodium.

title: peas and water chestnuts
directions: Cook frozen peas until almost tender; drain.
Add soup (undiluted), water chestnuts (drained and sliced).
Add salt to taste.
Place in buttered casserole.
Cover with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly and browned.

title: milk gravy
directions: Heat oil on medium heat in iron skillet.
Sprinkle flour over oil and *cook until well mixed.
Slowly stir milk into hot mixture; cook until blended.
Add salt and pepper.
Stir constantly until thickened, about 15 minutes.

title: old fashioned stew
directions: In a small bowl, mix all ingredients together except cabbage (using either vinegar, lime or lemon juice).
Mix well.
Pour over shredded cabbage and refrigerate until ready to use.

title: dumper salad
directions: Dump all ingredients together in order.
Chill.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Combine sweet potatoes, cream, eggs, sugar, salt and butter. Beat until smooth.
Pour into a greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Add marshmallows the last 20 minutes so the tops brown.

title: cheese and tortilla casserole
directions: *To make 2 cups sour milk, place 2 tablespoons lemon juice or vinegar in a glass measuring cup. Add enough milk to make 2 cups liquid; stir. Let the mixture stand for 5 minutes before using it in a recipe.

title: gingercreams(no fail cookies)
directions: Mix sugar, water, molasses, shortening and egg.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover; refrigerate 1 hour.

title: pureed garlic potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and cut in cubes.
Add water to cover in saucepan.
Add salt and garlic.
Boil and simmer 15 minutes or until tender.
Do not overcook.
Drain potatoes and garlic.
Mash or put through food mill.
Put back in saucepan.
Heat milk; add butter.
Add this to potato mixture a little at a time.
Add parsley, pepper, salt and nutmeg.
Blend well.
Keep warm until ready to serve.
(Use your judgment as to the amount of milk needed.) Yield:

title: yogurt pop
directions: Add the milk to the yogurt, then blend in the drink mix.
Stir to dissolve.
Pour into the ice tups set.
Seal and freeze.
Makes 6.

title: cutout cookies
directions: Combine flour, baking soda, cream of tartar and salt in medium bowl and set aside.
At medium speed in large mixer bowl, beat margarine, sugar and powdered sugar until blended.
Beat in egg, vanilla and food coloring.
At low speed, beat in flour mixture until well blended.
Divide dough into three portions.
Cover and chill for 1 to 2 hours until firm enough to handle.

title: brown jug soup
directions: Combine all in a large pot. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer for 1 1/2 hours. Add 2 cans cream of celery soup and 1 pound Velveeta cheese, cubed. Stir until well blended.

title: golden corn cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add milk, egg and oil.
Bake in greased 9-inch dish for 20 minutes at 425°.

title: chow chow pickle(mrs. elva tucker's recipe)
directions: Cut up vegetables, mix well with salt.
Drain overnight.
Next morning make syrup with remaining ingredients.
Boil 40 minutes, then add all other ingredients and bring to boil; boil five minutes.
Can while hot.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain green beans and pour into casserole dish.
Add cheese, soup and fried onions (save a few onions to sprinkle on top). Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Sprinkle remaining onions on top and brown for 10 minutes.
Serves hot!

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: In a saucepan, combine margarine, brown sugar and milk.
Boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Beat in confectioners sugar, peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into shallow dish and top with nuts.
Cool.
Cut into 1-inch squares.

title: baby vidalia sweet onion casserole
directions: Wash and cut zucchini and onions into 1/4-inch slices.
Place in medium sized saucepan.
Add water to cover and bring to a boil over medium-high heat.
Boil until tender; drain.
Combine remaining ingredients except cheese.
Add to zucchini-onion mixture; mix until well blended.
Pour into a greased 8-inch casserole.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: granola
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread oats in ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Heat in oven 10 minutes.
Combine coconut, sunflower seeds, wheat germ, cinnamon, banana chips and hot oats.
Add honey and oil; mix well.
Return mixture to baking pan.
Bake 15 minutes, stir.
Bake 10 minutes, stir.
Bake another 10 minutes or until brown.
Add raisins and store in airtight container.

title: chicken in crock-pot
directions: Cook low until done.
