title: light fettuccine alfredo
directions: Combine all ingredients in container of electric blender; process until smooth, stopping once to scrape down sides.
Pour into a small saucepan; cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until thoroughly heated.
Yields 2 3/4 cups.

title: punch
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large canning pot.
Add water to make about 3/4 full.
Serves 30 to 50 people.

title: forgotten torte
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Butter bottom only of tube pan.
Have whites at room temperature.
Add salt and cream of tartar.
Beat until almost stiff. Add sugar slowly, 2 tablespoons at a time, and continue to beat.
Beat in vanilla last and spread evenly in buttered pan.
Put in oven. Close door and turn off heat at once. Forget until the next morning.
Loosen edges and turn out in plate.
Frost with stiffly beaten cream. Serve with fresh sliced strawberries.

title: can't fail divinity
directions: Boil sugar, water and salt until mixture forms a hard ball in cold water.
Place marshmallow cream in mixing bowl and stir in hot syrup.
Continue stirring until slightly stiff.
Fold in nuts and vanilla.
Drop from spoon onto waxed paper.
Yield:
24 servings.

title: apple-butter cinnamon pie
directions: Combine apple butter, eggs, sugar, cornstarch, cinnamon and mace; mix well.
Add milk gradually; blend well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Top with lattice made of pastry dough.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: creme de menthe brownies
directions: Cream 1/2 cup butter; gradually add sugar and beat until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine flour and salt; add to creamed mixture alternately with chocolate syrup, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 28 minutes.
Cool completely.
Brownies will shrink from sides of pan while cooling.

title: lynn's great northern soup
directions: Mix all ingredients, except macaroni, and simmer about one and a half hours.
Shortly before serving add cooked macaroni and season to taste with salt and pepper.

title: 24 hour slaw
directions: Combine oil, vinegar, sugar, mustard and salt; bring to a boil.
Combine remaining ingredients; pour over cabbage mixture. Refrigerate for 24 hours. Yield: 24 servings.

title: peanut butter buckeyes
directions: Blend together the peanut butter, confectioners sugar and margarine until smooth. Roll into balls (chestnut size).
Chill for 1 hour.

title: children's play dough
directions: Place flour in a bowl.
Add hot water, salt, baking powder, oil and food coloring; stir thoroughly until well mixed and a dough ball is formed.
Knead ball on floured surface until smooth and workable.
Store in airtight container in the refrigerator.

title: rhubarb bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together. Beat wet ingredients. Blend dry ingredients into wet ingredients. Add rhubarb and nuts. Pour into 2 greased and floured pans and top with brown sugar and butter. Bake in preheated oven at 325° for 45-60 minutes.

title: mexican salad
directions: Mix together beans, onion, green pepper and tomato in large salad bowl.
Before serving add cheese, salsa and chips.

title: tasty lamb chops
directions: Sear chops.
Place rice in bottom of buttered casserole.
Put chops on rice layer.
Arrange orange sections over them.
Add bouillon and seasonings.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°. Serves 4.

title: pineapple fluff cake
directions: Add milk and sugar to pudding, then beat.
Add pineapple. Whip whipping cream; add to other mixture with spoon.
Slice cake and ice both layers.
Put extra hole in center of cake. Chill for 2 or 3 hours.

title: knox blox
directions: Combine Knox gelatine and Jell-O. Add boiling water and stir until dissolved.
Pour into shallow 13 x 9-inch pan.
Chill until firm.
Cut into squares for serving.

title: rhubarb pecan muffins
directions: In large bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder, soda, salt and nuts.
In another bowl, combine egg, oil, orange peel and orange juice.
Add to dry ingredients all at once.
Stir until moistened.
Stir in rhubarb.
Put in muffin pans.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: appleless pie
directions: Bring water to boil.
Add sugar, cream of tartar, Ritz crackers, margarine and cinnamon.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Pour mixture into pie crust.
Bake at 400° until crust is done or browned.

title: egg quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Crumble bread into a glass baking dish. Whip eggs.
Layer on top of bread.
Brown sausage.
Sprinkle on eggs (add mushrooms now); then sprinkle top with cheese.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes, until brown.
Serve hot.

title: mexican quiche
directions: Brush pie shells with butter.
Distribute cream cheese equally and evenly over the bottom of the pie shells.
Chill until the butter has set.
Sprinkle chiles over cream cheese in pie shells and top with shredded cheeses.
Mix together remaining ingredients until well blended.
Pour egg mixture equally into pie shells. Bake in preheated 450° oven for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and continue baking 30 minutes or until center of pie is firm. Cool 5 to 10 minutes before serving.
Each pie serves 8.

title: susan's apple cake
directions: Grease angel food pan.
Preheat oven to 375°.
In a small bowl, mix walnuts, cinnamon and 1 1/2 cups sugar.
In a large bowl, beat butter until creamy.
Add remaining sugar; beat until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, then vanilla, beating after each addition.

title: red beet eggs
directions: Drain beets, reserve liquid.
Place drained beets in 1 1/2-quart jar.
Measure reserved liquid.
If necessary, add enough water to make 1 cup.
In pan, combine beet liquid, vinegar, sugar and salt; bringing to a boil, stirring.
Pour over beets; refrigerate, tightly covered.
Cool 4 hours.

title: indian fudge
directions: In heavy skillet on medium heat, melt butter.
Stir in cream and cheese until smooth.
Stir in nuts.
Cook and stir constantly for about 15 minutes, until it becomes a thick mass with a fine consistency.
Stir in dry milk, working it into the mixture.
Cook and stir another 15 minutes (should be well thickened by now). Stir in sugar until well absorbed.
Cook and stir 5 minutes more. Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan to 1/2-inch thickness.
Smooth out; let set.
Cool to fudge consistency.
Cut into squares.
Refrigerate to store.

title: german chocolate deluxe cake
directions: Bake in three 9-inch cake pans at 350° by baking time on cake box.
Let cool.

title: broccoli and cauliflower mix
directions: Mix vinegar, Miracle Whip or mayonnaise and sugar with an electric mixer until smooth.
Cook bacon until crisp and then drain and crumble.
Add bacon to dressing.
Mix with broccoli and cauliflower, cut into bite size pieces.
Refrigerate.

title: black forest cake
directions: Mix flour and butter; add pecans.
Put in the bottom of pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Scald milk; stir in sugar, salt and margarine. Cool to lukewarm. Soften yeast in warm water. Add milk mixture, eggs and 2 cups flour; beat until smooth. Add enough remaining flour to make a soft dough. Turn dough out on a lightly floured board; knead about 8 to 10 minutes or until smooth and elastic. Place in a greased bowl, turning to grease top. Cover and let rise in a warm place until doubled in bulk (about 30 minutes). Punch down. Turn dough out on a lightly floured board. Shape into crescent, Parker House, cloverleaf, fan tan or pan rolls. Cover; let rise in a warm place until doubled in bulk (about 30 minutes). Brush with melted butter. Bake at 400° about 10 to 15 minutes. Yield: 2 1/2 to 4 dozen, depending on shape.

title: charles' pimento pinwheels
directions: Spread pimento cheese spread on tortillas.
Roll up like a jelly roll.
Wrap in waxed paper and chill in refrigerator for 4 to 5 hours or overnight.
Prior to serving, slice into 1/2-inch pieces and serve.

title: yeast rolls or bread
directions: Mix the package of yeast in 1/2 cup warm water and let set 10 minutes.
Add 1 cup warm water.
In a bowl, add salt, sugar and grease or butter to the yeast mixture.
Stir in enough flour until you get the consistency you want.
Knead the dough and place into a greased bowl.
Cover with a cloth and let rise until double.
Shape into rolls or loaves; place in greased pan and let rise.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes for rolls, 50 to 60 minutes for loaves.

title: twinkie delight
directions: Slice Twinkies in half (sponge side down, white up).
Top with pudding.
Then top with sliced strawberries with 1/2 of juice. Add Cool Whip.
Cool.
Ready to eat!

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding and milk with mixer or wire whip.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Layer in bowl:
vanilla wafers, bananas and pudding mix. Sprinkle top with crushed wafer crumbs.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve the Jell-O in hot water.

Add enough water to juices from fruit to make 1 cup if needed. Add this to the Jell-O. Add the blueberries, pineapple and pecans to Jell-O after it has set. Top with cream cheese, sugar, sour cream and vanilla. Mix and spread on top of Jell-O.
Use a long, oblong dish.

title: hawaiian pancakes
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving all juice.
Combine juice and maple syrup in a heavy saucepan.
Heat.
Make pancakes according to package directions.
Top pancakes with pineapple chunks.
Serve with warm syrup and Honey Butter.
Makes 4 servings.

title: gingerbread
directions: In small mixing bowl, beat eggs.
Add margarine, sugar and molasses.
Sift flour.
Add all dry ingredients into first mixture.
Add water last.
Line greased 9 x 13-inch pan with waxed paper.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Drizzle with Lemon Sauce. Serve hot!

title: lemon bars
directions: Cream together flour, butter and powdered sugar.
Press into 8 or 9-inch square pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Mix rest of ingredients well.
Pour over cool crust.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes longer.
Sprinkle sifted powdered sugar on top as soon as removed from oven.
Cool before cutting.

title: seafoam candy
directions: Mix water and sugar together and boil on high about 5 minutes. While mixture boils, beat egg whites in a stainless steel bowl until stiff peak forms.
Pour hot syrup mixture slowly over egg whites and beat about 5 more minutes, until candy forms soft peaks.
Dip spoonfuls onto wax paper.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Drain cooked broccoli well.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, eggs, onion, salt and pepper and broccoli.
Pour in casserole dish. Sprinkle cheese over top.
Mix butter and crumbs.
Sprinkle over cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: tempura sauce
directions: Note:
Cook shrimp shells in water and strain to make the 1 cup required.
Boil shoyu sauce, sugar and water for 3 minutes.
Cool and add the liquid to the grated daikon.

title: tostado casserole
directions: Brown meat.
Add onions.
Add taco seasoning and 1 can pizza sauce.
Simmer for a few minutes.
Mix beans and remaining can of pizza sauce.
Put 2 cups crushed corn chips on top when almost done.
Put Cheddar cheese on top of the corn chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: microwave best rice pudding
directions: In a 3-quart casserole, cook rice, raisins, butter, salt and 1 1/3 cup water, covered, on High 7 to 8 minutes, until rice is very tender and liquid is absorbed.
Refrigerate 15 minutes to cool slightly.

title: surprise salad
directions: Heat pineapple and juice until boiling.
Add Jell-O; stir until dissolved, then let cool.
Add buttermilk and Cool Whip and chill.

title: broccoli, cheese and rice casserole
directions: Saute in butter the onions, celery and mushrooms for 20 minutes, or until tender.
Add mushroom soup, Cheez Whiz and cooked rice and set aside.
Cook broccoli until slightly tender according to package directions.
Place drained broccoli in buttered casserole dish.
Pour soup and cheese sauce over broccoli.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: salmon horseradish pate(a great way to use leftover cooked salmon)
directions: In a bowl, combine salmon, shallots, dill, horseradish, mayonnaise and pepper.
Let ripen at least 4 hours in the refrigerator.
(Keep only 1 to 2 days in the refrigerator.) Spread on thinly sliced cucumber rounds.
Can also be used as a dip for raw vegetables.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Combine crushed pretzels, margarine (melted) and 3 tablespoons sugar; press into pan and bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Let cool.

title: better biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°. Sift together flour, baking powder, salt (and soda if using). Cut in shortening until fine; add milk and mix until soft dough forms. Then with floured hands, gently knead dough a few times. Press or roll out on floured surface to 3/8-inch thickness. Cut out and place on lightly greased baking sheet. Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown. Makes 12 to 16 biscuits, depending on size of your cutter.

title: christmas pickles
directions: Heat to boiling, reduce heat and cook slowly until cukes look transparent (do not overcook).
Put in jars and seal.

title: teriyaki sauce
directions: For Chicken Fondue:
Cut up chicken breasts in 1-inch cubes and soak in sauce 2 hours.
Then fondue as usual.

title: chunky applesauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large glass bowl.
Cover bowl with wax paper; cook on High 8 to 11 minutes or until apples are tender.
Stir once.
Let stand covered for 7 minutes.
Mash apples until chunky; serve warm or chilled.
Makes 5 1/2 cups.

title: baked beef stew
directions: Place all except potatoes in a pan and cover tightly. (Casserole may be used).
Bake in oven at 250°.
Quarter one cup of potatoes and add about 1 1/2 hours before done.
Serve when potatoes are done.
About halfway through cooking time, remove cover and stir, return to oven.

title: chicken (turkey) broccoli delight
directions: Simmer chicken in water until tender; drain. Bone and cut into bite-sized pieces.
Cook broccoli according to directions; drain liquid.
Melt 1 1/2 sticks margarine.
Add soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Mix thoroughly.
Melt remaining margarine.
Mix with bread crumbs.

title: slim jim chili
directions: Brown beef, onion and celery; drain thoroughly.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer, covered, for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce for poultry
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Let stand overnight, if possible.
Use for barbecuing chicken.

title: carrot bread
directions: Mix in order listed; add nuts if desired.
Bake in loaf pan at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Mix ingredients well and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake in 400° oven about 25 minutes or until mixture is set and crust is golden brown.

title: pecan pie
directions: In a large bowl, stir together the first five ingredients until well blended.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: sweetened condensed milk substitute
directions: Place all ingredients in blender and process at high speed until smooth.
Store in refrigerator until ready to use.
May be used in any recipe which requires sweetened condensed milk. Yields 1 1/4 cups.

title: baked beans
directions: Fry bacon.
Remove from skillet and drain on paper towel.
Add onions to one tablespoon bacon drippings and brown.
Add pork and beans, sugar, catsup and crumbled bacon; mix well.
Pour into casserole and bake uncovered at 300° for 1 hour.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Cut in Crisco until it resembles coarse meal.
In a separate bowl, beat together water, vinegar and egg. Add to dry ingredients and mix well.
Refrigerate, then divide into thirds.
Roll out.
Makes 3 (8 or 9-inch) crusts.

title: bean salad
directions: Bring sugar, water, salt and oil to boil.
Simmer 10 minutes and cool.
Add vinegar and dill weed.
Pour over beans and vegetables.
Refrigerate overnight.
Keeps a long time.

title: chocolate-oatmeal-peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients; stir until dissolved.
Boil 4 minutes.
In large mixing bowl, put peanut butter and vanilla. Add hot mixture to this.
Then add oatmeal; mix well.
Drop by tablespoon on wax paper.
Let chill.

title: ham croissants
directions: Unroll dinner rolls.
Cut each one in half to form a triangle. Spread a little mustard on each triangle.
Add a small amount of ham and cheese near the longest side of each triangle.
Roll up and place, seam side down, on an ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes, or until golden brown.
Serves 16.

title: no name cake
directions: Put in 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan, apple pie filling and then crushed pineapple.
Sprinkle over this the cake mix.
Add nuts, then melted margarine; spread evenly.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: graham cookies
directions: Cook eggs, sugar and butter over low heat.
Stir occasionally until thick.
Let cool!
Add remaining ingredients.
Press on waxed paper in rolls and refrigerate.
Slice into cookies.

title: peanut butter chocolate bars
directions: Beat butter, Equal and brown sugar until well combined. Stir in milk, peanut butter, egg and vanilla until blended. Gradually mix in combined flour, oats, baking soda and salt until blended. Stir in chocolate chips. Spread mixture evenly in well-sprayed 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake in preheated 350° oven 20 to 22 minutes. Cool completely in pan on wire rack. Cut into bars; store in airtight container at room temperature. Makes 48 bars.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown hamburger and onions in large skillet.
Season with salt and pepper to taste; drain grease.
Put in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Spread mushrooms on top of hamburger.
Spread corn on top of mushrooms.
Cover with potatoes.
Top with grated cheese. Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes, uncovered, until cheese is brown.
Serves 4.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all together. Pour into greased dish. Sprinkle with crushed crackers.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: mustard potato salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and chill.
You may garnish with the lettuce leaves and radishes.

title: olive cheese balls
directions: Toss cheese and flour to mix.
Pour in butter and stir with a fork to form dough.
Scoop dough by the teaspoon and mold around each olive.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Chill 1 hour. Preheat oven to 400°.
Bake 15-20 minutes.	Serve hot or at room temperature.
Yields 36 balls.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: In a large bowl, layer lettuce, cauliflower, onion and bacon. Mix together Miracle Whip, salt, pepper and sugar. Pour over vegetables; cover and let sit overnight or several hours in refrigerator. Stir just before serving.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix together ground beef, bread crumbs, milk, salt, spices and egg.
Shape into desired size of meatballs.
(Small ones are best.)
Place on a jelly roll pan or stove broiler pan and bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until done.
Remove and place in a casserole dish.

title: baked cabbage(bulgaria)
directions: Cut up the cabbage. Place peppers, tomatoes and cabbage in a large bowl, mix well, add 1/2 to 1 cup water. Place in baking dish. Bake at least 1-2 hours at 350 until cabbage is soft. Stir occasionally to make sure cabbage on to does not burn. Serve when done. Serves 4-6.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Bring shortening, milk and eggs to room temperature.
Sift flour, sugar and cocoa into large bowl.
Add margarine, Crisco and milk.
Beat until smooth and creamy.
Add baking powder and salt. Beat.
Add vanilla and eggs, one at a time, beating until smooth and creamy.
Place in greased and wax paper lined tube pan.
Bake at 325° for one hour and 30 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool.

title: chicken clarisse
directions: Place the fryer pieces into a well-greased baking dish.
Mix together all other ingredients; spread over the chicken pieces. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: dumplings
directions: Blend all dry ingredients.
Add enough milk (scant 1 cup) to moisten.
Drop by spoon on top of boiling soup.
Cook, covered, for 15 minutes.
Very good with bean or chicken soup.

title: baked brie and roasted garlic
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Remove all but one layer of skin from garlic.
Do not expose flesh.
Arrange tightly in small baking dish. Drizzle with oil.
Sprinkle with salt.
Cover with foil. Bake until garlic is tender, 75 to 90 minutes.

title: patsy's peanut butter pie
directions: Cream the cream cheese, sugar and peanut butter.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread in pie shell.
Top with Cool Whip.
Drizzle with hard topping chocolate sauce.

title: light rolls and 1 loaf bread
directions: Knead all ingredients in flour to make dough.
Grease bowl and put dough in to rise.
Work down, then rise again.
Then make into rolls or loaves.
Bake rolls at 450° for 15 minutes.
Bake bread at 375° about 50 minutes.

title: fat pat's caramel dip
directions: Melt all ingredients together, then add Eagle Brand milk. Bring to a boil; remove from heat.
May be refrigerated.
Can be rewarmed to dip fruit in.

title: ham fried rice
directions: Saute onions, bell pepper and celery.
Put ham in.
Mix with rice.
Add black pepper and soy sauce.

title: salmon mousse
directions: Mix by blender; fold in sour cream at the last.
Chill in mold until firm.
Use cucumbers, olives for eyes and garnish.

title: pizza sauce
directions: Boil tomatoes, parsley, celery seed, onions, pepper and salt together for 30 minutes, then put through strainer.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Boil
for 15 minutes.
Cold pack 15 minutes.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Fry ground beef and onion.
Add soup and water to desired consistency.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: spinach lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef, onion, green peppers and mushrooms. Once beef is browned and veggies are tender, set aside and allow flavors to settle. Boil lasagna noodles for approximately 5 minutes. Place one layer of noodles in bottom of (9 x 13 x 2) inch baking dish. Place a thin layer of sauce. Add 1/4 of meat mixture, 1/4 cottage cheese, 1/4 spinach, 1 oz. parmesan cheese, 1 oz. cheddar cheese. Spread evenly over noodles. Repeat until all ingredients are used. Last, spread Mozzeralla cheese on top. Bake in 350°F. oven for 25 minutes.

title: ham, sausage and bacon bean soup
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in slow cooker and cook on low heat overnight or bake, uncovered, at 325° for 45 minutes.
Serves 30 people. Good to freeze.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Cream butter and 1 1/4 cups sugar well.
Add eggs and mix well.
Mix together remaining dry ingredients (except sugar topping) and add alternately with milk.

title: butter cookies
directions: Cream together the oleo, sugar and eggs.
Gradually add the flour, baking soda, vanilla, salt and cream of tartar.
Chill. Roll out 1/4 inch thick and cut with cookie cutters.
Bake at 400° (350° to 375° for electric oven) for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: peach cake
directions: Drain and chop peaches.
In a large mixing bowl, combine margarine, eggs, sugar and cinnamon.
Gradually add flour and mix thoroughly.
Add peaches and mix.
Pour batter into a well-greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chicken crescents
directions: Mix bread crumbs, cream cheese, lemon juice, chicken and mushrooms.
Put 1 heaping tablespoonful in each roll.
Roll up and brush with butter.
Roll in more bread crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve with creamy chicken gravy over top.

title: green chile enchilada casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown meat in skillet sprayed with nonstick cooking spray.
Sprinkle enchilada seasoning on the meat; set aside.

title: jambalaya
directions: Cook and drain sausage.
Brown chicken in olive oil.
Add chopped green peppers and chopped onions.
Cook in large skillet or heavy Dutch oven until onions are clear.
Add sausage, rice, broth and spices.
Cook on low heat until most of liquid is absorbed.

title: french breakfast puffs(doughnuts)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix shortening, sugar, and eggs.
Sift together flour, salt, baking powder and nutmeg (if desired) and stir in alternately with milk.
Blend both mixtures together. Fill greased muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Immediately roll in melted butter, then in sugar/cinnamon mixture.
Makes 12 medium sized puffs.

title: nutty bottom pound cake
directions: Grease tube pan with generous amount of solid Crisco.
Put pecans in the bottom of pan; press firmly to bottom of pan.
(Do not flour pan.)
Set aside.
Mix butter, Crisco and sugar until creamy.
(Sift flour and baking powder.)
Add eggs and cream with sugar and butter-Crisco, then add flour alternately with buttermilk.
Mix until creamed well; add flavorings and pour or spoon batter over pecans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Turn oven off.
Let cake stay in oven for 5 minutes.
Take cake out.
Let stand in pan 10 minutes before removing from pan.
May frost with 7 Minute Frosting or serve plain.

title: four hour beef stew
directions: Cut meat into 1 1/2 inch cubes.
Place ingredients in casserole dish in order given.
Cover tightly with foil and bake 4 hours in 250° oven.

title: sarah's casserole
directions: Mix together cottage cheese, sour cream and cream cheese and set aside.

title: bread pudding
directions: Combine and mix well.
Turn into 9 x 9-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Serve with sauce.

title: spaghetti with eggs
directions: In a saucepan, heat butter on low flame.
Brown the garlic and add the spaghetti.
Stir.
Mix eggs.
Cook until firm; mix often. Serve with salad.

title: beef teriyaki(20 minutes)
directions: Heat oil and brown beef with onion.
Add ginger, pepper strips and bouillon and bring to a boil.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Cover, remove from heat and let stand 5 minutes.
Stir and serve.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash and onions with bouillon cube in lightly salted water until very tender.
Drain.
Mix other ingredients with drained squash/onions.
Bake in a 1 1/2-quart or 2-quart casserole dish at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: mom's sugar cookies
directions: Sift flour with 1 cup of sugar and next 4 ingredients, in a large bowl.
Cut in butter (use hands).
Beat eggs slightly and add rest of sugar to eggs, gradually.
Blend in buttermilk and vanilla.
Add and mix into first mix of flour.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes, or until lightly browned on the bottom.
Do not overbake.

title: baked corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Pour into buttered 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Yields 8 servings.

title: delaine king's hawaiian cake
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch pan, spread pineapple with juice on bottom. Sprinkle coconut.
Sprinkle cake mix.
Dot butter on top. Sprinkle nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: honey ham loaf
directions: Soak bread crumbs in milk.
Combine bread crumbs, ham, pork, egg, 2 tablespoons honey, cinnamon and cloves. Mix well.
Shape mixture into a loaf in a greased 2-quart shallow baking dish.

title: grandma's wafer cookies
directions: In saucepan, cook dates, pineapple, sugar, eggs and butter until thick.
Remove from heat and add nuts.
Allow to cool. Spread mixture on a vanilla wafer, top with another wafer; roll in powdered sugar.
Store in airtight container.

title: quick and easy peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil sugar and milk until a soft ball forms when dropped in cold water.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and peanut butter. Mix well.
Put in a 9-inch pie pan. Cut when cool.

title: perfect pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Heavily grease Bundt pan. With an electric mixer, beat margarine until light and fluffy.
Gradually beat in sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, along with flour.
It is important to beat well. Pour batter in prepared pan. Bake 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean.
The cake forms a crisp outside crust.

title: seaton chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream shortening, butter and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Blend in the dry ingredients.
Add chocolate chips.

title: tangy pork cutlets
directions: Put the crushed Rice Krispies in one dish. Beat egg and lemon juice in second dish.
Put the flour, salt and pepper in third dish.
Dip the cutlets into the flour mixture, then egg mixture and last the crumbs.
Dot with margarine.
Bake at 325° until done, about 1 hour.

title: my mother's garlic butter
directions: Crush garlic in margarine.
Cook 45 minutes on low to remove the water from the margarine and until the garlic is browned. Refrigerate to solidify the margarine and garlic.
Add parsley and Parmesan.
Spread onto 1-inch slices of French bread loaf. Wrap in foil and seal well.
Bake in oven at 350° to 375° for 20 minutes.
Open foil on top and roll down around sides.
Cook an additional 10 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: sweet-sour green beans
directions: Drain and rinse green beans to remove canned taste.
In a large mixing bowl, combine sugar, water, vinegar, salad oil, garlic and onions.
Add beans and mix gently.
Cover and let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Before serving, add salt and pepper to taste.

title: coconut chess pie
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients; beat well.
Stir in 1 cup coconut.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes or until set.
Cool on a wire rack.
Garnish with toasted coconut if desired.
Yields 1 (9-inch) pie.

title: quick pizza crust
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; add other ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Let rest for 15 minutes.
Divide dough in half and pat into 2 greased round pizza pans.
Add canned sauce, browned hamburger, pepperoni, green peppers, mushrooms, etc. (whatever you prefer) and top with grated Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes or until brown.

title: bean wraps
directions: Drain beans; stack in a layer a small amount of beans. Hold in your hand while wrapping bacon around beans. Hold together with toothpicks and place on cookie sheet. Bake until bacon is brown. Good with baked potato!

title: cinnamon rolls or dinner rolls
directions: In
pan,
bring milk just to boiling. Remove from heat. Add Crisco,
sugar and salt.
Let cool to lukewarm.
Add yeast to
1/2 cup
lukewarm
water and dissolve.
Slowly stir flour into Crisco,
milk
and sugar mixture.
Beat well with spoon. Stir
in yeast mixture.
Mix well.
Knead this mixture.
Place in greased bowl.
Let
rise
hours or until double in size.
Punch down.
Shape into rolls or roll out in rectangle and
spread
with melted margarine and sprinkle with cinnamon, sugar, nuts
or raisins.
Roll
up and slice.
Place in pans. Let rise until double in size, about 45 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: fried ice cream dessert
directions: Combine Rice Chex, walnuts and coconut. Put sugar and butter in small saucepan and bring to boil. Pour over cereal mixture. Put half of cereal mixture in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan and then ice cream.
Top with other half of cereal mixture.

title: beans with an attitude
directions: You will need 1 microwave container (large) and 1 frying pan (large).

title: cheese and buttered corn-on-the-cob
directions: Remove shuck of corn and set in cold water for about 1 hour. Mix Cheez Whiz, butter and salt to taste in a mixer bowl and beat with an electric mixer on medium speed until fluffy.
Set aside.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In saucepan, combine tomato sauce, onion, green pepper, broth mix, chili powder and garlic powder. Simmer for 8 to 10 minutes until vegetables are tender.
Add beef, 4 ounces cheese and rice.
Stir until cheese melts.
Turn into a 9 x 13-inch pan treated with a release agent.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake for 1/2 hour.
Allow to sit for 10 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: frozen cole slaw
directions: Shred cabbage and sprinkle with salt and let stand one hour. Drain and add green peppers and carrot.
Mix together the vinegar, sugar, water, celery seed and mustard seed.
Boil dressing ingredients together 1 minute.
Cool and add to the other ingredients.
This recipe freezes well.

title: party mix
directions: Select a dozen young tender radishes. Wash and cut off leaves. Place on a cutting board, making several slices down, without cutting all the way through.
Soak in salted ice water for 1 hour before serving.
This causes the radishes to open and resemble miniature roses.

title: hot spiced wine
directions: Cook cranberries and water until mushy, approximately 30 minutes.
Strain.
Add sugar, water, orange juice and lemon juice. Add cinnamon and heat approximately 10 minutes.
Makes approximately 5 quarts without wine.
Add 1 quart light red wine for added flavor!

title: cinnamon applesauce salad
directions: Dissolve 1 package gelatin in 1 cup boiling water.
Stir in cold water.
Pour into 6 cup mold.
Chill until set but not firm. Meanwhile, dissolve remaining gelatin in 3/4 cup boiling water. Blend in applesauce, sour cream and cinnamon.
Chill until mixture starts to thicken.
Spoon into mold on top of other mixture. Chill until firm, about 3 hours.
Unmold and garnish with salad greens.
Makes 5 cups or 10 servings.

title: hamburger, potato and onion casserole
directions: Saute hamburger.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Peel and slice potatoes.
Slice onion into rings.
In a greased medium casserole dish, alternate layers of meat and sliced potatoes, ending with potatoes.
Place onion rings on top of last layer of potatoes.
In a separate bowl, mix 1/2 cup milk and cream of chicken soup together until smooth, then pour over top of entire casserole. Cover; bake at 350° for about 1 hour, or until potatoes are tender.

title: walnut clusters
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease cookie sheets with shortening.
Sift together flour and baking powder onto piece of wax paper.
Beat together butter, sugar, egg and vanilla until fluffy, about 3 minutes.
Fold in flour mixture and melted chocolate; fold in walnuts.
Drop dough by heaping teaspoonfuls onto prepared cookie sheets.
Bake in preheated oven for 10 to 12 minutes or until firm.

title: sugar free apple pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in crust.

title: quick and easy banana bread
directions: In a large bowl, combine 1 cup of flour and sugar.
Add mashed bananas, margarine and milk.
Beat with an electric mixer on low until blended, then on high for 2 minutes.
Add eggs and remaining flour; beat until blended.
Stir in nuts (optional).
Pour into greased bread pan (8 x 4 x 2-inch).
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
(If toothpick comes out clean, it's done.)

title: minestrone soup
directions: In large pot on stove, slice sausage in olive oil.
Add onion, garlic, carrots and basil.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add zucchini, tomatoes, bouillon and cabbage and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for one hour.
Add beans, rice and wine.
Cook on low for 20 minutes.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Pour Tater Tots in greased baking dish.
Pour hamburger and onion over Tater Tots.
Mix soups together.
Pour over other ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Cook until melts.

title: pork chops with tomato soup
directions: Place pork chops in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put sliced onions on top of meat.
Add tomato soup; spread over meat and onions.
Bake at 350° for about one hour or until meat is tender.

title: "mix-easy" two egg cake
directions: (With butter, margarine or lard, use 1 cup milk minus 2 tablespoons.)

title: ice cream pie
directions: Mix and bake for 10 minutes at 350° the crushed Oreo cookies and 1/4 cup melted butter.

title: pumpkin pudding cake
directions: Beat eggs and milk together.
Add remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Pour into 9x13-inch pan and sprinkle 1 packaged yellow or white cake mix on top (sift if lumpy).
Sprinkle 1 cup chopped nuts on top of cake mix and drizzle 1-1/2 cubes of melted butter over all.
Bake at 350 degrees for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: favorite chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, flour, and cornstarch together; add egg yolks, one at a time; mixing well. Add vanilla, milk, and butter. Cook in heavy sauce pan over medium heat until thick, stirring consistently.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar thoroughly; add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add sifted dry ingredients gradually, beating well.
Add sour cream and flavoring; beat well. Grease and flour tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Do not open oven for the first hour.

title: lemon lust
directions: Combine butter and flour.
Pat into bottom of an 8 x 10-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 375°.
Let cool.
Combine 1 cup Cool Whip, powdered sugar and cream cheese.
Put on top of crust. Combine pudding and milk.
Put on top of mixture.
Spread Cool Whip on top.
Let chill.

title: pepper relish
directions: Grind peppers and onions.
Let stand in salt for at least 2 hours.
Drain.
Run water through and drain.
Boil for 5 minutes in vinegar, sugar, celery seed and mustard mixture.
Seal in jars.
Yields about 6 pints.

title: crab rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spread on sliced sour French bread, rolls or hamburger buns.
Top with sliced American or Swiss cheese and sprinkle crumbled bacon on top.
Broil 4 inches from heat until bubbly.

title: fluffy cocoa frosting
directions: Mix cocoa and sugar.
Cream part of cocoa and sugar mixture with butter.
Blend in vanilla and half of milk.
Add remaining cocoa and sugar mixture and blend well.
Add remaining milk and beat to desired spreading consistency.
Additional milk may be added, if desired. Yields frosting for two 9-inch layers.

title: punch
directions: I use lime Kool-Aid and sherbet.
Mix sugar with Kool-Aid, water and juice.
Freeze to a slush.
Then add sherbet and Seven-Up when starting to serve only.
(I freeze up ahead and thaw in refrigerator back to a slush.) Serves 50.

title: meatball stew
directions: Mix beef, oatmeal, egg, salt and pepper in mixing bowl.
Mix well.
Shape into balls.
Brown in oil over medium heat until all sides are browned.
Remove them from pan.
Add onions until tender.
Add flour to this (will be like a paste).
Slowly add water, making a gravy (will be thin).

title: spinach with cherry tomatoes
directions: Rinse tomatoes; pat dry.
Place in medium nonstick skillet. Heat, shaking skillet, over medium heat until several tomatoes pop their skins, about 5 minutes.
Combine oil, garlic and pepper in small bowl; add to tomatoes.
Toss to combine.
Layer spinach leaves over tomatoes; cover skillet and cook over medium heat until leaves are wilted but not mushy, about 3 minutes.
Stir once to combine and transfer to serving dish.
Serve warm or at room temperature.

title: baby ruth bars
directions: Bring syrup and sugar to a full boil; remove from heat immediately.
Add peanut butter and cereal.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chips together.
Spread like icing over mixture.
Cool and cut.
(Refrigerate to cool.)

title: refrigerator date pinwheels
directions: Combine
dates,
sugar	and water and cook until thick, about 10 minutes.
This will burn easily.
Add nuts and cool.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease 10 x 13-inch pan.
Spread coconut on bottom.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Mix 1 German chocolate cake mix (regular way) and spread over nuts.
Melt 1 stick of butter; add 8 ounces cream cheese; beat in box of powdered sugar.
Drizzle this mixture over cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: festive fajitas
directions: Cut chicken in thin strips.
Saute in oil for 4 minutes.
Add peppers and onions; mix together.
Cook 5 minutes or until tender. Add Velveeta cheese cubes; stir until cheese melts.
Fill tortillas with 1/4 of chicken mixture.
Top with tomatoes; fold.
Makes 4 servings.

title: oven fried potatoes
directions: Wash unpeeled potatoes and cut lengthwise into wedges.
Roll them in melted butter.
Place in single layer in baking dish. Bake in oven preheated to 375° until brown.

title: georgia apple pie filling
directions: After preparing pastry, preheat oven to 425°.
Mix sugar, flour, nutmeg, cinnamon and salt.
Stir in apples and turn into pastry lined 9-inch pie plate.
Dot with butter or margarine. Cover with top crust that has slits cut in it.
Fold upper crust over lower crust.
Seal and flute.
Cover browning.
Remove during last 15 minutes.
Bake until crust is brown and filling bubbles through slits (about 40 to 50 minutes).
Serves 8.
Has 407 calories per serving.

title: tomato-brussels sprouts salad
directions: Cook Brussels sprouts as directed on package.
Drain.
Pour dressing over Brussels sprouts, turning each until well coated. Cool.
Cover and refrigerate at least 3 hours.
Add tomatoes; toss.
Serve in lettuce cups, if desired.

title: chocolate amaretto dip for strawberries
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients; microwave on Medium or Low for 5 to 6 minutes; stir well.
Add Amaretto and mix thoroughly.
Serve with fruit (strawberries, bananas, apples and pineapple are wonderful!).

title: frozen lemon dessert
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and pour over graham cracker crust.
Put some cracker crumbs on top.
Freeze.

title: mississippi mud pie
directions: Mix like pie dough and just press it in a 9 x 13-inch pie dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook one chicken or 4 chicken breasts in enough water for 1-quart of broth, to save.
Take chicken off bones.
Cook vermicelli noodles, onion and bell pepper in broth.
Add tomatoes, mushrooms and chicken a little later.
Add peas and cheese last. Pour into greased casserole dish.

title: pasta pizza
directions: Cook noodles until tender.
Mix noodles with eggs. Spread onto cookie sheet and cook at 350° for 20 minutes (crust).

title: barbecue cheese spread
directions: Spread on half hamburger buns, bagels, muffins or bread slice. Place on baking sheet or in toaster oven (400°) for 7 minutes.

title: salmon dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and serve with your favorite crackers.

title: cheese ball appetizer
directions: Mix well and form into ball.
Chill for several hours or overnight.
Serve with raspberry or strawberry preserves on crackers.

title: old-fashioned gingersnaps
directions: Mix first four ingredients together.
Mix remaining ingredients together and add to first mixture.
If soft, chill. Roll into 1-inch balls and dip in sugar.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheets at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: baked fudge dessert
directions: Beat eggs and add all dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Stir in melted butter, pecans and vanilla.
Pour into an 11 x 7-inch metal pan and set in another pan of boiling water.
Bake in a 325° oven for 45 minutes or until set like a custard.
Do not overbake. Cool and cut into 2-inch squares.
Best if slightly warm and served with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: almond punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together except ginger ale. Chill. Add chilled ginger ale just before serving.

title: mama's french fries
directions: Wash and peel potatoes.
Slice for French fries.
Soak in cold water for an hour or more.
Drain off water; salt and pepper. Tumble potatoes with flour.
Drop few at a time in hot oil.
Cook until golden brown.
I use deep fat fryer.

title: stuffing for chicken
directions: Just mix all the ingredients and place in poultry.
Or as a side dish in the oven with poultry.
Cook at same time.

title: crackle top molasses cookies
directions: Melt shortening and pour into bowl to cool.
Sift together dry ingredients and set aside.
Stir sugar, molasses and egg (well beaten) into cooled shortening.
Add dry ingredients.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and enough of the milk to make a thick mixture; don't use too much.
Pack in loaf pan and place in refrigerator.
Slice later.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Put shortening into a cup of boiling water. When melted, add 1 cup cold water. Beat eggs well and add them to the water and shortening.
Add also the sugar, yeast dissolved in 1/2 cup water, salt and flour.
Mix all ingredients well.
Put into a greased bowl in refrigerator overnight.
Grease hands.
Make balls the size of walnuts and put 3 in each greased muffin cup.
Let rise 2 1/2 hours.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Place chicken in airtight container.
Add lemon juice, parsley flakes, salt and pepper.
Put the lid on and shake container slightly.
Refrigerate overnight.
Place in 300° oven.
Baste every 15 minutes with mixture of barbecue sauce and honey; more mixture may need to be made.
Total baking time will be 2 to 2 1/2 hours. Coating should have glazed appearance when done.
You may switch the oven from "bake" to "broil" during the last 15 to 30 minutes if coating doesn't look thick enough.
Serves 4.

title: fudge pecan pie
directions: Combine all ingredients, except pecans.
Beat ingredients for 30 seconds.
Stir in chopped nuts and pour in the pie shell. Arrange half pecan meats over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheddar mashed potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Place potatoes in a saucepan and cover with water; cover and bring to a boil over medium-high heat.
Cook for 15 to 20 minutes or until tender.
Drain and mash.
Add sour cream, butter, salt and pepper; beat until smooth and fluffy. Transfer to a greased 2-1/2 quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese, bacon and chives if desired.
Bake, uncovered for 20 minutes or until heated through and cheese is melted.
Yield:
8 to 10 servings.

title: savannah red rice
directions: Fry bacon in heavy pot until crisp. Remove. Saute onion, celery and bell pepper in bacon fat until onion is translucent. Crumble bacon; return to pot. Add rice to coat with grease. Add tomatoes. Measure reserved tomato juice and tomato sauce; add water to make 2 1/2 cups total liquid. Pour over rice and bring to boil, stirring occasionally. Lower heat to simmering. Cover pot and simmer for 20 minutes. After 20 minutes, remove from heat and let set at least 20 minutes. Do not peek. After 20 minutes, fluff with fork and serve.

title: lemon whippersnappers
directions: Grease cookie sheets.
Combine first 3 ingredients in large bowl.
Stir until well mixed.
Drop by teaspoon into powdered sugar; roll to coat.
Place 1 1/2 inches apart on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes, until light golden brown. Makes about 4 dozen cookies.
(High altitude, no adjustment necessary.)
Children and adults love the tangy flavor of these cookies and are very good in other flavors, such as strawberry, orange, chocolate, etc.

title: busy day cake (eggless)
directions: Melt shortening; cool a little.
Blend in sugar and cocoa. Sift together flour, baking soda and salt; stir into cocoa mixture alternately with buttermilk (or sour milk).

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Make ground beef into patties and line in casserole on bottom and alternate with a layer of potatoes, onions and meat.
Pour soup over casserole and 1 can water or less and salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour until done.

title: crab pate
directions: Heat soup over low heat until warm.
Remove from heat; set aside.
Dissolve gelatin in cold water.
Add this to soup; mix well.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well, using low speed of mixer.
Season to taste with salt, black pepper, red pepper and Tabasco.
Turn into 4-cup mold; chill until firm.
Serve with crackers.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix flour, salt, and baking soda.
Set aside.
Mix margarine and peanut butter.
Add both kinds of sugar.
Mix well.
Add eggs and beat.
Stir flour mixture into peanut butter mixture.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto baking sheet.
Flatten with fork.
Bake at 375 degrees for 10 to 15 minutes until light brown.
Yields 4 to 5 dozen.

title: grandma woods lemon cheese cake
directions: Mix together and then mix with Jell-O mixture.
Whip Pet milk until thick.
Add Jell-O and cream cheese mixture.
Top with remaining graham crackers.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours or overnight.

title: cadillac bar's ramos gin fizz
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender.
Serve over crushed ice in tall glass.
Serves one.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well.
Add baking powder to flour and flavorings to milk.
Add milk and flour alternately to creamed mixture, beating just enough to mix.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 325° until done, or about 1 1/2 hours.

title: santa fe chicken and rice
directions: Sprinkle chicken breasts with salt; set aside.
Cook onion and garlic in oil in electric skillet for 2 minutes.
Add chicken broth and salsa.
Bring to boil.
Stir in rice.
Arrange chicken breasts over rice.
Cover tightly and simmer 20 minutes.
Remove from heat. Let stand covered until all liquid is absorbed, about 5 minutes. Garnish with avocado if desired.
Sprinkle with tomato and cheese. Makes 6 servings.

title: mushrooms stuffed with crabmeat
directions: Dice bell peppers, onions, parsley and 1 pound mushrooms. Saute vegetables in 1/2 of butter until transparent.
In a separate pan, saute mushrooms with other 1/2 of butter until almost done.
Add to vegetables.
Add cream.
Cook approximately 5 minutes.
Add crabmeat, bread crumbs and cheese until firm.
(Add more bread crumbs slowly if necessary.)
Salt and pepper to taste. Using mushrooms with stems, cut a tiny piece of top off mushrooms to let stand.
Cut a small piece of stem off.
Wipe mushrooms (do not wash).
Let stuffing cool for 10 to 15 minutes.
Form stuffing into small ball and stuff on stem of mushroom.
Place in baking dish.
Cook 10 to 15 minutes until warm.

title: spinach lasagna
directions: Cook noodles as directed and drain.
Cook spinach as directed and drain.
Mix cottage cheese, eggs, parsley, butter, salt, pepper and garlic powder in bowl.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Place layer of noodles in dish, followed by layer of cottage cheese mixture, Monterey Jack cheese, spinach and Parmesan cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: butter pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar in bowl until fluffy.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour and milk alternately, mixing well after each addition.
Add baking powder and vanilla.
Mix well.

title: zesty macaroni salad
directions: Prepare macaroni; drain.
Toss other ingredients with macaroni. Chill and serve.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Cook carrots until tender, yet crisp.
Add 1 1/2 tablespoons butter and 1/3 cup packed brown sugar.
Heat slowly, stirring occasionally, until nicely glazed, about 15 minutes.

title: cream of cauliflower soup
directions: Cook all ingredients except cream over medium heat until cauliflower is tender.
Transfer to blender and blend until smooth, adding cream.
Serve hot.

title: low-fat spaghetti
directions: Spray skillet and brown turkey and onions.
Cook spaghetti as directed on package.
Drain.
Add turkey, onions and meat sauce. Stir well.

title: no shortening pineapple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together flour and sugar in a large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour mixture into an ungreased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes. Cool completely before icing.

title: treebeard's butter cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Mix 1 egg with dry cake mix and add butter to a moist dough consistency.
Grease a 13x9 pan. Press dough into pan.
Beat softened cream cheese, 3 eggs, and vanilla with a mixer until creamy.
Add powdered sugar gradually. Pour mixture over dough.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: sarah's crabmeat appetizers
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Do not burn!
Stir in next 5 ingredients, being careful not to overmix or break up crabmeat too much. Spread mixture generously over English muffins and bake in preheated 350° oven approximately 5 to 8 minutes.
Broil for a few seconds to brown tops.
Cut into quarters and serve.
Makes 48.

title: buttered celery
directions: Cook celery in boiling salted water until tender, about 10 minutes; drain.
Add butter and stir until melted and celery is coated.
Season to taste.

title: mandarin orange compote
directions: Combine oranges, nuts, raisins and coconut in a serving dish. Chill several hours.
Serves 2.

title: parmesan cheesebites
directions: Pulse 1st four ingredients in food processor until blended. Shape dough into 2 (4-inch) logs. Wrap in plastic wrap and place in an airtight container. Chill 8 hours. (Freeze up to 3 weeks, if desired; thaw in refrigerator overnight.)
Cut dough into 1/4-inch thick slices and place on a lightly greased baking sheet. Brush with milk. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned. Yield: 2 1/2 dozen.

title: blueberries 'n cheese squares
directions: Roll Keebler Honey Graham crackers to fine crumbs.
In 11 3/4 x 7 1/2-inch baking dish, combine crumbs and butter or margarine, mixing well.
Reserve 1/2 cup crumb mixture for topping.
Press remaining crumbs in bottom of dish.
Chill while preparing cream cheese.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix peanut butter and powdered sugar until the mixture is like meal.
Bake pie shell and cool.
When cool, put 3/4 of peanut butter mixture into pie shell and press on bottom and sides.
Save the remainder to put on top of meringue before baking.

title: hot chicken salad pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together well, except cheese and potato chips.
Put in casserole dish and top with grated cheese and crushed potato chips.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Blend brown sugar and instant coffee.
On lightly floured board, divide dough into 24 equal pieces.
Dip each piece in melted margarine; roll in brown sugar mixture.
Place 12 pieces in bottom of well-greased 10-inch tube pan.
(If pan has removable bottom, line with aluminum foil.)
Arrange second layer of 12 pieces on top of first layer.
Cover; let rise in warm place, free from draft, until doubled in bulk, about 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes, or until done.
Remove from pan.
Drizzle with frosting while warm.

title: marinated tomatoes
directions: Toss tomatoes with all other ingredients and marinate in refrigerator.
Serve over lettuce, over pork or veal cutlets, linguini with olives or garlic toast with Mozzarella cheese. Brush on fish fillets as a marinade, then serve tomatoes on the side.
Or, add onions and chili peppers and use as salsa.

title: cheesy apples
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add 1/2 pound Kraft Velveeta cheese and flour.
Pour sliced apples in 2-quart buttered casserole.
Spread mix on top of apples.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8.
Delicious with pork and ham dishes.

title: corn soup
directions: Put corn, water, salt and butter in a pot and cook until tender, about 15 to 20 minutes.
Then mix flour and milk together until smooth.
Pour into pot with corn and cook about 2 to 4 minutes.
Good with biscuits and tomatoes.

title: red potato-vegetable salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and 2/3 cup pickled beet liquid. Chill at least 4 hours or overnight.
Serve on lettuce.
Makes 6 servings.

title: grape hull pie
directions: Mix together.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake until just about set.
Beat egg whites and put on pie and brown.
You may want to add some grated coconut to mix before baking.

title: barbecue ribs
directions: Salt ribs with lemon pepper.
Cook in crock-pot for 2 hours on high, until reasonably tender.
Add no water.
Take out of crock-pot and let cool in dish.
Pour barbecue sauce on top and refrigerate for 1 hour.
Place on charcoal grill and let them brown.

title: creole crabmeat eastern shore style
directions: In large skillet, cook all
of the ingredients in olive oil, except tomatoes and crab meat for
5 minutes.
Do not let brown. Add crab meat and tomatoes,
cook
for about 30 minute or less. Serve over fluffed	rice.
Makes
a
complete
meal, served with a salad.

title: warmer kartoffel salat(variation with sour cream)
directions: Cook potatoes in salted boiling water until fork-tender; peel and slice and

add onion. In a large skillet, cook bacon and remove from heat; remove bacon and set aside. Pour off fat. Return 1/4 cup to skillet. Add flour and sugar and bring to a boil. Remove from heat and add sour cream. Add potatoes, onions and half of the bacon. Toss gently. Add rest of bacon and parsley. Serves 10.

title: honey dijon mustard dip
directions: Mix all together and store in refrigerator.
Recipe from Hills and Pines Garden Club, Raleigh, North Carolina.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Butter sides of heavy 2-quart saucepan.
In it combine granulated sugar and milk.
Stir over medium heat until sugar is dissolved and the mixture boils.
Cook to a slow boil stage (234°). Remove from heat, quickly blend in Marshmallow Creme, peanut butter, chocolate pieces and vanilla.
Pour into buttered 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Score; cut when firm.

title: gulliver's creamed corn
directions: Combine the first 7 ingredients; bring to a boil and simmer 5 minutes.
Blend the butter and 2 tablespoons flour.
Add to corn; mix well and remove from heat.
When you add everything together, it lumps into a frozen mass, but as it heats, you will be able to mix the ingredients.

title: cookie salad
directions: Mix well pudding and milk.
Fold in mandarin oranges first, then Cool Whip, then crushed cookies.
Chill well and serve.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: In a 2 1/2-quart saucepan, combine brown sugar, corn syrup, margarine, cream of tartar and salt.
Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Stirring constantly, boil rapidly to a hard boil stage (260°) or 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in baking soda quickly but thoroughly.
Pour at once over popcorn in a large roasting or baking pan.
Stir gently until all popcorn is covered. Bake at 200° for 1 hour, stirring 2 or 3 times during baking.
Turn out onto waxed paper.
Let cool completely.
Break apart.
Store in tightly covered container.
Makes 6 quarts.

title: kifles(dessert)
directions: Mix cream cheese and butter; add flour and shape into small balls.
Refrigerate one hour.
Press ball in palm of hand like a circle.
Fill with less than 1 teaspoon of pineapple preserves. Fold over and crimp with fork.
Bake at 400° to 425° for 10 minutes.
When cool or before serving, sprinkle powdered sugar on.

title: shrimp dip
directions: *Also good with crab meat.

title: beef bavarian
directions: Cut steak in small pieces.
Blend starch, garlic salt and salt. Coat meat and brown in oil.
Add onion and cook 2 to 3 minutes. Stir in beer, broth, pepper sauce and sugar.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and cover; simmer 15 minutes.
Add carrots and cook 15 minutes or until meat is tender.
Serve over rice.

title: raised doughnuts
directions: Pour yeast into lukewarm water.
Add 1 teaspoon sugar, stir and let stand 5 minutes. Scald milk and let cool.
Cream together shortening, salt and rest of sugar.
Add to this well beaten eggs, cinnamon, nutmeg, lemon and vanilla.
Add softened yeast to milk when lukewarm and blend this liquid with 3 cups sifted flour, beating until smooth.
Add creamed mix, beating well and enough more flour (4 or more sifted cups) to make soft dough.
Knead until smooth, keeping dough as soft as can be handled without sticking.
Let rise in cozy, warm place until doubled, fold down and let rise again until nearly doubled.
Roll a portion on floured board until 1/3-inch thick.
Cut with doughnut cutter. Let rise until doubled.
Fry in deep fat at 375° or drop a piece of dough in fat and it should be brown in 1 minute.
Drain on paper and when cool, shake in a bag with granulated sugar and cinnamon mixture.

title: pizza spaghetti
directions: Cook and drain spaghetti; set aside.
Cook and drain ground beef, onion and green pepper.
Mix sauces, meat and mushrooms. Layer spaghetti sauce, meat mixture and cheeses in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake until cheese bubbles, approximately 30 minutes at 350°.

title: ice cream jello
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water well in large bowl.
Cut ice cream in a about 8 pieces and stir into hot jello until melted. pour in dish and refrigerate.

title: chicken salad veronique
directions: On special occasions, this cake might be followed by a sweet dessert wine like a Tokay Aszii.
This cake may also be made with hazelnuts; simply substitute ground hazelnuts for walnuts.
Then, it is called "Magyoro Torta" in Hungary.

title: pork chops with apples
directions: Brown pork chops and onion in a large skillet coated with vegetable cooking spray (Pam).
Combine water, bouillon granules and pepper, stirring to dissolve; add to skillet.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes.
Skim off fat.
Add apple slices and cinnamon to mixture in skillet.
Cover and simmer an additional 15 minutes.
Transfer to a serving platter and serve hot.

title: mom's pie bird dutch apple pie
directions: Mix
ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Place pie crust in pie pan.
Save top.

title: vidalia onion pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Have partially baked pie shell ready, melt butter in heavy skillet and saute onions until tender. Arrange in pie crust.

title: party beans
directions: Brown the ground chuck. Spoon off the fat. Add onions and celery to meat and cook until tender. Stir in the soup, paste and catsup. Simmer for 15 minutes. Drain the green, lima and wax beans and combine with meat mixture. Do not drain the other beans, just add. Stir in brown sugar and mustard. Bake in a preheated 325° oven for 1 hour or cook in crock-pot on low all day.

title: funnel cakes
directions: In electric skillet, set control at 400° to 450° to maintain a temperature of 360° to 375°.

title: fresh fruit crisp
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine oats, brown sugar, margarine and cinnamon.
Set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients except fruit. Add fruit slices, tossing to coat.
Spoon into 8-inch square glass baking dish.
Top with oat mixture.
Bake 40 or 50 minutes or until fruit is tender.
Serves 9.

title: wedding cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add water and vanilla.
Add sifted flour; add nuts.
Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.
Roll in balls and flatten.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: sweet toast
directions: Mix egg and milk.
Set aside.
Mix sugar, salt and cinnamon. Combine the liquid and dry mixtures.
Mix well.
Lay slices of bread side by side on cookie sheet until cookie sheet is filled. Spread the prepared mixture over the bread slices, covering each well.

title: suds maker
directions: Punch a hole under the rim of the cup.
Add dish soap (1 tablespoon) and water (1/3 cup).
Place Handiwipe square over top of the cup.
Attach with a rubber band.
Push straw through hole until it touches the bottom of the cup.
Then hold the cup in two hands and blow through the straw.
Bubbles will appear in abundance!

title: 24-hour cole slaw
directions: Sprinkle sugar over grated cabbage; mix well.
Let set.

title: streusel caramel bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine flour, sugar and egg.
Cut in 1/2 cup margarine/butter until crumbly.
Stir in nuts.
Reserve 1 1/2 cups crumb mixture; press remainder firmly on bottom of greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: italian chicken
directions: Coat chicken with flour and seasoned salt mixture.
Brown in oil on both sides; set aside.
Drain oil.
Add tomato sauce, mushrooms and garlic powder; mix well.
Simmer 3 to 4 minutes. Add chicken.
Heat 4 to 5 minutes.
Sprinkle chicken with cheese; simmer until done.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Saute in oleo the celery, bell pepper and onion.
Mix together the remaining ingredients.
Boil spaghetti.
Mix all ingredients together.
Put in 13-inch pan.
Bake at 250° until bubbly.

title: tandy cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour cookie sheet.
Blend first 6 ingredients in large bowl.
Pour into cookie sheet and bake 20 minutes.
Take out of oven and spread 2 cups peanut butter on top.
Cool in refrigerator.
Melt Hershey bars and spread over cooled cake and refrigerate.

title: cheesy ham casserole
directions: Prepare noodles according to package directions.
Drain and pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
In medium skillet, saute sliced mushrooms, peppers and onion in butter or oil until soft, but not brown.
Remove from heat.
Rinse peas under hot water until slightly thawed.
Add sauteed vegetables, peas and sliced thick cubed ham to noodles.

title: barbecups
directions: Mix all ingredients and simmer.
Line muffin tins with canned biscuits.
Fill with hamburger mixture.
Sprinkle with cheese. Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 400°.

title: fried mush
directions: Cook cornmeal according to directions.
Serve like oatmeal. Refrigerate leftovers for another meal.
Slice about 1/2-inch thick and heat and brown slightly.
Use as potato substitute.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown meat, onion and chilies on medium-high in large saucepan.
Drain some fat.
Stir in the rest and bring to a boil. Simmer for 30 minutes on low.
Great for crock-pot.
Garnish individual servings with dollop of sour cream and/or grated cheese, raw onion, etc.
Great served with corn bread or tortilla chips.
Recipe may be doubled or tripled for large crowds.

title: karo nut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour into an unbaked 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 350° until done.
Pie is done when toothpick inserted comes out clean.

title: broccoli-beef stir-fry
directions: Heat 1 tablespoon butter in nonstick skillet or wok.
Add beef and stir until brown.
Add broccoli, onion and carrots.
Cook until crunchy-tender.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Add flour, milk and sugar to the margarine.
Mix well.
Put berries in 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Pour mixture over berries. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve warm or cold.

title: tiramisu("pick-me-up")
directions: Step One:
Prepare Mascarpone mixture by combining egg yolks, sugar, Espresso or coffee and cognac (brandy) into a large mixing bowl.
Beat with rotary beater for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add Mascarpone and continue to beat for another 3 to 5 minutes, until consistency is smooth.
Set aside.

title: stewed chicken
directions: Cut chicken into serving pieces.
Salt and pepper to taste and place in a large saucepan.

title: hobo stew
directions: Mix and cook until done.

title: molasses cake
directions: Mix butter and sugar.
Then add eggs.
Mix in remainder of ingredients and pour in a greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° until cake springs back when touched.

title: chicken eden isle
directions: Pepper chicken.
Wrap bacon around each piece of chicken. Layer dried beef in bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Arrange chicken on top of beef.
Mix soup, sour cream and cream cheese together.
Pour sauce over chicken; cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours.
Remove foil to brown chicken last 15 minutes. Serves 10 to 12 people.

title: delicious cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter together and add well beaten eggs. Sift flour.
Beat in the butter and egg mixture.
Mix thoroughly. Make into small balls.
Place on cookie sheet.
Press down flat with a fork and sprinkle with sugar lightly.
Bake in moderate oven about 350°.

title: lynn's cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Grease an iron skillet with cold Crisco (this makes the bread not stick to the pan); pour the batter into the skillet.
Bake slowly at about 325° to 350° until bread is very brown and crispy.
If you prefer it softer, don't brown quite as much.
These are my kid's most favorite things I cook.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, butter and cream cheese.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Add flavorings and blend.
Finally, add flavor all at once.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: turkey surprise
directions: Melt shortening. Add garlic and saute until brown.
Stir in flour. Cook until bubbly, stirring constantly. Add broth, soy sauce, cooked turkey and pepper. Cook until thickened. Serve over a bed of rice.

title: seven layered salad
directions: Place lettuce on bottom of large dish.
Layer celery, carrots, bell pepper, onion, and English peas.
Mix mayonnaise and sour cream.
Spread over layers.
Top with bacon and cheese.

title: oysters nina
directions: Make about 12 foil cups.
You can form them over the bottom of a glass.
Put 1 to 3 oysters in foil cup (depends upon how big oysters are).
Add a thin slice of sausage.
Sprinkle with about 1/2 teaspoon Worcestershire sauce and a few drops hot sauce.
Broil a few minutes until sausage is done.
Remove from broiler; top with grated Cheddar and put back under broiler until cheese is melted.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix pork and beans, onion, syrup and ketchup together in a large baking dish.
When mixed good, lay strips of bacon on top of beans. Bake, covered, in a 400° oven for 1 hour.

title: mrs. mckenzie's shortbread
directions: Let butter soften in a large bowl.
Add sugar and cream well. Sift flours and add gradually to butter/sugar mixture.
Place in 9-inch pie or shortbread pan.
Level with heel of hand (bottom and up sides).
Press with knuckles in rows all over.
Fork through dough to pan all over.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain. Combine all ingredients except crackers and margarine. Mix well. Pour into buttered baking dish. Cook 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Crumble enough crackers; mix with 3 tablespoons margarine to cover casserole.
Bake an additional 10 minutes.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and add taco mix as directed. Let simmer for 10 minutes. Put ingredients in a 13 x 9-inch pan in order given here: rice, chili beans, cheese, hamburger mixture and crushed chips. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: zucchini chicken skillet
directions: In skillet, brown chicken in shortening.
Pour off excess fat. Add soup, tomatoes and seasonings; cover.
Cook on low heat for 30 minutes.
Add zucchini and cook 15 minutes longer.

title: pickled okra
directions: Wash and drain okra.
Prick with a fork and pack in jar. Place dill, garlic and chili pepper in jars.
Boil wate rand vinegar.
Add salt.
Pour over the okra-packed jars.
Seal with lids and boil in water bath for 10 minutes.

title: spiced rhubarb soup
directions: Place rhubarb, water, cinnamon and salt in saucepan; cook 20 minutes or until soft.
Remove cinnamon.
Put rhubarb through a sieve.
Blend cornstarch with sugar; add to juice.
Stir and cook until juice begins to thicken.
Remove from heat; tint with food coloring.
Add lemon.
Cool and chill.
Serve topped with sweetened sour cream.

title: creamed meatballs
directions: Mix soup and water together; reserve 3/4 of this and mix all other ingredients together.
Make medium-sized meatballs and brown in shortening in skillet.
Pour off fat.
Add reserved soup. Cover and simmer about 15 minutes.
Stir often.

title: salsa
directions: *For mild salsa use 1 cup banana peppers and 1 cup hot peppers.

title: easy crock-pot venison
directions: Put all ingredients in crock-pot.
Cook on low for 6 to 8 hours.
Serve with rice or noodles.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix with hands; squeeze together and form into ball.
Roll ball in chopped pecans or paprika.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Let cheese and margarine soften.
Add flour, Rice Krispies and pepper.
Roll in small balls and press down with a fork.
Bake at 400° for about 12 minutes.

title: mary grace's funnel cakes
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine eggs and milk.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to the egg mixture.
Beat until smooth.
Test mixture to see if it flows easily through a funnel. If too thick, add milk.
If too thin, add flour.
Heat cooking oil to 360°.
Covering the bottom of funnel with finger, pour a generous 1/2 cup batter into funnel.
Remove finger and release batter into hot oil in a spiral shape.
Fry until golden, about 3 minutes.
Turn cake carefully; cook 1 minute more.
Drain on a paper towel.
Sprinkle with sifted confectioners sugar.
Serve hot with syrup.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: You will need Reynolds Wrap.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Line rectangular pan with foil.
Cover bottom with uncooked rice.
Pour onion soup and water over rice.
Lay chicken pieces in pan on top of rice.
Salt and pepper as desired.
Spread cream of celery soup (no water) on chicken.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients except shrimp in food processor or blender.
Fold in shrimp.
Serve with chips.

title: caramel popcorn balls
directions: In saucepan, combine butter, sugar and corn syrup. Stir well and bring to a boil over medium heat. Stir in condensed milk and simmer, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a soft ball stage (234° to 238°). Stir in vanilla.
Pour over popped corn and stir to coat.
Butter hands lightly and shape into popcorn balls, about 3 1/2-inches in diameter.
Makes about 15.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix together and press into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan graham crackers crumbs and melted oleo to make crust.
Refrigerate.
Beat 1 stick oleo, eggs, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Pour over graham crust and add remaining ingredients by layers.
Sprinkle with walnuts and garnish with cherries.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours before serving.

title: savory scalloped potatoes
directions: Make a sauce of the butter, flour and milk.
When thickened and smooth, remove from heat.
Add cheese and stir until melted. Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Add onion.
In buttered dish, layer potatoes and sauce, ending with the sauce.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350° or until cheese starts to brown.
Serves 6.

title: taco salad
directions: In a large skillet, brown meat and drain.
Add chopped pepper and onion.
Season with salt and pepper.
Brown a few minutes more.
Add chili and cumin.

title: split pea soup
directions: Rinse peas and place in large pan.
Cover with water and soak overnight.
In the morning, rinse and barely cover with additional water.
Add ham bone, celery, onions, carrot, parsley, bay leaves and pepper.
Cook over medium heat until simmering.
Reduce heat and stir occasionally until peas are smooth, about 3 hours.
(Can also be cooked in a crock pot.)
May need to add more water depending on thickness desired.
(I add milk to make it creamy.) Remove ham bone, chop any meat remaining on bone and add back to soup.
Also remove bay leaves, as they are not edible.
Garnish each dish with a sprig of fresh parsley.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Drain pickles well.
Cut into chunks and return to jar.
Layer with sugar.
Add vinegar and celery seed.
Place lid on tightly and leave jar at room temperature until sugar dissolves.
Turn upside-down every hour.
Refrigerate to have crisp pickle chunks.

title: apple, cream cheese, almond torte
directions: Important:
Divide granulated sugar into thirds.
Mix flour, 1/3 sugar and brown sugar.
Add butter in pieces and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Mix (with fingers or pastry blender) until it resembles coarse meal.
Chill briefly, then press into 9-inch spring-form pan, building up edges about 1-inch all around.

title: noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles
in a separate pan according to directions on package and drain.	Brown
meat and onion in oil in 12-inch Dutch oven.
Add soup, peas, seasonings and noodles.
Bake for 1/2 hour at medium heat (350° to 375°).

title: quick chili
directions: Brown meat and onion; add beans, water, tomato sauce, salt and chili powder.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Add extra water if needed.

title: chicken chow mein
directions: Boil chicken and cook until done.
Cube chicken when cool. Set aside.
In a medium skillet saute the butter, celery and onion.
Mix all the ingredients together and put in a 2-quart casserole dish; bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
If you want a crunchier taste, put the chow mein noodles on top of ingredients 15 minutes before recipe is done, rather than adding to the rest of the ingredients.

title: chow-chow
directions: Chop vegetables fine and toss together.
Add salt, sprinkled over mixture.
Let stand while mixing liquid.

title: potato salad with indian spices
directions: In a large saucepan, cover the potatoes with cold water.
Add salt and bring to a boil over high heat.
Add the sweet potato. Reduce heat and simmer until the potatoes are tender, about 20 minutes.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Slice cake into thin slices.
Add layers of the following into punch bowl:
1 layer of cake slices, 1 can pineapple, layer of cake, cherry pie filling, layer or cake, vanilla pudding, layer of cake and fruit cocktail.
Top with Cool Whip.
Cover with Saran Wrap and refrigerate.
(You may use and substitute any fruits you like.)

title: autumn apple salad
directions: In saucepan, combine pineapple in juice and sugar.
Bring to a boil and boil 3 minutes.
Add lemon jello.
Stir until dissolved. Add softened cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Fold in apples, celery and nuts.
Chill until firm.

title: baked creamed cabbage
directions: Shred cabbage very fine and cook 9 minutes in boiling salted water.
Drain well and place in buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Melt butter in saucepan and stir in flour and salt until smooth.
Add milk gradually; continue stirring until thickened. Pour sauce over cabbage.
Sprinkle with crumbs over top.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.

title: potato soup
directions: Cover potatoes with water. Cook until tender. Saute onions. Fry bacon crisp. Break bacon into pieces and add bacon and onion to potatoes. Mix together cream of chicken soup and evaporated milk. Add to potato mixture. Blend with mixer until smooth and creamy.

title: pumpkin blueberry muffins
directions: In a large bowl, combine flour, soda, salt, baking powder, cinnamon and allspice. Set aside.

title: peanut butter-cornflake balls
directions: Heat syrup and sugar until melted (do not boil). Add peanut butter. Stir until melted. Pour over cornflakes, slowly turning flakes until coated. Cool to touch and roll in balls. Place on wax paper.

title: strawberry angel food cake
directions: Crumble up Angel Food cake and set aside.
Mix 1 large box instant vanilla pudding mix according to directions on package. In a large dish- layer cake, then pudding, then strawberries until dish is full.
Top with Cool Whip and ref overnight.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Make sauce with butter, flour and milk. Add spices, cheese and salt. Be sure that the cheese melts. Add slightly beaten egg yolks. Cook for 5 minutes over low heat. Mix seafood with sauce. Saute mushrooms and add to seafood and sauce. Add lemon juice. Pour into a large casserole dish. Garnish with additional cheese. Bake at 450° for 15 minutes. Serves 12.

title: rave review coconut cake
directions: Blend cake mix, pudding, water, oil and eggs.
Beat on medium speed for 4 minutes.
Stir in coconut and nuts.
Pour into 3 greased and floured 9-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Cool 15 minutes.

title: applesauce and cinnamon salad
directions: Measure water, then return
to saucepan.
On medium to low heat, dissolve candies in water.
Remove from heat.
Add gelatin, applesauce, celery and nuts in order.
Pour into a mold and chill several hours.

title: doughnuts
directions: Measure and sift together flour and baking powder.
Mix all and chill for 1 hour.
Knead and roll dough.
Cut out with floured cutter and fry in hot fat about 4 minutes.
Drain on paper toweling and dust with sugar if desired.

title: white chocolate cookies
directions: Put chocolate and peanut butter in large pan and melt for 20 minutes. Add cereal, marshmallows and peanuts. Drop by tablespoon on wax paper and cool. Make 100 cookies.

title: turtle brownies
directions: Mix 1/3 cup of milk, cake mix and margarine in a bowl.
Press 1/2 of the cake mixture in a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 8 minutes at 350°.
