Melt caramels with 1/3 cup of the milk over low heat, stirring frequently.
When the cake is done, sprinkle 1 cup of the walnuts and 1/2 cup of the chips over crust; top with caramel mixture.
Top with teaspoonfuls of remaining cake mixture. Press gently into caramel mixture.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/2 cup walnuts and 1/2 cup chips.
Bake 18 minutes at 350°.
Cool and cut into bars.
Makes 24.

title: jam cake
directions: Sift all dry ingredients, except soda.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well each time.
Add jam or jelly and part of the dry ingredients.
Mix nuts and dates with rest of the dry ingredients.
Stir soda into buttermilk and add alternately with dry ingredients.
Add vanilla.
Beat well.
Bake layers about 30 minutes or loaf cake about 1 hour to 1 1/2 hours.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix peanut butter, sugar and butter well.
Roll into small balls and chill for 20 minutes.
While this chills, steam together the chocolate chips and paraffin in double boiler.
Dip balls into chocolate mixture using toothpicks.
Lay on wax paper until firm.
Makes about 100.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix cake and bake as directed on the box.

title: butter dips
directions: Stir all ingredients except oleo together until well blended. Knead 8 to 10 times.
Pat out 1/2-inch thick or 9 x 9-inch square. With floured knife, cut in strips or squares.
Dip each side in melted butter.
Place in metal baking pan or on sheet and bake until golden brown.
Serve hot.
(If using self-rising flour, use 1 1/4 cups flour and milk or water.)
Bake 15 to 10 minutes at 450°.

title: chocolate oatmeal drops
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix sugar, margarine, shortening, water, egg and vanilla.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop by rounded teaspoonful about 1 inch apart onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until almost no indentation remains when touched, 10 to 12 minutes.
Immediately remove from cookie sheet.
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: quick butterscotch cookies
directions: Dissolve the soda in hot water.
Cream sugar and butter thoroughly. Add eggs and soda mixtures, beating until smooth.
Add flour and nuts.
Mix well.
Drop teaspoonfuls of dough 2-inches apart onto lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes. Yields 6 dozen.

title: easy red velvet cake
directions: In a mixing bowl combine contents of cake mix and baking soda. Add eggs, buttermilk, food coloring and vanilla; blend on low until moistened.

Beat on high speed for 2 min. Pour into two greased and floured 9 inch round cake pans. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean. Cool for 10 minutes, remove from pans to a wire rack to cool completely.

title: curried pecans
directions: In a heavy 10-inch skillet over medium heat, stir together oil, salt and garlic powder.
Add pecans.
Cook and stir constantly for 8 to 10 minutes, or until toasted.
Remove from heat.
Sprinkle curry over pecans and stir to mix well.
Serve at room temperature.
Store in an airtight container in a cool place.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs.
Mix well.
Add other ingredients.
Blend together.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: coffee punch
directions: Prepare coffee using 3/4 cup coffee and 2 quarts water. Combine coffee, 2 cups coffee ice cream, 1 cup vanilla ice crem, Kahlua, brandy and sugar in large mixing bowl.
Beat at medium speed until smooth.
Pour into punch bowl.
Scoop 2 cups coffee ice cream and vanilla ice cream into coffee mixture.
Combine whipping cream and powdered sugar; beat at medium speed until soft peaks form.
Dollop over coffee mixture and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Yields 3 1/2 quarts.

title: venison burgers
directions: Mix well all seasonings and the ground venison.
Form into patties and cook on gas grill or charcoal grill.
Wonderful and fat-free.

title: never fail peanut butter candy
directions: Add and mix well the graham cracker crumbs, powdered sugar and peanut butter.
Spread mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan, then melt your chocolate chips and put on top.
Let cool.
Cut and serve.

title: bread pudding
directions: Combine bread cubes and raisins in buttered casserole.
Scald milk in saucepan.
In separate bowl, combine eggs, sugar, vanilla, butter and salt.
Mix this and milk together.
Mix well and pour over bread cubes. Set casserole in pan and pour hot water in pan around casserole, about 1-inch deep of water.
Bake
at 325° about 1 hour or until butter knife inserted comes out clean.
Serve with Rum Sauce.

title: chickette
directions: Cook spaghetti and add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 12 servings.

title: caramel oatmeal cake
directions: Mix shortening, brown sugar and white sugar.
Beat 2 eggs in. Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Steam broccoli, drain and mash.
Saute onion in margarine. Add flour, milk, chicken broth and broccoli.
Bring to a boil. Add grated cheese and nutmeg.
Makes 6 servings.

title: hot rolls
directions: Mix all together good; then add flour and knead well, until bread is not sticky.
Brush with shortening and cover.
Let rise in a warm place until double in bulk, about 1 hour or more. Grease pan and put your hot rolls in a size of your choice.
Let rise until double or real high.
Bake at 325° for about 45 minutes.
Brush tops with butter and serve.

title: pasta primavera
directions: Cook cheeses, milk and seasonings while you are cooking your choice of pasta.
Steam vegetables of your choice (you may use frozen if fresh is not available).
If you use fresh, it is best to cut them up before starting the cooking process.
Mix sauce with cooked pasta.
Put on plate and then top with steamed vegetables. Serve at once.

title: banana pudding(quick and easy - so good)
directions: Combine pudding mix and milk according to the package directions.
Stir in the Eagle Brand Sweetened Condensed Milk and then fold in the Cool Whip.
Layer with bananas and wafers.

title: fruit fluff pie
directions: Blend the Cool Whip and cream cheese on low with mixer, then fold in the pineapple and cherry pie filling.
Pour mixture into graham cracker crust.
Chill for about 1 hour before serving.

title: white fruit cake - "big mama"
directions: Cream the butter.
Add sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Beat well.
Add juice, flour and baking powder.
Dredge fruit and nuts with flour and add.
Bake in slow oven 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Decorate top when cake is half done.

title: party salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add fruit juice.
Chop fruit and nuts into a mixing bowl.
Add crushed pineapple to jello mixture and semi-congeal with a lump of ice.
Mix cream cheese with mayonnaise to a smooth paste.
Add mayonnaise mixture to jello and stir well.
Oil salad molds with salad oil and line with whole grapes.
Whip cream and fold into the salad mixture.
Fill molds and congeal.
Serves 8.

title: easy dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients until blended and smooth.
Chill a few hours or overnight.
Delicious with vegetables or crackers.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Chop cabbage, peppers and onions together.
Add sugar.
Mix oil, vinegar, celery seed, mustard and salt.
Bring to a boil. Pour over cabbage mixture.
Seal in airtight container.
Do not stir or uncover for at least 4 hours.
This coleslaw will keep in refrigerator a week or more.

title: joannie's simple sausage subs
directions: Boil sausages to remove excess grease.
Cut cooled sausages into wafer-like slices.
Fry peppers, onions, mushrooms, garlic and salt and pepper in frying pan with oil.
Add sausage and jar of spaghetti sauce and simmer for 1/2 hour to 1 hour.
Serve on Italian rolls.

title: chocolate praline cake
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients together in a saucepan on the top of the stove.
Cook on low until the sugar is dissolved.
Take off burner and pour into buttered cake pans (2) 8-inch round.
Add pecans to top of mixture in pan.
Preheat oven to 325°.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet, stirring until crumbly; drain. Add taco seasoning; mix well.
Combine lettuce, tomatoes and onion in salad bowl.
Top with ground beef mixture.
Drizzle with salad dressing.
Sprinkle with cheese and nacho chips.
Yields 6 servings.

title: baked chicken
directions: You may use more chicken.

title: banana muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
In another bowl, mix oleo, egg and banana; add dry ingredients.
Stir until just moist.
Fill greased muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Makes 18 muffins.

title: lazy day salad
directions: Stir fruits and puddings together.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Chill for 2 hours before serving.
Will keep a week in refrigerator.

title: macaroni 'n beef
directions: In skillet, brown beef and cook onion with oregano.
Stir to separate meat.
Pour off fat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat; stir often.
Makes about 5 cups.

title: sweet pickles from dills
directions: Drain juice of dill pickles and pour boiling water over them and let cool.
Slice pickles, either across or the long way and cover with the following syrup:
Boil sugar, water and vinegar. Pour over pickles.
Refrigerate until ready to eat (3 or 4 days). If you wish, you can add pickling spices tied in cheesecloth to the syrup when bringing to a boil.
These are delicious.

title: pastel divinity
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and water until sugar is dissolved. Bring to a boil and cook to hard ball stage at 250°.

title: spinach with artichokes
directions: Cook spinach according to directions only until completely thawed, drain thoroughly.
Have cream cheese at room temperature, soften cheese well, then blend in melted butter until smooth.
Add lemon juice and combine with spinach.
Stir in all seasonings, blend well and check seasonings.
Place artichoke hearts, pointed ends up, in large ovenproof baking dish (16 x 8-inches).
Spoon spinach over artichokes, cover with foil.
Punch a few holes in the foil and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yields 15 servings.

title: sugar-free lime congealed salad
directions: Mash cream cheese and blend in pineapple.
Add nuts. Dissolve Jello in boiling water.
When cool, mix with cream cheese, pineapple, and nuts mixture.
Pour into bowl and chill until set.

title: fruity medley
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Chill about 1 hour. Makes 12 servings.

title: chicken and artichoke hearts
directions: Flatten chicken cutlets and slice into quarters.
Flour chicken and place on plate.
Heat skillet.
Add 2 teaspoons margarine and start cooking chicken on both sides.
Chicken will turn golden.
Remove chicken when done and repeat until all chicken is cooked.
Add 2 teaspoons margarine each time you place chicken in skillet.
When all chicken is done, return all to skillet.
Add 2 teaspoons margarine, artichoke hearts and juice of 2 lemons.
Cover and simmer on low flame for 20 minutes.
Serve with rice.

title: baked beans and hamburger("one of les' favorites")
directions: Fry ground beef and chopped onion until medium brown.
Drain off fat.
Mix all ingredients in a baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Recipe may be doubled for a large group.
Cooking time remains the same.

title: carols chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.

title: sweet picante salsa
directions: Cut and peel tomatoes; cook down until thick, about 2 hours. Simmer.
Chop pears, apples, onions, green peppers and celery and add to thickened tomatoes; boil down about 20 minutes.
Add sugar, salt, vinegar and spices and simmer until thickened, usually 3 to 4 hours.
Yields 1 gallon (approximately).
May be put into 1 container and refrigerated or packed in canning jars with hot lids.

title: pfeffernuesse cookies
directions: Heat honey into a 4-quart saucepan until thin and hot (do not boil).
Stir in butter; cool to lukewarm.
Beat egg into honey mixture.
Sift flour with salt, baking powder, baking soda, nutmeg, allspice, cardamon and pepper.
Blend in crushed anise seed.
Stir into honey mixture.
(Dough will be sticky.) Refrigerate 30 minutes to 1 hour or until dough is easy to handle. Shape into 3/4-inch balls.
Put on lightly greased cookie sheets. Bake at 350° for 13 to 15 minutes.
Cool on a rack.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix beans, soup and salt.
Bake for 15 minutes at 359°. Top with onion rings and bake 10 minutes more.
Serve hot.

title: orange salad
directions: Combine Cool Whip and cream cheese; mix well.
Add dry jello and drained fruit.
Mix well.
Chill 4 hours.
Serve as an accompaniment to ham, turkey, etc., or can be served as a dessert.

title: tuna macaroni salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill salad for several hours to blend flavors.

title: shrimp roll
directions: This is an appetizer or snack.

title: german potato salad
directions: Peel and slice cool boiled potatoes.
Fry bacon crisp and crumble.
Cook bacon fat and chopped onion.
Add flour, sugar, salt and pepper.
Stir in vinegar and water and boil 1 minute.
Add bacon to sauce.
Pour over sliced potatoes.
Garnish with parsley and pimentos.
Serves 8.

title: hall's chicken salsa
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Stir-fry chicken chunks in large frying pan with 2 tablespoons olive oil.
After 2 minutes, add mushrooms and fry 2 more minutes.
Add soup, sour cream and salsa.
Blend.
Place mixture in casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, 30 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese on last 5 minutes to melt.
Garnish top with black olives and chopped scallions.
Serve over steamed rice or cooked noodles. Serves 4 to 6.

title: old fashioned a & p bar cake
directions: Simmer water and raisins in a medium saucepan for 10 minutes. Add shortening; let cool.
In a large bowl, sift together sugar, baking soda, flour, spices and salt. Stir in nuts, if desired. Add cooled raisin mixture; blend well.
Pour batter in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 35 minutes.
Let cool completely. Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting, if desired.
Serves 20 to 24.

title: swedish fruit soup
directions: Soak dried apricots, prunes and raisins in cold water for 30 minutes. Add cinnamon stick, lemon slices, tapioca and sugar. Bring to a boil. Cover and simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally. Stir in orange, apple and pear cubes. Simmer until apple pieces are tender, about 5 minutes. Stir in the booze.
Pour into large serving bowl and cool to room temperature. Remove cinnamon stick. Cover and chill until serving.
Makes about 6 servings.
Choice of fruits can depend on preference and availability.

title: soft custard
directions: Scald milk.
Pour over egg mixture.
Cook in double boiler until mixture coats spoon.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix and pour into graham cracker crust.
Sprinkle nuts on top. Makes 2 pies.

title: cranberry cream pie
directions: In a chilled bowl, combine heavy cream, vanilla and spices. Beat until soft peaks form. Gradually add marmalade, beating until stiff. Fold in cranraspberry sauce. Spoon mix into pie shell. Freeze until firm, about 6 hours or overnight. Thaw to serve.

title: angel food delight cake
directions: Mix condensed milk, lemon juice and drained pineapple and set aside.
Slice angel food cake into 3 layers.
Spread pineapple mixture between layers as you stack the layers.
Ice the cake with whipped topping.

title: mini garlic bread
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine butter, dill weed, garlic powder and Italian seasoning, stirring well to blend.
Spread on cut sides of each roll.
Place on baking sheet; broil until brown.

title: tomato custard
directions: Stew tomatoes
in
own juice (no water) and run through sieve. Cool
and
add
eggs, milk and seasoning. Bake in buttered custard cups.
Makes 6 servings.

title: spoon corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients with spoon. Cook in hot oil. Goes good with fish.

title: green beans
directions: Cut bacon into 3 pieces; place in a heavy boiler and cook until almost done and
drain.
If you use ham cook the ham for about 10 minutes in the water before adding the beans; do not drain.
Add fresh snapped beans, 1/4 teaspoon salt, and sugar; cover with water.
Cover and bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer about 10 minutes.
Taste liquid to see if you need more salt, if you do add it now with a light hand.
If they are to salty add an irish potato that has been peeled and cut into large cubes; the potato will soak up any extra salt.
Continue cooking until beans are done.
Add warm water as needed to keep beans just covered.

title: saucy turnips
directions: Wash turnip greens and roots; cut in half.
Combine greens, roots, water and salt in a large Dutch oven; bring to a boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer 1 hour or until greens and roots are tender.
Drain greens, reserving 1 cup liquid.
Set aside.
Cook bacon in a skillet until crisp; remove bacon, reserving drippings in skillet.
Crumble bacon and set aside.
Saute onions in drippings.
Add to greens.
Dissolve flour and sugar in vinegar; stir in the reserved cooking liquid.
Add mixture to greens, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Stir in the bacon.
Yields 6 servings.

title: yummy porcupine meatballs
directions: Mix 1/4 cup soup with beef, rice, egg, onion, parsley and salt.
Shape into 1 1/2-inch balls (about 16).
Brown meatballs and garlic in shortening in skillet; blend in remaining soup and water.
Cover; simmer 40 minutes or until rice is tender.
Stir often.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cinnamon baked yams
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In cup, combine brown sugar with cinnamon and salt.
Slice yams lengthwise 1/4-inch thick and place a layer in a greased shallow casserole. Sprinkle lightly with some sugar mixture and spoon on some melted butter.
Repeat until yams and sugar mixture are used.
Bake 25 minutes or until yams are hot and sugar is bubbly.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: crisp sheet bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water and let stand for 5 minutes.
Add honey, rosemary and 1 tablespoon of oil.
Sift in half the flour and salt and stir well.
Knead in remaining flour.
Pour 2 tablespoons of oil on a 9 x 13-inch cookie sheet.
Press dough into an even layer on the pan.
Pour remaining 4 tablespoons of oil over the dough and sprinkle with coarse salt.
Bake 25 minutes at 400°.

title: broccoli sauce
directions: Combine butter or margarine, flour and milk.
Stir continuously while simmering for 3 minutes.
Do not overheat.
Add salt, horseradish, prepared mustard and mayonnaise.
Blend well. Serve over cooked broccoli.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: In saucepan, melt margarine and peanut butter.
Add vanilla; turn off heat and add powdered sugar.
Put mixture
on platter; smooth out.
Cut into pieces.
Chill and refrigerate for 15 minutes.

title: easy bake chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.

Place chicken in an 11 x 9-inch baking dish. Add sauce, stirring to coat chicken. Cover tightly and bake 35 to 40 minutes. Remove chicken from oven. Add rice to casserole. Let stand 5 minutes or until rice is tender.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli; drain. Layer broccoli and chicken in long baking dish.
Combine next 5 ingredients and pour over chicken and broccoli.
Mix crumbs and melted butter; sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: zippy tuna salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 2 tablespoons of juice. Combine pineapple, tuna, eggs, celery and onion. In a small bowl, combine mayonnaise, mustard, seasonings and reserved pineapple juice. Add to tuna mixture; mix well. Chill. Add pecans just before serving. Yield: 3 cups.

title: chocolate coconut balls
directions: Mix together and form balls.
Refrigerate for 60 minutes before dipping.
Melt together 12 ounce package chocolate chips and 1 block paraffin or use 1 package of Brock chocolate in double boiler.

title: amaretto hot fruit compote
directions: Drain fruits, reserving syrup for other uses.
Combine canned fruits in large bowl; set aside.
Combine bananas and lemon juice and toss gently.
Add to fruit mixture.
Layer half each of fruit mixture and macaroon crumbs in a 2 1/2-quart baking dish; sprinkle with 3 tablespoons of the nuts and dot with 2 tablespoons butter. Repeat procedure.
Pour Amaretto evenly over fruit mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes; sprinkle with remaining almonds.
Stir before serving.
Yield:
12 to 14 servings.

title: banana buttermilk dessert
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate for 3 to 4 hours.
Add one 12 ounce Cool Whip and mix well.
Refrigerate until ready to use. This freezes well and can be made in advance.
Delicious!!

title: broccoli au gratin
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on package; drain.
Bring soup to boil; add broccoli.
Place in casserole.
Sprinkle with crumbs and cheese.
Serve hot.
Serves 6.

title: sweet, juicy bread
directions: First make 4 pieces of each slice of bread.
In a skillet, fry the bread pieces in butter until pinkish.
In another skillet, heat water and sugar.
Let the water boil with sugar until it becomes a thick syrup.
Add the fried pieces of bread to the syrup.
Keep in syrup for 2 hours.
Now they are ready to eat.

title: mystery vegetable dip
directions: Mix the 5 ingredients.
Chill and serve with vegetable sticks, potato chips or on tomato slices or wedges, broccoli or cauliflower.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Brown ground beef in large skillet.
Drain fat.
Add thawed spinach and cheese.
Cook shells and soak in cold water.
Stuff shells with beef mixture and place in baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Top with spaghetti sauce, if desired.
Very tasty!

title: yellow punch
directions: Mix all together and freeze to a slush.

title: cracklin' corn bread
directions: Sift together corn meal, flour, baking powder and salt.
In another bowl, combine beaten egg, milk and the cracklins.
Combine with dry ingredients and beat well.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake in 425° oven until done.
Should be brown.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown meat slowly; spoon off excess fat.
Add next seven ingredients to meat.
Simmer, uncovered, until thick (45 to 60 minutes), stirring occasionally.
Cook lasagne wide noodles in boiling salted water until tender.
Drain and rinse in cold water. Combine cottage cheese with next 5 ingredients.

title: cholesterol-free brown beans
directions: Cook beans in water according to package, adding the remaining ingredients.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients, then fold in Cool Whip.
Chill.

title: apricot jello
directions: Put in mold and let set until firm.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli; blend broccoli and Cheez Whiz, rice and soup together.
Place in baking dish.
In another pan, melt butter and mix with cracker crumbs and scatter on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until it bubbles.

title: rhubarb bars
directions: Beat together sugar, shortening, eggs and vanilla.
Sift together flour, soda and salt and add to first ingredients.
Add rhubarb, chips and nuts.
Mix and spread in a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350° or until it leaves the side of pan.
To keep crisp, do not cover.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Bring a pot of water to a boil.
Add salt and Mrs. Dash.
Add chicken and some onion.
Cook approx. 30 - 45 mins. (until tender) Remove chicken and add remaining ingredients to water and cook until pasta is to your liking.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Mix first 10 ingredients together.
Make balls.
Brown in 1/2 cup vegetable oil.
Remove meatballs and keep oil.
Mix flour, paprika, salt and black pepper.
Add sour cream.
Add this mix to oil.
Return balls to gravy and cook in oven 15 to 20 minutes.

title: swiss and ham sandwich
directions: Mix well together margarine, mustard, poppy seed and onion. Spread on both sides of rolls.
Place ham and cheese slices on each roll.
Wrap individually in foil.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: sugar drop cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Empty cookie mix into large bowl and break up lumps.
Add butter, eggs and water.
Stir with spoon until blended.
Drop round tablespoonfuls of dough 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until golden brown at edge.

title: ham tetrazzini
directions: In saucepan, brown ham and onion in butter until onion is tender.
Blend in soup, water, cheese and sherry (if used).
Cook over low heat until cheese melts, stirring often.
Add spaghetti (cooked and drained), chopped pimiento and parsley.
Heat.
Serves 4.

title: strawberry chiffon pie
directions: In large bowl, dissolve jello in water.
Add Fluff and dissolve.
Mix in strawberries and juice.
Refrigerate until mixture begins to harden.
Beat mixture until it is light and fluffy.

title: sausage and rice
directions: Brown sausage in a large skillet.
Drain.
Add green pepper, onion and half of celery and saute.
Combine soup mix and boiling water in large saucepan.
Stir in rice.
Cover and simmer until rice is tender.
Add sausage mixture, salt and pepper and stir well.
Pour into a greased baking dish, 12 x 8 x 2-inch.
Sprinkle remaining celery over top and drizzle melted butter over this. Bake at 375° until brown.
May be refrigerated.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown beef with onion.
Drain grease.
Add the remaining ingredients (except Ricotta, Mozzarella and American cheeses), then cook 1 hour over medium-low heat.
Stir Ricotta cheese into mixture.

title: barbecued green beans
directions: Brown bacon and onion in skillet. Add catsup and brown sugar; mix well. Place green beans in baking dish. Pour bacon mixture over green beans. Bake at 250° for 3 hours. Yield: 8 servings.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix cake mix, pudding mix and seed.
Add water and oil and beat well.
Add eggs one at a time.
Pour into well-greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake for 45 to 60 minutes before removing from pan.

title: sausage, egg, cheese breakfast casserole
directions: Place croutons on bottom of a 9 x 12-inch greased baking pan. (Can use sliced bread or other bread.)
Top with cheese.
Add sausage.
Beat eggs, milk and mustard in bowl.
Add mushrooms and soup.
Pour mixture over ingredients
in pan.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Let set 5 minutes before serving.

title: easy cracker jacks
directions: Boil first 3 ingredients on medium-high heat for 5 minutes. Then add baking soda.
Mix in well.
Pour over popcorn.
Bake at 225° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: mexican beefy noodles
directions: Brown hamburger in margarine.
Add chopped green pepper and cook 5 minutes.
Add tomato soup, milk, cooked noodles, corn, olives and 1/2 cup grated cheese.
Put in shallow baking dish. Sprinkle 1/2 cup cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Serves 4.

title: classic cream pound cake
directions: Do not preheat oven.
Grease and flour a 10-inch tube pan. Cream butter and sugar with electric mixer in a large mixing bowl until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Blend in vanilla.
Sift flour and salt together.
Add to creamed mixture alternating with heavy cream, beginning and ending with flour.
Spoon batter into prepared pan. Place in cold oven.
Turn oven to 325°.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool in pan 10 minutes; turn out on a wire rack and cool completely.
Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: applesauce fruitcake
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease 10-inch tube pan.
Line bottom with wax paper and grease again.
In large bowl, beat sugar and shortening until light and fluffy.
Add eggs; blend well.
Reserve 1/2 cup flour.
Add remaining 2 3/4 cups flour, soda and spices to egg mixture.
Blend on low speed until moistened.
Beat 2 minutes on medium speed.
Combine reserved flour, nuts, raisins and dates until lightly coated.
By hand, stir fruit and nut mixture and applesauce into batter.
Mix well.
Pour batter into greased and lined tube pan.
Top with cherry and pecan halves.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 to 1 3/4 hours or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan upright 5 minutes.
Remove from pan and remove wax paper.
Turn upright and cool completely on wire rack.
Wrap in foil or plastic to keep moist.
Store in refrigerator.
Serves 20.

title: ham ball
directions: Mix ingredients except for pecans.
Shape into ball.
Roll in chopped pecans.

title: mint tea
directions: Steep the first 3 ingredients for 5 minutes.
Add the next 3 ingredients.
After sugar has dissolved, strain all of the ingredients into 1 large container and add 1 quart of cold water. Refrigerate overnight.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: dump cake
directions: Mix all together, pour into 9 x 12-inch greased and lightly floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve with Cool Whip or frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: chocolate chip squares
directions: Mix dry ingredients together, then add the milk and mix well. Prepare 8 x 8-inch pan by greasing well, then line the bottom of the pan with aluminum foil or waxed paper.
Grease again.
Pour mixture into prepared pan.
Bake for 35 to 45 minutes at 350°. Let cool for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: zucchini or banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together eggs, oil, vanilla, zucchini or bananas.
Sift together flour, cinnamon, salt, baking soda and baking powder.
Mix all ingredients together and bake in 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake for 45 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: holiday salad
directions: Blend pineapple, cottage cheese and Cool Whip.
Fold in marshmallows, jello and pecans.

title: chicken or turkey divan
directions: Mix soups, mayo and lemon juice.
Pour over chicken and beans. Top with cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours. Makes 6 servings.

title: pineapple delight
directions: Place 3/4 of crumbs in greased casserole.
Beat oleo and sugar until smooth.
Add eggs and beat until creamy.
Pour mixture over wafer crumbs.
Fold pineapple and marshmallows into Cool Whip. Pour over oleo mixture.
Top with rest of wafer crumbs. Refrigerate until firm, overnight, if possible.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: fluffy apricot salad
directions: Combine crushed pineapple (do not drain) and jello in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Cook for 2 1/2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Cool.
In a large mixing bowl, combine the mixture, cottage cheese, peaches (drained and cut into small pieces) and the Cool Whip.
Refrigerate until firm.
Can add nuts, if desired.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pound chicken breasts to 1/4-inch thickness.
Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam cooking spray.
Dip each breast in milk, then coat with bread crumbs.
Place in pan.
Repeat until all breasts are coated.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Pull chicken from oven.
Take marinara sauce (your favorite brand), spoon over all 4 chicken breasts, top with Parmesan cheese and bake 10 additional minutes.

title: eclair dessert
directions: In 9x13 pan put one layer of graham crackers.
Mix pudding, milk and Cool Whip with electric mixer and put 1/2 of this mixture on first graham cracker layer.
Put another (second) layer of graham crackers, then the rest of pudding mixture on top.
Put last (third) layer of graham crackers on top.
Put chocolate frosting in microwave for 1/2 minute.
Stir and pour on top of last graham cracker layer.
Cover with foil and put in refrigerator overnight.

title: banana cake
directions: Combine melted margarine and graham cracker crumbs.
Press on bottom and sides of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat sugar, eggs and butter for 15 minutes.
Pour into pan.
In layers, add bananas, pineapple, Cool Whip, pecans and cherries.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: spicy apple dumplings
directions: Sift together the flour and salt.
With pastry blender, cut in the shortening until it looks like corn meal. Add the 5 tablespoons of water and mix until dough clings together. Round into a ball and let stand a few minutes.
Roll dough 1/2-inch thick on floured board. Cut in 7-inch squares.
Pare and core the apples.
Place apple on each square. Fill apples with mixture of 1/2 cup sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon.
Dot with butter. Moisten points of dough; bring opposite points up over the apple overlapping them and seal.

title: gingerbread
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and eggs.

title: easy french dressing
directions: Beat 15 minutes in a blender.

title: buttermilk pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients, pour into uncooked deep pie crust. Bake 45 minutes at 325°. Double recipe for 3 pies.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients and boil 2 minutes.
Take off heat.
Add soda and vanilla.
Pour over popcorn.
Put in brown paper bag.
Cook in microwave for 1 1/2 minutes on High, then shake well.
Put back in microwave for another 1 1/2 minutes. Take out of bag and separate to cool.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake in 3 layers and cool.
Crumble 1 layer of cake in bottom of punch bowl.
Layer strawberries, starting around edge, pudding mix (prepare according to package directions and let stand 10 minutes before using) and Cool Whip.
Repeat twice more.
Bowl will be full; refrigerate.

title: cranberry chutney
directions: Simmer first 9 ingredients 5 minutes.
Add fruit, dates and brown sugar.
Continue to simmer 15 to 20 minutes more.
Berries will "pop" and mixture will thicken.
Cool; store in refrigerator. Serve warm or chilled as an accompaniment to turkey, ham or beef. Keeps well in refrigerator.
Makes 3 1/2 cups.

title: baked brie
directions: Roll out 1 flat of pastry very thin.
Place Brie in center. Spread preserves on top.
Wrap dough around Brie.
Pinch edges to seal.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes and check.
If needed for browning, bake 10 more minutes.

title: simple apple cake
directions: Place in plastic bag, shaking apples in the mixture until they are well coated. Set aside.

title: rice pudding with caramel sauce
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
No cooking is required beyond the initial cooking of the rice.
Pour in a serving bowl or serving dishes.
Serve with the following Caramel Sauce.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix sugar and Wesson oil in bowl.
Beat.
Add flour and 1 egg at a time.
Mix cinnamon and soda.
Fold in carrots with a spoon. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Put in baking dish and cook at 325° until bubbly.
Serve with Waverly crackers.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Put crumbled saltines in a 9 x 9-inch baking dish, reserving some for the topping.
Put asparagus with juice over saltines. Next, layer with cheese, eggs, pimento and mushrooms.
Spread soup over casserole and top with remaining crumbled saltines.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until mixture bubbles.

title: kathy's tea cakes
directions: Mix thoroughly shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Blend in flour.
Heat oven to 400°.
Roll dough 1/8-inch thick on lightly floured surface.
Cut into desired shapes.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Cook only about 3 minutes.
Take out when bottoms are lightly browned.
Watch them closely; they are easy to burn.

title: low-fat pineapple cheesecake
directions: Boil juice; add jello.
Cool to lukewarm.
Process cottage cheese, flavorings and 1 tablespoon sugar.
Blend well.
Add juice mixture.
Blend 30 seconds more.
Pour in crust.
Refrigerate until well-formed.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix together cream cheese, sour cream, mayonnaise, lemon juice and Worcestershire and Tabasco sauces.
Stir until smooth.
Add horseradish, onion and shrimp.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours before serving.
Serve with chips.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Combine sugar, butter and cream; cook until a soft ball forms in cold water.
Add vanilla and peanut butter.
Beat until thick; pour in buttered plate.

title: pat's potato soup
directions: Use 2-quart pan.
Cook potatoes, onion and garlic.
(Note: Put just enough water to cover the potatoes and cook down until the potatoes are tender.
The water will have a very cloudy appearance; do not drain.)
Reduce heat and add butter.
Fill the remainder of the pan with milk.
Simmer until milk is warm. Thicken slightly with flour and water mixture.
Add salt and pepper.

title: cauliflower and broccoli salad
directions: Cut cauliflower and broccoli into flowerets.
Mix all vegetables.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over vegetables. Refrigerate and let set overnight.

title: crab thermidor(low calorie)
directions: About 30 minutes before serving, preheat oven to 350°.
Toast bread in oven until golden brown.
Turn; toast other side. Meanwhile in medium saucepan, melt margarine.
Stir in flour, stirring constantly.
Slowly add half and half.
Cook, stirring until thickened and smooth.
Stir in salt, nutmeg, paprika, pepper, garlic salt and sherry.
Add crab.
Heat, stirring, to simmering. Turn into 1-quart casserole dish; sprinkle with cheese.
Put in broiler until cheese melts and is golden.

title: glorified cabbage
directions: Cut cabbage in small pieces and boil until very tender in lightly salted water.
Saute onion, celery and garlic in butter. When wilted, add cheese and soup; heat until melted and well blended.
Place cabbage in casserole dish and pour sauce on top. Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350 degrees for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: taco salad dip
directions: Mix taco seasoning with sour cream and cream cheese.
Spread on cookie sheet or pizza pan.
Cut lettuce, tomato, onion and olives into small pieces and sprinkle them on top of the cream cheese mixture in layers.
Spread taco sauce over the top.
Shred about 3 cups of Cheddar cheese and sprinkle it on the top, also. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: cozy vegetable soup
directions: Heat olive oil in a Dutch oven over medium-high heat. Add cabbage and next 5 ingredients; saute 2 minutes. Add water and vegetable broth; bring to a boil. Cover, reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes. Add remaining ingredients and cook until thoroughly heated. Makes 4 servings.

title: jeanne's chocolate mochi cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Melt margarine and chocolate chips together and combine with the evaporated milk, vanilla and eggs.
Mix well and stir into the dry ingredients until it becomes a smooth batter.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: wild rice waldorf salad
directions: Wash rice thoroughly; place in heavy saucepan with 3 1/3 cups of water.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and cover.
Simmer 45 to 60 minutes or until rice has puffed and most of liquid is absorbed.
Chill cooked rice.

title: tasty meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Place in greased loaf pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes or until top is bubbly and brown.

title: mexican style black-eyed peas
directions: Combine onion, garlic and bacon.
Cook until bacon is brown. Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Cook chicken, debone and cut into bite-size pieces.
Place in bottom of large casserole dish.
Spread stuffing mix over chicken. Sprinkle celery and onion over this.
Mix soups and broth.
Pour over casserole.
Bake at 350° until done (30 to 40 minutes).

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, oats, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Set aside.
Cream butter gradually, adding sugars, beating until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix well. Alternate additions of dry ingredients and pumpkin, mixing well after each addition.
Stir in morsels.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until they are firm and light brown.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients and place in a greased 2-quart flat baking dish.
Top with cracker crumbs and pat with 1/2 stick butter or oleo.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until bubbly throughout and topping is nicely browned.

title: imperial salad freeze
directions: Mash bananas and blend with all other ingredients.
Fill cupcake liners in muffin pans and freeze.

title: lime mallow salad
directions: Heat marshmallows and milk until dissolved.
Stir gel until dissolved, chill until it begins to thicken.
Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Add to jello and marshmallow mix.
Add crushed pineapple, Cool Whip and nuts; mix well.
Turn into mold or pan (11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch).
Chill to firm.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: fresh peach meringue pie
directions: Cream butter, sugar and flour together. Add the 3 egg yolks plus one whole egg.
Beat well.
Fold in peaches and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° until firm.
Add meringue while pie is hot.

title: old fashion brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in a 14 x 9 x 2-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chuck roast in foil
directions: Place roast in center of foil in a roasting pan.
Brush meat with steak sauce.
Sprinkle the onion soup mix over it.
Spread with mushroom soup.
Add about 1/4 can of water.
Wrap loosely in foil and bake 2 1/2 to 3 hours at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: new england baked beans
directions: Soak beans overnight in water (8 to 12 hours).
Boil beans for approximately 30 minutes.
Drain and place in a large Pyrex bowl.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Mix cake mix, egg and butter, then press into 9 x 13-inch pan. Beat sugar, 2 eggs and cream cheese 3 minutes.
Pour onto first mixture and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Press out crescent rolls onto a cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Mix the cream cheese, sour cream, dressing mix and mayonnaise together.
Spread on rolls.
Top with desired vegetables.
Press vegetables into roll mix (use wax paper). Refrigerate and cut into squares.
